 64 Array.deleteFirst = function(obj) {
 65   for (var i=0; i<this.length; i++) {
 66     if (this[i] == obj) {
 67       this.splice(i,1)
 68       return true
 69     }
 70   }
 71   return false
 72 }
 73 
 74 Array.stableSort = function(cmp) { 
 75   // hack to work around Chrome's qsort
 76   for(var i=0; i<this.length; i++) {
 77     this[i].__arrayPos = i;
 78   }
 79   return this.sort(Array.__stableSorter(cmp));
 80 }
 81 Array.__stableSorter = function(cmp) {
 82   return (function(c1, c2) {
 83     var r = cmp(c1,c2);
 84     if (!r) { // hack to work around Chrome's qsort
 85       return c1.__arrayPos - c2.__arrayPos
 86     }
 87     return r;
 88   });
 89 }

 91 Array.equals = function(array) {
 92   if (!array) return false
 93   if (this.length != array.length) return false
 94   for (var i=0; i<this.length; i++) {
 95     var a = this[i]
 96     var b = array[i]
 97     if (a.equals && typeof(a.equals) == 'function') {
 98       if (!a.equals(b)) return false
 99     } else if (a != b) {
100       return false
101     }
102   }
103   return true
104 }
105 
106 Array.rotate = function(backToFront) {
107   if (backToFront) {
108     this.unshift(this.pop())
109     return this[0]
110   } else {
111     this.push(this.shift())
112     return this[this.length-1]
113   }
114 }
115 
116 Array.pick = function() {
117   return this[Math.floor(Math.random()*this.length)]
118 }
119 
120 Array.flatten = function() {
121   var a = []
122   for (var i=0; i<this.length; i++) {
123     var e = this[i]
124     if (e.flatten) {
125       var ef = e.flatten()
126       for (var j=0; j<ef.length; j++) {
127         a[a.length] = ef[j]
128       }
129     } else {
130       a[a.length] = e
131     }
132   }
133   return a
134 }
135 
136 Array.take = function() {
137   var a = []
138   for (var i=0; i<this.length; i++) {
139     var e = []
140     for (var j=0; j<arguments.length; j++) {
141       e[j] = this[i][arguments[j]]
142     }
143     a[i] = e
144   }
145   return a
146 }

158 Array.set = function(key, value) {
159   for (var i=0; i<this.length; i++) {

161   }

164 Array.allWith = function() {
165   var a = []
166   topLoop:
167   for (var i=0; i<this.length; i++) {
168     var e = this[i]
169     for (var j=0; j<arguments.length; j++) {
170       if (!this[i][arguments[j]])
171         continue topLoop
172     }
173     a[a.length] = e
174   }
175   return a
176 }

180 if (!Function.prototype.bind) {
181   /**
182      * Creates a function that calls this function in the scope of the given
183      * object.
184      * 
185      * var obj = { x: 'obj' } var f = function() { return this.x } window.x =
186      * 'window' f() // => 'window' var g = f.bind(obj) g() // => 'obj'
187      * 
188      * @param object
189      *            Object to bind this function to
190      * @return Function bound to object
191      * @addon
192      */
193   Function.prototype.bind = function(object) {
194     var t = this
195     return function() {
196       return t.apply(object, arguments)
197     }
198   }
199 }

212 if (!Array.indexOf) {
213   /**
214      * Returns the index of obj if it is in the array. Returns -1 otherwise.
215      * 
216      * @param obj
217      *            The object to find from the array.
218      * @return The index of obj or -1 if obj isn't in the array.
219      * @addon
220      */
221   Array.indexOf = function(obj) {
222     for (var i=0; i<this.length; i++)
223       if (obj == this[i]) return i
224     return -1
225   }
226 }
227 if (!Array.includes) {
228   /**
229      * Returns true if obj is in the array. Returns false if it isn't.
230      * 
231      * @param obj
232      *            The object to find from the array.
233      * @return True if obj is in the array, false if it isn't
234      * @addon
235      */
236   Array.includes = function(obj) {
237     return (this.indexOf(obj) !== -1);
238   }
239 }
240 /**
241  * Iterate function f over each element of the array and return an array of the
242  * return values.
243  * 
244  * @param f
245  *            Function to apply to each element
246  * @return An array of return values from applying f on each element of the
247  *         array
248  * @type Array
249  * @addon
250  */
251 Array.map = function(f) {
252   var na = new Array(this.length)
253   if (f)
254     for (var i=0; i<this.length; i++) na[i] = f(this[i], i, this)
255   else
256     for (var i=0; i<this.length; i++) na[i] = this[i]
257   return na
258 }
259 Array.forEach = function(f) {
260   for (var i=0; i<this.length; i++) f(this[i], i, this)
261 }
262 if (!Array.reduce) {
263   Array.reduce = function(f, s) {
264     var i = 0
265     if (arguments.length == 1) {
266       s = this[0]
267       i++
268     }
269     for(; i<this.length; i++) {
270       s = f(s, this[i], i, this)
271     }
272     return s
273   }
274 }
275 if (!Array.find) {
276   Array.find = function(f) {
277     for(var i=0; i<this.length; i++) {
278       if (f(this[i], i, this)) return this[i]
279     }
280   }
281 }

313      *         inside string escaped.

358 if (!Math.sinh) {
359   /**
360      * Returns the hyperbolic sine of x.
361      * 
362      * @param x
363      *            The value for x
364      * @return The hyperbolic sine of x
365      * @addon
366      */
367   Math.sinh = function(x) {
368     return 0.5 * (Math.exp(x) - Math.exp(-x))
369   }
370   /**
371      * Returns the inverse hyperbolic sine of x.
372      * 
373      * @param x
374      *            The value for x
375      * @return The inverse hyperbolic sine of x
376      * @addon
377      */
378   Math.asinh = function(x) {
379     return Math.log(x + Math.sqrt(x*x + 1))
380   }
381 }
382 if (!Math.cosh) {
383   /**
384      * Returns the hyperbolic cosine of x.
385      * 
386      * @param x
387      *            The value for x
388      * @return The hyperbolic cosine of x
389      * @addon
390      */
391   Math.cosh = function(x) {
392     return 0.5 * (Math.exp(x) + Math.exp(-x))
393   }
394   /**
395      * Returns the inverse hyperbolic cosine of x.
396      * 
397      * @param x
398      *            The value for x
399      * @return The inverse hyperbolic cosine of x
400      * @addon
401      */
402   Math.acosh = function(x) {
403     return Math.log(x + Math.sqrt(x*x - 1))
404   }
405 }

407 function logStackTrace(levels) {
408     var c = console;
409     var callstack = [];
410     var isCallstackPopulated = false;
411     try {
412         throw new Error();
413     } catch (e) {
414         if (e.stack) { //Firefox
415             var lines = e.stack.split('\n');
416             for (var i = 0, len = lines.length; i < len; i++) {
417                 if (lines[i].match(/^\s*[A-Za-z0-9\-_\$]+\(/)) {
418                     callstack.push(lines[i]);
419                 }
420             }
421             //Remove call to logStackTrace()
422             callstack.shift();
423             isCallstackPopulated = true;
424         }
425         else if (window.opera && e.message) { //Opera
426             var lines = e.message.split('\n');
427             for (var i = 0, len = lines.length; i < len; i++) {
428                 if (lines[i].match(/^\s*[A-Za-z0-9\-_\$]+\(/)) {
429                     var entry = lines[i];
430                     //Append next line also since it has the file info
431                     if (lines[i + 1]) {
432                         entry += " at " + lines[i + 1];
433                         i++;
434                     }
435                     callstack.push(entry);
436                 }
437             }
438             //Remove call to logStackTrace()
439             callstack.shift();
440             isCallstackPopulated = true;
441         }
442     }
443     if (!isCallstackPopulated) { //IE and Safari
444         var currentFunction = arguments.callee.caller;
445         while (currentFunction) {
446             var fn = currentFunction.toString();
447             var fname = fn.substring(fn.indexOf("function") + 8, fn.indexOf("(")) || "anonymous";
448             callstack.push(fname);
449             currentFunction = currentFunction.caller;
450         }
451     }
452     if (levels) {
453         c.log(callstack.slice(0, levels).join('\n'));
454     }
455     else {
456         c.log(callstack.join('\n'));
457     }
458 };

460 /**
461  * Creates and configures a DOM element.
462  * 
463  * The tag of the element is given by name.
464  * 
465  * If params is a string, it is used as the innerHTML of the created element. If
466  * params is a DOM element, it is appended to the created element. If params is
467  * an object, it is treated as a config object and merged with the created
468  * element.
469  * 
470  * If params is a string or DOM element, the third argument is treated as the
471  * config object.
472  * 
473  * Special attributes of the config object: content - if content is a string, it
474  * is used as the innerHTML of the created element - if content is an element,
475  * it is appended to the created element style - the style object is merged with
476  * the created element's style
477  * 
478  * @param {String}
479  *            name The tag for the created element
480  * @param params
481  *            The content or config for the created element
482  * @param config
483  *            The config for the created element if params is content
484  * @return The created DOM element
485  */
486 E = function(name, params, config) {
487   var el = document.createElement(name)
488   if (params) {
489     if (typeof(params) == 'string') {
490       el.innerHTML = params
491       params = config
492     } else if (params.DOCUMENT_NODE) {
493       el.appendChild(params)
494       params = config
495     }
496     if (params) {
497       if (params.style) {
498         var style = params.style
499         params = Object.clone(params)
500         delete params.style
501         Object.forceExtend(el.style, style)
502       }
503       if (params.content) {
504         if (typeof(params.content) == 'string') {
505           el.appendChild(T(params.content))
506         } else {
507           el.appendChild(params.content)
508         }
509         params = Object.clone(params)
510         delete params.content
511       }
512       Object.forceExtend(el, params)
513     }
514   }
515   return el
516 }
517 E.append = function(node) {
518   for(var i=1; i<arguments.length; i++) {
519     if (typeof(arguments[i]) == 'string') {
520       node.appendChild(T(arguments[i]))
521     } else {
522       node.appendChild(arguments[i])
523     }
524   }
525 }
526 // Safari requires each canvas to have a unique id.
527 E.lastCanvasId = 0
528 /**
529  * Creates and returns a canvas element with width w and height h.
530  * 
531  * @param {int}
532  *            w The width for the canvas
533  * @param {int}
534  *            h The height for the canvas
535  * @param config
536  *            Optional config object to pass to E()
537  * @return The created canvas element
538  */
539 E.canvas = function(w,h,config) {
540   var id = 'canvas-uuid-' + E.lastCanvasId
541   E.lastCanvasId++
542   if (!config) config = {}
543   return E('canvas', Object.extend(config, {id: id, width: w, height: h}))
544 }

557 /**
558  * Merges the src object's attributes with the dst object, ignoring errors.
559  * 
560  * @param dst
561  *            The destination object
562  * @param src
563  *            The source object
564  * @return The dst object
565  * @addon
566  */
567 Object.forceExtend = function(dst, src) {
568   for (var i in src) {
569     try{ dst[i] = src[i] } catch(e) {}
570   }
571   return dst
572 }
573 // In case Object.extend isn't defined already, set it to Object.forceExtend.
574 //if (!Object.extend)
575 //  Object.extend = Object.forceExtend
576 Object.extend = function(dst, src) {
577 	for(var i in src)
578 	   dst[i] = src[i];
579 	   
580 	return dst;
581 }
582 
583 /**
584  * Merges the src object's attributes with the dst object, preserving all dst
585  * object's current attributes.
586  * 
587  * @param dst
588  *            The destination object
589  * @param src
590  *            The source object
591  * @return The dst object
592  * @addon
593  */
594 Object.conditionalExtend = function(dst, src) {
595   for (var i in src) {
596     if (dst[i] == null)
597       dst[i] = src[i]
598   }
599   return dst
600 }

602 /**
603  * Creates and returns a shallow copy of the src object.
604  * 
605  * @param src
606  *            The source object
607  * @return A clone of the src object
608  * @addon
609  */
610 Object.clone = function(src) {
611   if (!src || src == true)
612     return src
613   switch (typeof(src)) {
614     case 'string':
615       return Object.extend(src+'', src)
616       break
617     case 'number':
618       return src
619       break
620     case 'function':
621       obj = eval(src.toSource())
622       return Object.extend(obj, src)
623       break
624     case 'object':
625       if (src instanceof Array) {
626         return Object.extend([], src)
627       } else {
628         return Object.extend({}, src)
629       }
630       break
631   }
632 }

634 /**
635  * Creates and returns an Image object, with source URL set to src and onload
636  * handler set to onload.
637  * 
638  * @param {String}
639  *            src The source URL for the image
640  * @param {Function}
641  *            onload The onload handler for the image
642  * @return The created Image object
643  * @type {Image}
644  */
645 Object.loadImage = function(src, onload) {
646   var img = new Image()
647   if (onload)
648     img.onload = onload
649   img.src = src
650   return img

653 /**
654  * Returns true if image is fully loaded and ready for use.
655  * 
656  * @param image
657  *            The image to check
658  * @return Whether the image is loaded or not
659  * @type {boolean}
660  * @addon
661  */
662 Object.isImageLoaded = function(image) {
663   if(!image) return false;
664   if (image.tagName == 'CANVAS') return true
665   if (!image.complete) return false
666   if (image.naturalWidth == null) return true
667   return !!image.naturalWidth
668 }

670 /**
671  * Sums two objects.
672  */
673 Object.sum = function(a,b) {
674   if (a instanceof Array) {
675     if (b instanceof Array) {
676       var ab = []
677       for (var i=0; i<a.length; i++) {
678         ab[i] = a[i] + b[i]
679       }
680       return ab
681     } else {
682       return a.map(function(v){ return v + b })
683     }
684   } else if (b instanceof Array) {
685     return b.map(function(v){ return v + a })
686   } else {
687     return a + b
688   }
689 }
690 
691 /**
692  * Substracts b from a.
693  */
694 Object.sub = function(a,b) {
695   if (a instanceof Array) {
696     if (b instanceof Array) {
697       var ab = []
698       for (var i=0; i<a.length; i++) {
699         ab[i] = a[i] - b[i]
700       }
701       return ab
702     } else {
703       return a.map(function(v){ return v - b })
704     }
705   } else if (b instanceof Array) {
706     return b.map(function(v){ return a - v })
707   } else {
708     return a - b
709   }
710 }

715 if (!window.Mouse) Mouse = {}
716 /**
717  * Returns the coordinates for a mouse event relative to element. Element must
718  * be the target for the event.
719  * 
720  * @param element
721  *            The element to compare against
722  * @param event
723  *            The mouse event
724  * @return An object of form {x: relative_x, y: relative_y}
725  */
726 Mouse.getRelativeCoords = function(element, event) {
727   var xy = {x:0, y:0}
728   var osl = 0
729   var ost = 0
730   var el = element
731   
732   /*if(event.offsetX !== undefined) {
733     xy.x = event.offsetX
734     xy.y = event.offsetY
735 
736     return xy
737   }*/
738   
739   while (el) {
740     osl += (el.offsetLeft || el.offsetX || 0)
741     ost += (el.offsetTop || el.offsetY || 0)
742     el = el.offsetParent
743   }
744   xy.x = (event.pageX || event.clientX) - osl
745   xy.y = (event.pageY || event.clientY) - ost
746   return xy
747 }

749 Browser = (function(){
750   var ua = window.navigator.userAgent
751   var khtml = ua.match(/KHTML/)
752   var gecko = ua.match(/Gecko/)
753   var webkit = ua.match(/WebKit\/\d+/)
754   var ie = ua.match(/Explorer/)
755   if (khtml) return 'KHTML'
756   if (gecko) return 'Gecko'
757   if (webkit) return 'Webkit'
758   if (ie) return 'IE'
759   return 'UNKNOWN'
760 })()

772 Function.prototype.Extenze = function(base, interfaces) {
773     var o = this.prototype;
774     
775     var binit = base.prototype.initialize;
776     //base.prototype.initialize = function() {};
777     this.prototype = new base;
778     //base.prototype.initialize = binit;
779     
780        
781     interfaces = interfaces || [];
782     if(!interfaces.pop && !interfaces.concat)
783        interfaces = [interfaces];
784        
785     for(var n = 0 ; n < interfaces.length ; n++) {
786         var inf = interfaces[n];
787         
788         if(inf.prototype) for(var i in inf.prototype)
789           this.prototype[i] = inf.prototype[i];
790         else for(var i in inf)
791           this.prototype[i] = inf[i];
792     }
793     
794     for(var i in o)
795        this.prototype[i] = o[i];
796        
797     var main_init = this.prototype.initialize;
798     this.prototype.initialize = function() {
799         //binit.apply(this, arguments);
800         for(var i in interfaces) {
801             var a = (interfaces[i].prototype || interfaces[i]);
802             if(a.initialize) a.initialize.apply(this, arguments); 
803         }
804         main_init.apply(this, arguments);
805     };
806 
807     for(var i in this.prototype)
808        this[i] = this.prototype[i];
809 };
810 
811 /**
812  * Klass is a function that returns a constructor function.
813  * 
814  * The constructor function calls #initialize with its arguments.
815  * 
816  * The parameters to Klass have their prototypes or themselves merged with the
817  * constructor function's prototype.
818  * 
819  * Finally, the constructor function's prototype is merged with the constructor
820  * function. So you can write Shape.getArea.call(this) instead of
821  * Shape.prototype.getArea.call(this).
822  * 
823  * Shape = Klass({ getArea : function() { raise('No area defined!') } })
824  * 
825  * Rectangle = Klass(Shape, { initialize : function(x, y) { this.x = x this.y =
826  * y },
827  * 
828  * getArea : function() { return this.x * this.y } })
829  * 
830  * Square = Klass(Rectangle, { initialize : function(s) {
831  * Rectangle.initialize.call(this, s, s) } })
832  * 
833  * new Square(5).getArea() //=> 25
834  * 
835  * @return Constructor object for the class
836  */
837 
838 Klass = function() {
839   var c = function() {
840     this.initialize.apply(this, arguments)
841   }
842   c.ancestors = $A(arguments)
843   var prot = c.prototype = {__createdArgs: arguments}
844   for(var i = 0; i<arguments.length; i++) {
845     var a = arguments[i]
846     if (a.prototype) {
847       Object.extend(c.prototype, a.prototype)
848     } else {
849       Object.extend(c.prototype, a)
850     }
851   }
852   Object.extend(c, c.prototype)
853   c.prototype = prot;
854   
855   return c
856 }

862  * @param config Values to be copied to the event.
863  */
864 function GenericEvent(type, config, bubbles, cancelable) {
865 	this.type = type;
866 	
867 	//this.__proto__.initEvent(type, bubbles || false, cancelable || false);
868     for(var i in config)
869         this[i] = config[i];
870 }
871 //GenericEvent.prototype = document.createEvent('Events');
872 GenericEvent.prototype = Event.prototype;

874 Curves = {
875   angularDistance : function(a, b) {
876     var pi2 = Math.PI*2
877     var d = (b - a) % pi2
878     if (d > Math.PI) d -= pi2
879     if (d < -Math.PI) d += pi2
880     return d
881   },
882 
883   linePoint : function(a, b, t) {
884     return [a[0]+(b[0]-a[0])*t, a[1]+(b[1]-a[1])*t]
885   },
886 
887   quadraticPoint : function(a, b, c, t) {
888     // var d = this.linePoint(a,b,t)
889     // var e = this.linePoint(b,c,t)
890     // return this.linePoint(d,e,t)
891     var dx = a[0]+(b[0]-a[0])*t
892     var ex = b[0]+(c[0]-b[0])*t
893     var x = dx+(ex-dx)*t
894     var dy = a[1]+(b[1]-a[1])*t
895     var ey = b[1]+(c[1]-b[1])*t
896     var y = dy+(ey-dy)*t
897     return [x,y]
898   },
899 
900   cubicPoint : function(a, b, c, d, t) {
901     var ax3 = a[0]*3
902     var bx3 = b[0]*3
903     var cx3 = c[0]*3
904     var ay3 = a[1]*3
905     var by3 = b[1]*3
906     var cy3 = c[1]*3
907     return [
908       a[0] + t*(bx3 - ax3 + t*(ax3-2*bx3+cx3 + t*(bx3-a[0]-cx3+d[0]))),
909       a[1] + t*(by3 - ay3 + t*(ay3-2*by3+cy3 + t*(by3-a[1]-cy3+d[1])))
910     ]
911   },
912 
913   linearValue : function(a,b,t) {
914     return a + (b-a)*t
915   },
916 
917   quadraticValue : function(a,b,c,t) {
918     var d = a + (b-a)*t
919     var e = b + (c-b)*t
920     return d + (e-d)*t
921   },
922 
923   cubicValue : function(a,b,c,d,t) {
924     var a3 = a*3, b3 = b*3, c3 = c*3
925     return a + t*(b3 - a3 + t*(a3-2*b3+c3 + t*(b3-a-c3+d)))
926   },
927 
928   catmullRomPoint : function (a,b,c,d, t) {
929     var af = ((-t+2)*t-1)*t*0.5
930     var bf = (((3*t-5)*t)*t+2)*0.5
931     var cf = ((-3*t+4)*t+1)*t*0.5
932     var df = ((t-1)*t*t)*0.5
933     return [
934       a[0]*af + b[0]*bf + c[0]*cf + d[0]*df,
935       a[1]*af + b[1]*bf + c[1]*cf + d[1]*df
936     ]
937   },
938 
939   catmullRomAngle : function (a,b,c,d, t) {
940     var dx = 0.5 * (c[0] - a[0] + 2*t*(2*a[0] - 5*b[0] + 4*c[0] - d[0]) +
941              3*t*t*(3*b[0] + d[0] - a[0] - 3*c[0]))
942     var dy = 0.5 * (c[1] - a[1] + 2*t*(2*a[1] - 5*b[1] + 4*c[1] - d[1]) +
943              3*t*t*(3*b[1] + d[1] - a[1] - 3*c[1]))
944     return Math.atan2(dy, dx)
945   },
946 
947   catmullRomPointAngle : function (a,b,c,d, t) {
948     var p = this.catmullRomPoint(a,b,c,d,t)
949     var a = this.catmullRomAngle(a,b,c,d,t)
950     return {point:p, angle:a}
951   },
952 
953   lineAngle : function(a,b) {
954     return Math.atan2(b[1]-a[1], b[0]-a[0])
955   },
956 
957   quadraticAngle : function(a,b,c,t) {
958     var d = this.linePoint(a,b,t)
959     var e = this.linePoint(b,c,t)
960     return this.lineAngle(d,e)
961   },
962 
963   cubicAngle : function(a, b, c, d, t) {
964     var e = this.quadraticPoint(a,b,c,t)
965     var f = this.quadraticPoint(b,c,d,t)
966     return this.lineAngle(e,f)
967   },
968 
969   lineLength : function(a,b) {
970     var x = (b[0]-a[0])
971     var y = (b[1]-a[1])
972     return Math.sqrt(x*x + y*y)
973   },
974 
975   squareLineLength : function(a,b) {
976     var x = (b[0]-a[0])
977     var y = (b[1]-a[1])
978     return x*x + y*y
979   },
980 
981   quadraticLength : function(a,b,c, error) {
982     var p1 = this.linePoint(a,b,2/3)
983     var p2 = this.linePoint(b,c,1/3)
984     return this.cubicLength(a,p1,p2,c, error)
985   },
986 
987   cubicLength : (function() {
988     var bezsplit = function(v) {
989       var vtemp = [v.slice(0)]
990 
991       for (var i=1; i < 4; i++) {
992         vtemp[i] = [[],[],[],[]]
993         for (var j=0; j < 4-i; j++) {
994           vtemp[i][j][0] = 0.5 * (vtemp[i-1][j][0] + vtemp[i-1][j+1][0])
995           vtemp[i][j][1] = 0.5 * (vtemp[i-1][j][1] + vtemp[i-1][j+1][1])
996         }
997       }
998       var left = []
999       var right = []
1000       for (var j=0; j<4; j++) {
1001         left[j] = vtemp[j][0]
1002         right[j] = vtemp[3-j][j]
1003       }
1004       return [left, right]
1005     }
1006 
1007     var addifclose = function(v, error) {
1008       var len = 0
1009       for (var i=0; i < 3; i++) {
1010         len += Curves.lineLength(v[i], v[i+1])
1011       }
1012       var chord = Curves.lineLength(v[0], v[3])
1013       if ((len - chord) > error) {
1014         var lr = bezsplit(v)
1015         len = addifclose(lr[0], error) + addifclose(lr[1], error)
1016       }
1017       return len
1018     }
1019 
1020     return function(a,b,c,d, error) {
1021       if (!error) error = 1
1022       return addifclose([a,b,c,d], error)
1023     }
1024   })(),
1025 
1026   quadraticLengthPointAngle : function(a,b,c,lt,error) {
1027     var p1 = this.linePoint(a,b,2/3)
1028     var p2 = this.linePoint(b,c,1/3)
1029     return this.cubicLengthPointAngle(a,p1,p2,c, error)
1030   },
1031 
1032   cubicLengthPointAngle : function(a,b,c,d,lt,error) {
1033     // this thing outright rapes the GC.
1034     // how about not creating a billion arrays, hmm?
1035     var len = this.cubicLength(a,b,c,d,error)
1036     var point = a
1037     var prevpoint = a
1038     var lengths = []
1039     var prevlensum = 0
1040     var lensum = 0
1041     var tl = lt*len
1042     var segs = 20
1043     var fac = 1/segs
1044     for (var i=1; i<=segs; i++) { // FIXME get smarter
1045       prevpoint = point
1046       point = this.cubicPoint(a,b,c,d, fac*i)
1047       prevlensum = lensum
1048       lensum += this.lineLength(prevpoint, point)
1049       if (lensum >= tl) {
1050         if (lensum == prevlensum)
1051           return {point: point, angle: this.lineAngle(a,b)}
1052         var dl = lensum - tl
1053         var dt = dl / (lensum-prevlensum)
1054         return {point: this.linePoint(prevpoint, point, 1-dt),
1055                 angle: this.cubicAngle(a,b,c,d, fac*(i-dt)) }
1056       }
1057     }
1058     return {point: d.slice(0), angle: this.lineAngle(c,d)}
1059   }
1060 
1061 }

1065 /**
1066  * Color helper functions.
1067  */
1068 Colors = {
1069 
1070   /**
1071      * Converts an HSL color to its corresponding RGB color.
1072      * 
1073      * @param h
1074      *            Hue in degrees (0 .. 359)
1075      * @param s
1076      *            Saturation (0.0 .. 1.0)
1077      * @param l
1078      *            Lightness (0 .. 255)
1079      * @return The corresponding RGB color as [r,g,b]
1080      * @type Array
1081      */
1082   hsl2rgb : function(h,s,l) {
1083     var r,g,b
1084     if (s == 0) {
1085       r=g=b=v
1086     } else {
1087       var q = (l < 0.5 ? l * (1+s) : l+s-(l*s))
1088       var p = 2 * l - q
1089       var hk = (h % 360) / 360
1090       var tr = hk + 1/3
1091       var tg = hk
1092       var tb = hk - 1/3
1093       if (tr < 0) tr++
1094       if (tr > 1) tr--
1095       if (tg < 0) tg++
1096       if (tg > 1) tg--
1097       if (tb < 0) tb++
1098       if (tb > 1) tb--
1099       if (tr < 1/6)
1100         r = p + ((q-p)*6*tr)
1101       else if (tr < 1/2)
1102         r = q
1103       else if (tr < 2/3)
1104         r = p + ((q-p)*6*(2/3 - tr))
1105       else
1106         r = p
1107 
1108       if (tg < 1/6)
1109         g = p + ((q-p)*6*tg)
1110       else if (tg < 1/2)
1111         g = q
1112       else if (tg < 2/3)
1113         g = p + ((q-p)*6*(2/3 - tg))
1114       else
1115         g = p
1116 
1117       if (tb < 1/6)
1118         b = p + ((q-p)*6*tb)
1119       else if (tb < 1/2)
1120         b = q
1121       else if (tb < 2/3)
1122         b = p + ((q-p)*6*(2/3 - tb))
1123       else
1124         b = p
1125     }
1126 
1127     return [r,g,b]
1128   },
1129 
1130   /**
1131      * Converts an HSV color to its corresponding RGB color.
1132      * 
1133      * @param h
1134      *            Hue in degrees (0 .. 359)
1135      * @param s
1136      *            Saturation (0.0 .. 1.0)
1137      * @param v
1138      *            Value (0 .. 255)
1139      * @return The corresponding RGB color as [r,g,b]
1140      * @type Array
1141      */
1142   hsv2rgb : function(h,s,v) {
1143     var r,g,b
1144     if (s == 0) {
1145       r=g=b=v
1146     } else {
1147       h = (h % 360)/60.0
1148       var i = Math.floor(h)
1149       var f = h-i
1150       var p = v * (1-s)
1151       var q = v * (1-s*f)
1152       var t = v * (1-s*(1-f))
1153       switch (i) {
1154         case 0:
1155           r = v
1156           g = t
1157           b = p
1158           break
1159         case 1:
1160           r = q
1161           g = v
1162           b = p
1163           break
1164         case 2:
1165           r = p
1166           g = v
1167           b = t
1168           break
1169         case 3:
1170           r = p
1171           g = q
1172           b = v
1173           break
1174         case 4:
1175           r = t
1176           g = p
1177           b = v
1178           break
1179         case 5:
1180           r = v
1181           g = p
1182           b = q
1183           break
1184       }
1185     }
1186     return [r,g,b]
1187   },
1188 
1189   /**
1190      * Parses a color style object into one that can be used with the given
1191      * canvas context.
1192      * 
1193      * Accepted formats: 'white' '#fff' '#ffffff' 'rgba(255,255,255, 1.0)' [255,
1194      * 255, 255] [255, 255, 255, 1.0] new Gradient(...) new Pattern(...)
1195      * 
1196      * @param style
1197      *            The color style to parse
1198      * @param ctx
1199      *            Canvas 2D context on which the style is to be used
1200      * @return A parsed style, ready to be used as ctx.fillStyle / strokeStyle
1201      */
1202   parseColorStyle : function(style, ctx) {
1203     if (typeof style == 'string') {
1204       return style
1205     } else if (style.compiled) {
1206       return style.compiled
1207     } else if (style.isPattern) {
1208       return style.compile(ctx)
1209     } else if (style.length == 3) {
1210       return 'rgba('+style.map(Math.round).join(",")+', 1)'
1211     } else if (style.length == 4) {
1212       return 'rgba('+
1213               Math.round(style[0])+','+
1214               Math.round(style[1])+','+
1215               Math.round(style[2])+','+
1216               style[3]+
1217              ')'
1218     } else { // wtf
1219       throw( "Bad style: " + style )
1220     }
1221   }
1222 }

1251 /**
1252  * Navigating around differing implementations of canvas features.
1253  * 
1254  * Current issues:
1255  * 
1256  * isPointInPath(x,y):
1257  * 
1258  * Opera supports isPointInPath.
1259  * 
1260  * Safari doesn't have isPointInPath. So you need to keep track of the CTM and
1261  * do your own in-fill-checking. Which is done for circles and rectangles in
1262  * Circle#isPointInPath and Rectangle#isPointInPath. Paths use an inaccurate
1263  * bounding box test, implemented in Path#isPointInPath.
1264  * 
1265  * Firefox 3 has isPointInPath. But it uses user-space coordinates. Which can be
1266  * easily navigated around because it has setTransform.
1267  * 
1268  * Firefox 2 has isPointInPath. But it uses user-space coordinates. And there's
1269  * no setTransform, so you need to keep track of the CTM and multiply the mouse
1270  * vector with the CTM's inverse.
1271  * 
1272  * Drawing text:
1273  * 
1274  * Rhino has ctx.drawString(x,y, text)
1275  * 
1276  * Firefox has ctx.mozDrawText(text)
1277  * 
1278  * The WhatWG spec, Safari and Opera have nothing.
1279  * 
1280  * @namespace
1281  */
1282 CanvasSupport = {
1283   DEVICE_SPACE : 0, // Opera
1284   USER_SPACE : 1,   // Fx2, Fx3
1285   isPointInPathMode : null,
1286   supportsIsPointInPath : null,
1287   supportsCSSTransform : null,
1288   supportsCanvas : null,
1289 
1290   isCanvasSupported : function() {
1291     if (this.supportsCanvas == null) {
1292       var e = {};
1293       try { e = E('canvas'); } catch(x) {}
1294       this.supportsCanvas = (e.getContext != null);
1295     }
1296     return this.supportsCanvas;
1297   },
1298 
1299   isCSSTransformSupported : function() {
1300     if (this.supportsCSSTransform == null) {
1301       var e = E('div')
1302       var dbs = e.style
1303       var s = (dbs.webkitTransform != null || dbs.mozTransform != null)
1304       this.supportsCSSTransform = (s != null)
1305     }
1306     return this.supportsCSSTransform
1307   },
1308

1311       var c = E.canvas(1,1)

1315   },

1395     }

1397     e.sound = soundManager.getSoundById(sid)
1398     e.sound.options.onfinish = e._onfinish.bind(e)

1430 
1431   /**
1432      * Multiplies two 3x2 affine 2D column-major transformation matrices with
1433      * each other and stores the result in the first matrix.
1434      * 
1435      * Returns the multiplied matrix m1.
1436      */
1437   tMatrixMultiply : function(m1, m2) {
1438     var m11 = m1[0]*m2[0] + m1[2]*m2[1]
1439     var m12 = m1[1]*m2[0] + m1[3]*m2[1]
1440 
1441     var m21 = m1[0]*m2[2] + m1[2]*m2[3]
1442     var m22 = m1[1]*m2[2] + m1[3]*m2[3]
1443 
1444     var dx = m1[0]*m2[4] + m1[2]*m2[5] + m1[4]
1445     var dy = m1[1]*m2[4] + m1[3]*m2[5] + m1[5]
1446 
1447     m1[0] = m11
1448     m1[1] = m12
1449     m1[2] = m21
1450     m1[3] = m22
1451     m1[4] = dx
1452     m1[5] = dy
1453 
1454     return m1
1455   },
1456 
1457   /**
1458      * Multiplies the vector [x, y, 1] with the 3x2 transformation matrix m.
1459      */
1460   tMatrixMultiplyPoint : function(m, x, y) {
1461     return [
1462       x*m[0] + y*m[2] + m[4],
1463       x*m[1] + y*m[3] + m[5]
1464     ]
1465   },
1466 
1467   /**
1468      * Inverts a 3x2 affine 2D column-major transformation matrix.
1469      * 
1470      * Returns an inverted copy of the matrix.
1471      */
1472   tInvertMatrix : function(m) {
1473     var d = 1 / (m[0]*m[3]-m[1]*m[2])
1474     return [
1475       m[3]*d, -m[1]*d,
1476       -m[2]*d, m[0]*d,
1477       d*(m[2]*m[5]-m[3]*m[4]), d*(m[1]*m[4]-m[0]*m[5])
1478     ]
1479   },
1480 
1481   /**
1482      * Applies a transformation matrix m on the canvas context ctx.
1483      */
1484   transform : function(ctx, m) {
1485     if (ctx.transform)
1486       return ctx.transform.apply(ctx, m)
1487     ctx.translate(m[4], m[5])
1488     // scale
1489     if (Math.abs(m[1]) < 1e-6 && Math.abs(m[2]) < 1e-6) {
1490       ctx.scale(m[0], m[3])
1491       return
1492     }
1493     var res = this.svdTransform({xx:m[0], xy:m[2], yx:m[1], yy:m[3], dx:m[4], dy:m[5]})
1494     ctx.rotate(res.angle2)
1495     ctx.scale(res.sx, res.sy)
1496     ctx.rotate(res.angle1)
1497     return
1498   },
1499 
1500   // broken svd...
1501   brokenSvd : function(m) {
1502     var mt = [m[0], m[2], m[1], m[3], 0,0]
1503     var mtm = [
1504       mt[0]*m[0]+mt[2]*m[1],
1505       mt[1]*m[0]+mt[3]*m[1],
1506       mt[0]*m[2]+mt[2]*m[3],
1507       mt[1]*m[2]+mt[3]*m[3],
1508       0,0
1509     ]
1510     // (mtm[0]-x) * (mtm[3]-x) - (mtm[1]*mtm[2]) = 0
1511     // x*x - (mtm[0]+mtm[3])*x - (mtm[1]*mtm[2])+(mtm[0]*mtm[3]) = 0
1512     var a = 1
1513     var b = -(mtm[0]+mtm[3])
1514     var c = -(mtm[1]*mtm[2])+(mtm[0]*mtm[3])
1515     var d = Math.sqrt(b*b - 4*a*c)
1516     var c1 = (-b + d) / (2*a)
1517     var c2 = (-b - d) / (2*a)
1518     if (c1 < c2)
1519       var tmp = c1, c1 = c2, c2 = tmp
1520     var s1 = Math.sqrt(c1)
1521     var s2 = Math.sqrt(c2)
1522     var i_s = [1/s1, 0, 0, 1/s2, 0,0]
1523     // (mtm[0]-c1)*x1 + mtm[2]*x2 = 0
1524     // mtm[1]*x1 + (mtm[3]-c1)*x2 = 0
1525     // x2 = -(mtm[0]-c1)*x1 / mtm[2]
1526     var e = ((mtm[0]-c1)/mtm[2])
1527     var l = Math.sqrt(1 + e*e)
1528     var v00 = 1 / l
1529     var v10 = e / l
1530     var v11 = v00
1531     var v01 = -v10
1532     var v = [v00, v01, v10, v11, 0,0]
1533     var u = m.slice(0)
1534     this.tMatrixMultiply(u,v)
1535     this.tMatrixMultiply(u,i_s)
1536     return [u, [s1,0,0,s2,0,0], [v00, v10, v01, v11, 0, 0]]
1537   },
1538 
1539 
1540   svdTransform : (function(){
1541     // Copyright (c) 2004-2005, The Dojo Foundation
1542     // All Rights Reserved
1543     var m = {}
1544     m.Matrix2D = function(arg){
1545       // summary: a 2D matrix object
1546       // description: Normalizes a 2D matrix-like object. If arrays is passed,
1547       // all objects of the array are normalized and multiplied sequentially.
1548       // arg: Object
1549       // a 2D matrix-like object, a number, or an array of such objects
1550       if(arg){
1551         if(typeof arg == "number"){
1552           this.xx = this.yy = arg;
1553         }else if(arg instanceof Array){
1554           if(arg.length > 0){
1555             var matrix = m.normalize(arg[0]);
1556             // combine matrices
1557             for(var i = 1; i < arg.length; ++i){
1558               var l = matrix, r = m.normalize(arg[i]);
1559               matrix = new m.Matrix2D();
1560               matrix.xx = l.xx * r.xx + l.xy * r.yx;
1561               matrix.xy = l.xx * r.xy + l.xy * r.yy;
1562               matrix.yx = l.yx * r.xx + l.yy * r.yx;
1563               matrix.yy = l.yx * r.xy + l.yy * r.yy;
1564               matrix.dx = l.xx * r.dx + l.xy * r.dy + l.dx;
1565               matrix.dy = l.yx * r.dx + l.yy * r.dy + l.dy;
1566             }
1567             Object.extend(this, matrix);
1568           }
1569         }else{
1570           Object.extend(this, arg);
1571         }
1572       }
1573     }
1574     // ensure matrix 2D conformance
1575     m.normalize = function(matrix){
1576         // summary: converts an object to a matrix, if necessary
1577         // description: Converts any 2D matrix-like object or an array of
1578         // such objects to a valid dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D object.
1579         // matrix: Object: an object, which is converted to a matrix, if
1580         // necessary
1581         return (matrix instanceof m.Matrix2D) ? matrix : new m.Matrix2D(matrix); // dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D
1582     }
1583     m.multiply = function(matrix){
1584       // summary: combines matrices by multiplying them sequentially in the
1585         // given order
1586       // matrix: dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D...: a 2D matrix-like object,
1587       // all subsequent arguments are matrix-like objects too
1588       var M = m.normalize(matrix);
1589       // combine matrices
1590       for(var i = 1; i < arguments.length; ++i){
1591         var l = M, r = m.normalize(arguments[i]);
1592         M = new m.Matrix2D();
1593         M.xx = l.xx * r.xx + l.xy * r.yx;
1594         M.xy = l.xx * r.xy + l.xy * r.yy;
1595         M.yx = l.yx * r.xx + l.yy * r.yx;
1596         M.yy = l.yx * r.xy + l.yy * r.yy;
1597         M.dx = l.xx * r.dx + l.xy * r.dy + l.dx;
1598         M.dy = l.yx * r.dx + l.yy * r.dy + l.dy;
1599       }
1600       return M; // dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D
1601     }
1602     m.invert = function(matrix) {
1603       var M = m.normalize(matrix),
1604         D = M.xx * M.yy - M.xy * M.yx,
1605         M = new m.Matrix2D({
1606           xx: M.yy/D, xy: -M.xy/D,
1607           yx: -M.yx/D, yy: M.xx/D,
1608           dx: (M.xy * M.dy - M.yy * M.dx) / D,
1609           dy: (M.yx * M.dx - M.xx * M.dy) / D
1610         });
1611       return M; // dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D
1612     }
1613     // the default (identity) matrix, which is used to fill in missing values
1614     Object.extend(m.Matrix2D, {xx: 1, xy: 0, yx: 0, yy: 1, dx: 0, dy: 0});
1615 
1616     var eq = function(/* Number */ a, /* Number */ b){
1617       // summary: compare two FP numbers for equality
1618       return Math.abs(a - b) <= 1e-6 * (Math.abs(a) + Math.abs(b)); // Boolean
1619     };
1620 
1621     var calcFromValues = function(/* Number */ s1, /* Number */ s2){
1622       // summary: uses two close FP values to approximate the result
1623       if(!isFinite(s1)){
1624         return s2;  // Number
1625       }else if(!isFinite(s2)){
1626         return s1;  // Number
1627       }
1628       return (s1 + s2) / 2; // Number
1629     };
1630 
1631     var transpose = function(/* dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D */ matrix){
1632       // matrix: dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D: a 2D matrix-like object
1633       var M = new m.Matrix2D(matrix);
1634       return Object.extend(M, {dx: 0, dy: 0, xy: M.yx, yx: M.xy}); // dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D
1635     };
1636 
1637     var scaleSign = function(/* dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D */ matrix){
1638       return (matrix.xx * matrix.yy < 0 || matrix.xy * matrix.yx > 0) ? -1 : 1; // Number
1639     };
1640 
1641     var eigenvalueDecomposition = function(/* dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D */ matrix){
1642       // matrix: dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D: a 2D matrix-like object
1643       var M = m.normalize(matrix),
1644         b = -M.xx - M.yy,
1645         c = M.xx * M.yy - M.xy * M.yx,
1646         d = Math.sqrt(b * b - 4 * c),
1647         l1 = -(b + (b < 0 ? -d : d)) / 2,
1648         l2 = c / l1,
1649         vx1 = M.xy / (l1 - M.xx), vy1 = 1,
1650         vx2 = M.xy / (l2 - M.xx), vy2 = 1;
1651       if(eq(l1, l2)){
1652         vx1 = 1, vy1 = 0, vx2 = 0, vy2 = 1;
1653       }
1654       if(!isFinite(vx1)){
1655         vx1 = 1, vy1 = (l1 - M.xx) / M.xy;
1656         if(!isFinite(vy1)){
1657           vx1 = (l1 - M.yy) / M.yx, vy1 = 1;
1658           if(!isFinite(vx1)){
1659             vx1 = 1, vy1 = M.yx / (l1 - M.yy);
1660           }
1661         }
1662       }
1663       if(!isFinite(vx2)){
1664         vx2 = 1, vy2 = (l2 - M.xx) / M.xy;
1665         if(!isFinite(vy2)){
1666           vx2 = (l2 - M.yy) / M.yx, vy2 = 1;
1667           if(!isFinite(vx2)){
1668             vx2 = 1, vy2 = M.yx / (l2 - M.yy);
1669           }
1670         }
1671       }
1672       var d1 = Math.sqrt(vx1 * vx1 + vy1 * vy1),
1673         d2 = Math.sqrt(vx2 * vx2 + vy2 * vy2);
1674       if(isNaN(vx1 /= d1)){ vx1 = 0; }
1675       if(isNaN(vy1 /= d1)){ vy1 = 0; }
1676       if(isNaN(vx2 /= d2)){ vx2 = 0; }
1677       if(isNaN(vy2 /= d2)){ vy2 = 0; }
1678       return {  // Object
1679         value1: l1,
1680         value2: l2,
1681         vector1: {x: vx1, y: vy1},
1682         vector2: {x: vx2, y: vy2}
1683       };
1684     };
1685 
1686     var decomposeSR = function(/* dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D */ M, /* Object */ result){
1687       // summary: decomposes a matrix into [scale, rotate]; no checks are
1688         // done.
1689       var sign = scaleSign(M),
1690         a = result.angle1 = (Math.atan2(M.yx, M.yy) + Math.atan2(-sign * M.xy, sign * M.xx)) / 2,
1691         cos = Math.cos(a), sin = Math.sin(a);
1692       result.sx = calcFromValues(M.xx / cos, -M.xy / sin);
1693       result.sy = calcFromValues(M.yy / cos, M.yx / sin);
1694       return result;  // Object
1695     };
1696 
1697     var decomposeRS = function(/* dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D */ M, /* Object */ result){
1698       // summary: decomposes a matrix into [rotate, scale]; no checks are done
1699       var sign = scaleSign(M),
1700         a = result.angle2 = (Math.atan2(sign * M.yx, sign * M.xx) + Math.atan2(-M.xy, M.yy)) / 2,
1701         cos = Math.cos(a), sin = Math.sin(a);
1702       result.sx = calcFromValues(M.xx / cos, M.yx / sin);
1703       result.sy = calcFromValues(M.yy / cos, -M.xy / sin);
1704       return result;  // Object
1705     };
1706 
1707     return function(matrix){
1708       // summary: decompose a 2D matrix into translation, scaling, and
1709         // rotation components
1710       // description: this function decompose a matrix into four logical
1711         // components:
1712       // translation, rotation, scaling, and one more rotation using SVD.
1713       // The components should be applied in following order:
1714       // | [translate, rotate(angle2), scale, rotate(angle1)]
1715       // matrix: dojox.gfx.matrix.Matrix2D: a 2D matrix-like object
1716       var M = m.normalize(matrix),
1717         result = {dx: M.dx, dy: M.dy, sx: 1, sy: 1, angle1: 0, angle2: 0};
1718       // detect case: [scale]
1719       if(eq(M.xy, 0) && eq(M.yx, 0)){
1720         return Object.extend(result, {sx: M.xx, sy: M.yy});  // Object
1721       }
1722       // detect case: [scale, rotate]
1723       if(eq(M.xx * M.yx, -M.xy * M.yy)){
1724         return decomposeSR(M, result);  // Object
1725       }
1726       // detect case: [rotate, scale]
1727       if(eq(M.xx * M.xy, -M.yx * M.yy)){
1728         return decomposeRS(M, result);  // Object
1729       }
1730       // do SVD
1731       var MT = transpose(M),
1732         u  = eigenvalueDecomposition([M, MT]),
1733         v  = eigenvalueDecomposition([MT, M]),
1734         U  = new m.Matrix2D({xx: u.vector1.x, xy: u.vector2.x, yx: u.vector1.y, yy: u.vector2.y}),
1735         VT = new m.Matrix2D({xx: v.vector1.x, xy: v.vector1.y, yx: v.vector2.x, yy: v.vector2.y}),
1736         S = new m.Matrix2D([m.invert(U), M, m.invert(VT)]);
1737       decomposeSR(VT, result);
1738       S.xx *= result.sx;
1739       S.yy *= result.sy;
1740       decomposeRS(U, result);
1741       S.xx *= result.sx;
1742       S.yy *= result.sy;
1743       return Object.extend(result, {sx: S.xx, sy: S.yy});  // Object
1744     };
1745   })(),
1746

1748   /**
1749      * Sets the canvas context ctx's transformation matrix to m, with ctm being
1750      * the current transformation matrix.
1751      */
1752   setTransform : function(ctx, m, ctm) {
1753     if (ctx.setTransform)
1754       //return ctx.setTransform.apply(ctx, m)
1755       return ctx.setTransform(m[0],m[1],m[2],m[3],m[4],m[5]);
1756     this.transform(ctx, this.tInvertMatrix(ctm))
1757     this.transform(ctx, m)
1758   },

1774   /**
1775      * Rotates a transformation matrix by angle.
1776      */
1777   tRotate : function(m1, angle) {
1778     // return this.tMatrixMultiply(matrix, this.tRotationMatrix(angle))
1779     var c = Math.cos(angle)
1780     var s = Math.sin(angle)
1781     var m11 = m1[0]*c + m1[2]*s
1782     var m12 = m1[1]*c + m1[3]*s
1783     var m21 = m1[0]*-s + m1[2]*c
1784     var m22 = m1[1]*-s + m1[3]*c
1785     m1[0] = m11
1786     m1[1] = m12
1787     m1[2] = m21
1788     m1[3] = m22
1789     return m1
1790   },
1791 
1792   /**
1793      * Translates a transformation matrix by x and y.
1794      */
1795   tTranslate : function(m1, x, y) {
1796     // return this.tMatrixMultiply(matrix, this.tTranslationMatrix(x,y))
1797     m1[4] += m1[0]*x + m1[2]*y
1798     m1[5] += m1[1]*x + m1[3]*y
1799     return m1
1800   },

1803      * Scales a transformation matrix by sx and sy.
1804      */
1805   tScale : function(m1, sx, sy) {
1806     // return this.tMatrixMultiply(matrix, this.tScalingMatrix(sx,sy))
1807     m1[0] *= sx
1808     m1[1] *= sx
1809     m1[2] *= sy
1810     m1[3] *= sy
1811     return m1
1812   },

1865   /**
1866      * Returns the name of the text backend to use.
1867      * 
1868      * Possible values are: 'MozText' for Firefox 'DrawString' for Rhino 'NONE'
1869      * no text drawing
1870      * 
1871      * @return The text backend name
1872      * @type String
1873      */

1876       this.textBackend = this.detectTextBackend()
1877     return this.textBackend

1880   /**
1881      * Detects the name of the text backend to use.
1882      * 
1883      * Possible values are: 'MozText' for Firefox 'DrawString' for Rhino 'NONE'
1884      * no text drawing
1885      * 
1886      * @return The text backend name
1887      * @type String
1888      */
1889   detectTextBackend : function() {
1890     var ctx = this.getTestContext()
1891     if (ctx.fillText) {
1892       return 'HTML5'
1893     } else if (ctx.mozDrawText) {
1894       return 'MozText'
1895     } else if (ctx.drawString) {
1896       return 'DrawString'
1897     }
1898     return 'NONE'
1899   },

1901   getSupportsPutImageData : function() {
1902     if (this.supportsPutImageData == null) {
1903       var ctx = this.getTestContext()
1904       var support = ctx.putImageData
1905       if (support) {
1906         try {
1907           var idata = ctx.getImageData(0,0,1,1)
1908           idata[0] = 255
1909           idata[1] = 0
1910           idata[2] = 255
1911           idata[3] = 255
1912           ctx.putImageData({width: 1, height: 1, data: idata}, 0, 0)
1913           var idata = ctx.getImageData(0,0,1,1)
1914           support = [255, 0, 255, 255].equals(idata.data)
1915         } catch(e) {
1916           support = false
1917         }
1918       }
1919       this.supportsPutImageData = support
1920     }
1921     return support
1922   },

1924   /**
1925      * Returns true if the browser can be coaxed to work with
1926      * {@link CanvasSupport.isPointInPath}.
1927      * 
1928      * @return Whether the browser supports isPointInPath or not
1929      * @type boolean
1930      */
1931   getSupportsIsPointInPath : function() {
1932     if (this.supportsIsPointInPath == null)
1933       this.supportsIsPointInPath = !!this.getTestContext().isPointInPath
1934     return this.supportsIsPointInPath
1935   },

1937   /**
1938      * Returns the coordinate system in which the isPointInPath of the browser
1939      * operates. Possible coordinate systems are CanvasSupport.DEVICE_SPACE and
1940      * CanvasSupport.USER_SPACE.
1941      * 
1942      * @return The coordinate system for the browser's isPointInPath
1943      */
1944   getIsPointInPathMode : function() {
1945     if (this.isPointInPathMode == null)
1946       this.isPointInPathMode = this.detectIsPointInPathMode()
1947     return this.isPointInPathMode
1948   },
1949 
1950   /**
1951      * Detects the coordinate system in which the isPointInPath of the browser
1952      * operates. Possible coordinate systems are CanvasSupport.DEVICE_SPACE and
1953      * CanvasSupport.USER_SPACE.
1954      * 
1955      * @return The coordinate system for the browser's isPointInPath
1956      * @private
1957      */
1958   detectIsPointInPathMode : function() {
1959     var ctx = this.getTestContext()
1960     var rv
1961     if (!ctx.isPointInPath)
1962       return this.USER_SPACE
1963     ctx.save()
1964     ctx.translate(1,0)
1965     ctx.beginPath()
1966     ctx.rect(0,0,1,1)
1967     if (ctx.isPointInPath(0.3,0.3)) {
1968       rv = this.USER_SPACE
1969     } else {
1970       rv = this.DEVICE_SPACE
1971     }
1972     ctx.restore()
1973     return rv
1974   },

1976   /**
1977      * Returns true if the device-space point (x,y) is inside the fill of ctx's
1978      * current path.
1979      * 
1980      * @function
1981      * @param ctx
1982      *            Canvas 2D context to query
1983      * @param x
1984      *            The distance in pixels from the left side of the canvas
1985      *            element
1986      * @param y
1987      *            The distance in pixels from the top side of the canvas element
1988      * @param matrix
1989      *            The current transformation matrix. Needed if the browser has
1990      *            no isPointInPath or the browser's isPointInPath works in
1991      *            user-space coordinates and the browser doesn't support
1992      *            setTransform.
1993      * @param callbackObj
1994      *            If the browser doesn't support isPointInPath,
1995      *            callbackObj.isPointInPath will be called with the
1996      *            x,y-coordinates transformed to user-space.
1997      * @param
1998      * @return {boolean }Whether (x,y) is inside ctx's current path or not
1999      * 
2000      */
2001   isPointInPath : function(ctx, x, y, matrix, callbackObj) {
2002     var rv
2003     if (!ctx.isPointInPath) {
2004       if (callbackObj && callbackObj.isPointInPath) {
2005         var xy = this.tMatrixMultiplyPoint(this.tInvertMatrix(matrix), x, y)
2006         return callbackObj.isPointInPath(xy[0], xy[1])
2007       } else {
2008         return false
2009       }
2010     } else {
2011       if (this.getIsPointInPathMode() == this.USER_SPACE) {
2012         if (!ctx.setTransform) {
2013           var xy = this.tMatrixMultiplyPoint(this.tInvertMatrix(matrix), x, y)
2014           rv = ctx.isPointInPath(xy[0], xy[1])
2015         } else {
2016           ctx.save()
2017           ctx.setTransform(1,0,0,1,0,0)
2018           rv = ctx.isPointInPath(x,y)
2019           ctx.restore()
2020         }
2021       } else {
2022         rv = ctx.isPointInPath(x,y)
2023       }
2024       return rv
2025     }
2026   }
2027 }

2127 RecordingContext.play = function(ctx, commands) {
2128   var dictionary = []
2129   for (var i=0; i<commands.length; i++) {
2130     var cmd = commands[i]
2131     if (cmd.length == 2) {
2132       var args = cmd[1]
2133       if (args[0] && args[0].isMockObject) {
2134         ctx[cmd[0]](dictionary[args[0].id])
2135       } else {
2136         ctx[cmd[0]].apply(ctx, cmd[1])
2137       }
2138     } else if (cmd.length == 3) {
2139       var obj = dictionary[cmd[0]]
2140       obj[cmd[1]].apply(obj, cmd[2])
2141     } else if (cmd.length == 4) {
2142       dictionary[cmd[0]] = ctx[cmd[2]].apply(ctx, cmd[3])
2143     } else {
2144       throw "Malformed command: "+cmd.toString()
2145     }
2146   }

2413                                   rotation[1], rotation[2] )
2414         CanvasSupport.tRotate( this.currentMatrix, rotation[0] )

2443   __scaleMatrix : function(scale) {
2444     if (scale.length == 2) {
2445       if (scale[0] == 1 && scale[1] == 1) return
2446       CanvasSupport.tScale(this.currentMatrix,
2447                            scale[0], scale[1])
2448     } else if (scale.length == 3) {
2449       if (scale[0] == 1 || (scale[0].length && (scale[0][0] == 1 && scale[0][1] == 1)))
2450         return
2451       CanvasSupport.tTranslate(this.currentMatrix,
2452                                scale[1], scale[2])

2454         CanvasSupport.tScale(this.currentMatrix,
2455                               scale[0][0], scale[0][1])
2456       } else {
2457         CanvasSupport.tScale( this.currentMatrix, scale[0], scale[0] )
2458       }
2459       CanvasSupport.tTranslate(this.currentMatrix,
2460                                -scale[1], -scale[2])
2461     } else if (scale != 1) {
2462       CanvasSupport.tScale( this.currentMatrix, scale, scale )
2463     }

2466   __matrixMatrix : function(matrix) {
2467     //CanvasSupport.tMatrixMultiply(this.currentMatrix, matrix)
2468     var m1 = this.currentMatrix;
2469     var m2 = matrix;
2470     
2471     var m11 = m1[0]*m2[0] + m1[2]*m2[1]
2472     var m12 = m1[1]*m2[0] + m1[3]*m2[1]
2473 
2474     var m21 = m1[0]*m2[2] + m1[2]*m2[3]
2475     var m22 = m1[1]*m2[2] + m1[3]*m2[3]
2476 
2477     var dx = m1[0]*m2[4] + m1[2]*m2[5] + m1[4]
2478     var dy = m1[1]*m2[4] + m1[3]*m2[5] + m1[5]
2479 
2480     m1[0] = m11
2481     m1[1] = m12
2482     m1[2] = m21
2483     m1[3] = m22
2484     m1[4] = dx
2485     m1[5] = dy
2486   },

2493     else
2494       CanvasSupport.setTransform(ctx, matrix, this.previousMatrix);
2495   },

2500     else

2506       if (rotation[1] || rotation[2]) {
2507         if (rotation[0] % (Math.PI*2) == 0) return
2508         ctx.translate( rotation[1], rotation[2] )
2509         ctx.rotate( rotation[0] )
2510         ctx.translate( -rotation[1], -rotation[2] )
2511       } else {
2512         ctx.rotate( rotation[0] )
2513       }
2514     } else {
2515       ctx.rotate( rotation )
2516     }
2517   },
2518

2526   __skewY : function(ctx, skewY) {

2529     else
2530       CanvasSupport.skewY(ctx, skewY)
2531   },
2532 
2533   __scale : function(ctx, scale) {
2534     if (scale.length == 2) {
2535       ctx.scale(scale[0], scale[1])
2536     } else if (scale.length == 3) {
2537       ctx.translate( scale[1], scale[2] )
2538       if (scale[0].length) {
2539         ctx.scale(scale[0][0], scale[0][1])
2540       } else {
2541         ctx.scale(scale[0], scale[0])
2542       }

2544     } else {
2545       ctx.scale(scale, scale)
2546     }

2556 /**
2557  * Timeline is an animator that tweens between its frames.
2558  * 
2559  * When object.time = k.time: object.state = k.state When object.time >
2560  * k[i-1].time and object.time < k[i].time: object.state = k[i].tween(position,
2561  * k[i-1].state, k[i].state) where position = elapsed / duration, elapsed =
2562  * object.time - k[i-1].time, duration = k[i].time - k[i-1].time
2563  */
2564 Timeline = Klass({
2565   startTime : null,
2566   repeat : false,
2567   lastAction : 0,
2568 
2569   /** @override */ initialize : function(repeat, pingpong) {
2570     this.repeat = repeat
2571     this.keyframes = []
2572   },
2573 
2574   addKeyframe : function(time, target, tween) {
2575     if (arguments.length == 1) this.keyframes.push(time)
2576     else  this.keyframes.push({
2577             time : time,
2578             target : target,
2579             tween : tween
2580           })
2581   },
2582 
2583   appendKeyframe : function(timeDelta, target, tween) {
2584     this.lastAction += timeDelta
2585     return this.addKeyframe(this.lastAction, target, tween)
2586   },
2587 
2588   evaluate : function(object, ot, dt) {
2589     if (this.startTime == null) this.startTime = ot
2590     var t = ot - this.startTime
2591     if (this.keyframes.length > 0) {
2592       // find current keyframe
2593       var currentIndex, previousFrame, currentFrame
2594       for (var i=0; i<this.keyframes.length; i++) {
2595         if (this.keyframes[i].time > t) {
2596           currentIndex = i
2597           break
2598         }
2599       }
2600       if (currentIndex != null) {
2601         previousFrame = this.keyframes[currentIndex-1]
2602         currentFrame = this.keyframes[currentIndex]
2603       }
2604       if (!currentFrame) {
2605         if (!this.keyframes.atEnd) {
2606           this.keyframes.atEnd = true
2607           previousFrame = this.keyframes[this.keyframes.length - 1]
2608           Object.extend(object, Object.clone(previousFrame.target))
2609           if (this.repeat) this.startTime = ot
2610           object.changed = true
2611         }
2612       } else if (previousFrame) {
2613         this.keyframes.atEnd = false
2614         // animate towards current keyframe
2615         var elapsed = t - previousFrame.time
2616         var duration = currentFrame.time - previousFrame.time
2617         var pos = elapsed / duration
2618         for (var k in currentFrame.target) {
2619           if (previousFrame.target[k] != null) {
2620             object.tweenVariable(k,
2621               previousFrame.target[k], currentFrame.target[k],
2622               pos, currentFrame.tween)
2623           }
2624         }
2625       }
2626     }
2627   }
2628 
2629 })

2635  * @interface
2636  */
2637 function Animatable() {
2638     Animatable.prototype.initialize.apply(this, arguments);  
2639 }
2640 Animatable.prototype = {
2641   /**
2642    * These are the available functions for the tween parameter of animate. They are
2643    * useable as strings or function references.
2644    * 
2645    * @namespace
2646    */
2647   tweenFunctions : {
2648   	/**
2649   	 * return v
2650   	 */
2651     linear : function(v) { return v },
2652 
2653     /** 
2654      * return Math.floor(v) 
2655      * @static */
2656     set : function(v) { return Math.floor(v) },
2657     /** 
2658      * return Math.floor(v) 
2659      * @static */
2660     discrete : function(v) { return Math.floor(v) },
2661 
2662     /**
2663      * return 0.5-0.5*Math.cos(v*Math.PI) 
2664      * @static */
2665     sine : function(v) { return 0.5-0.5*Math.cos(v*Math.PI) },
2666 
2667     /** 
2668      * (0.5-0.5*Math.cos(v*3.59261946538606)) * 1.05263157894737; 
2669      * @static */
2670     sproing : function(v) {
2671       return (0.5-0.5*Math.cos(v*3.59261946538606)) * 1.05263157894737;
2672       // pi + pi-acos(0.9)
2673     },
2674 
2675     /** @static */
2676     square : function(v) {
2677       return v*v
2678     },
2679 
2680     /** @static */
2681     cube : function(v) {
2682       return v*v*v
2683     },
2684 
2685     /** @static */
2686     sqrt : function(v) {
2687       return Math.sqrt(v)
2688     },
2689 
2690     /** 
2691      * return Math.pow(v, -0.333333333333)
2692      * @static */
2693     curt : function(v) {
2694       return Math.pow(v, -0.333333333333)
2695     }
2696   },

2698   initialize : function() {
2699     this.lastAction = 0
2700     this.timeline = []
2701     this.keyframes = []
2702     this.pendingKeyframes = []
2703     this.pendingTimelineEvents = []
2704     this.timelines = []
2705     this.animators = []
2706   },
2707 
2708   animFrameListener: function(t,dt) {
2709   	this.updateTimelines(t,dt);
2710     this.updateKeyframes(t,dt);
2711     this.updateTimeline(t,dt);
2712     this.updateAnimators(t,dt);
2713   },
2714 
2715   addAnimListeners: function() {
2716   	if(this.listenersAdded) return;
2717   	
2718   	this.listenersAdded = true;
2719     this.addFrameListener(this.animFrameListener)
2720   },
2721   
2722   removeAnimListeners: function() {
2723     this.listenersAdded = false;
2724     this.removeFrameListener(this.animFrameListener)
2725   },
2726 
2727   updateTimelines : function(t, dt) {
2728     for (var i=0; i<this.timelines.length; i++)
2729       this.timelines[i].evaluate(this, t, dt)
2730   },
2731 
2732   addTimeline : function(tl) {
2733     this.timelines.push(tl)
2734   },
2735 
2736   removeTimeline : function(tl) {
2737     //this.timelines.deleteFirst(tl)
2738     Array.deleteFirst.call(this.timelines, tl);
2739   },
2740 
2741   /**
2742      * Tweens between keyframes (a keyframe is an object with the new values of
2743      * the members of this, e.g. { time: 0, target: { x: 10, y: 20 }, tween:
2744      * 'square'})
2745      * 
2746      * Keyframes are very much like multi-variable animators, the main
2747      * difference is that with keyframes the start value and the duration are
2748      * implicit.
2749      * 
2750      * While an animation from value A to B would take two keyframes instead of
2751      * a single animator, chaining and reordering keyframes is very easy.
2752      */
2753   updateKeyframes : function(t,dt) {
2754     this.addPendingKeyframes(t)
2755     if (this.keyframes.length > 0) {
2756       // find current keyframe
2757       var currentIndex, previousFrame, currentFrame
2758       for (var i=0; i<this.keyframes.length; i++) {
2759         if (this.keyframes[i].time > t) {
2760           currentIndex = i
2761           break
2762         }
2763       }
2764       if (currentIndex != null) {
2765         previousFrame = this.keyframes[currentIndex-1]
2766         currentFrame = this.keyframes[currentIndex]
2767       }
2768       if (!currentFrame) {
2769         if (!this.keyframes.atEnd) {
2770           this.keyframes.atEnd = true
2771           previousFrame = this.keyframes[this.keyframes.length - 1]
2772           Object.extend(this, Object.clone(previousFrame.target))
2773           this.changed = true
2774         }
2775       } else if (previousFrame) {
2776         this.keyframes.atEnd = false
2777         // animate towards current keyframe
2778         var elapsed = t - previousFrame.time
2779         var duration = currentFrame.time - previousFrame.time
2780         var pos = elapsed / duration
2781         for (var k in currentFrame.target) {
2782           if (previousFrame.target[k] != null) {
2783             this.tweenVariable(k,
2784               previousFrame.target[k], currentFrame.target[k],
2785               pos, currentFrame.tween)
2786           }
2787         }
2788       }
2789     }
2790   },
2791 
2792   addPendingKeyframes : function(t) {
2793     if (this.pendingKeyframes.length > 0) {
2794       while (this.pendingKeyframes.length > 0) {
2795         var kf = this.pendingKeyframes.shift()
2796         if (kf.time == null)
2797           kf.time = kf.relativeTime + t
2798         this.keyframes.push(kf)
2799       }
2800       //this.keyframes.stableSort(function(a,b) { return a.time - b.time })
2801       Array.stableSort.call(this.keyframes, function(a,b) { return a.time - b.time })
2802     }
2803   },
2804 
2805   /**
2806      * Run and remove timelineEvents that have startTime <= t. TimelineEvents
2807      * are run in the ascending order of their startTimes.
2808      */
2809   updateTimeline : function(t, dt) {
2810     this.addPendingTimelineEvents(t)
2811     while (this.timeline[0] && this.timeline[0].startTime <= t) {
2812       var keyframe = this.timeline.shift()
2813       var rv = true
2814       if (typeof(keyframe.action) == 'function')
2815         rv = keyframe.action.call(this, t, dt, keyframe)
2816       else
2817         this.animators.push(keyframe.action)
2818       if (keyframe.repeatEvery != null && rv != false) {
2819         if (keyframe.repeatTimes != null) {
2820           if (keyframe.repeatTimes <= 0) continue
2821           keyframe.repeatTimes--
2822         }
2823         keyframe.startTime += keyframe.repeatEvery
2824         this.addTimelineEvent(keyframe)
2825       }
2826       this.changed = true
2827     }
2828   },
2829 
2830   addPendingTimelineEvents : function(t) {
2831     if (this.pendingTimelineEvents.length > 0) {
2832       while (this.pendingTimelineEvents.length > 0) {
2833         var kf = this.pendingTimelineEvents.shift()
2834         if (!kf.startTime)
2835           kf.startTime = kf.relativeStartTime + t
2836         this.timeline.push(kf)
2837       }
2838       //this.timeline.stableSort(function(a,b) { return a.startTime - b.startTime })
2839       Array.stableSort.call(this.timeline, function(a,b) { return a.startTime - b.startTime });
2840     }
2841   },
2842 
2843   addTimelineEvent : function(kf) {
2844     this.pendingTimelineEvents.push(kf)
2845   },
2846 
2847   /**
2848      * Run each animator, delete ones that have their durations exceeded.
2849      */
2850   updateAnimators : function(t, dt) {
2851     for (var i=0; i<this.animators.length; i++) {
2852       var ani = this.animators[i]
2853       if (!ani.startTime) ani.startTime = t
2854       var elapsed = t - ani.startTime
2855       var pos = elapsed / ani.duration
2856       var shouldRemove = false
2857       var fire_cb = false
2858       if (pos >= 1) {
2859         if (!ani.repeat) {
2860           pos = 1
2861           shouldRemove = true
2862         } else {
2863           if (ani.repeat !== true) ani.repeat = Math.max(0, ani.repeat - 1)
2864           if (ani.accumulate) {
2865             ani.startValue = Object.clone(ani.endValue)
2866             ani.endValue = Object.sum(ani.difference, ani.endValue)
2867           }
2868           if (ani.repeat == 0) {
2869             shouldRemove = true
2870             pos = 1
2871           } else {
2872             ani.startTime = t
2873             pos = pos % 1
2874           }
2875         }
2876         
2877         fire_cb = true
2878       } else if (ani.repeat && ani.repeat !== true && ani.repeat <= pos) {
2879         shouldRemove = true
2880         pos = ani.repeat
2881       }
2882       this.tweenVariable(ani.variable, ani.startValue, ani.endValue, pos, ani.tween)
2883       if (shouldRemove) {
2884         this.animators.splice(i, 1)
2885         i--
2886       }
2887       if(fire_cb && ani.callback)
2888         ani.callback()
2889         
2890       if(this.animators.length < 1)
2891         this.removeAnimListeners();
2892     }
2893   },
2894 
2895   tweenVariable : function(variable, start, end, pos, tweenFunction) {
2896     if (typeof(tweenFunction) != 'function') {
2897       tweenFunction = this.tweenFunctions[tweenFunction] || this.tweenFunctions.linear
2898     }
2899     var tweened = tweenFunction(pos)
2900     if (typeof(variable) != 'function') {
2901       if (start instanceof Array) {
2902         for (var j=0; j<start.length; j++) {
2903           this[variable][j] = start[j] + tweened*(end[j]-start[j])
2904         }
2905       } else {
2906         this[variable] = start + tweened*(end-start)
2907       }
2908     } else {
2909       variable.call(this, tweened, start, end)
2910     }
2911     this.changed = true
2912   },
2913 
2914   /**
2915    * Animate a property from a start value to an end value.
2916    * 
2917    * @see Animatable#tweenFunctions
2918    * 
2919    * @param {String} variable Variable name or receiving function function(percent, start, end)
2920    * @param {number} start Starting value
2921    * @param {number} end Ending value
2922    * @param {number} duration Tween duration
2923    * @param {String|Function} tween Tween function
2924    * @param {Object} config Optional configs
2925    * @param {boolean} config.additive Whether start and end are additive, or static
2926    * @param {boolean|Number} config.repeat true for infinite times or {number} of times
2927    * @param {Function} config.callback Callback for when completed
2928    * @param {boolean} config.accumulate Whether differences are accumulated or tweened 
2929    */
2930   animate : function(variable, start, end, duration, tween, config) {
2931     var start = Object.clone(start)
2932     var end = Object.clone(end)
2933     var diff;
2934     if (!config) config = {}
2935     if (config.additive) {
2936       diff = Object.sub(end, start)
2937       start = Object.sum(start, this[variable])
2938       end = Object.sum(end, this[variable])
2939     }
2940     if (typeof(variable) != 'function')
2941       this[variable] = Object.clone(start)
2942    
2943     var ani = {
2944       id : Animatable.uid++,
2945       variable : variable,
2946       startValue : start,
2947       endValue : end,
2948       difference : diff,
2949       duration : duration,
2950       tween : tween,
2951       repeat : config.repeat,
2952       additive : config.additive,
2953       accumulate : config.accumulate,
2954       pingpong : config.pingpong,
2955       callback : config.callback
2956     }
2957     this.animators.push(ani)
2958     this.addAnimListeners();
2959     return ani
2960   },
2961 
2962   removeAnimator : function(animator) {
2963     //this.animators.deleteFirst(animator)
2964     Array.deleteFirst.call(this.animators, animator);
2965   },
2966 
2967   animateTo : function(variableName, end, duration, tween, config) {
2968     return this.animate(variableName, this[variableName], end, duration, tween, config)
2969   },
2970 
2971   animateFrom : function(variableName, start, duration, tween, config) {
2972     return this.animate(variableName, start, this[variableName], duration, tween, config)
2973   },
2974 
2975   animateFactor : function(variableName, start, endFactor, duration, tween, config) {
2976     var end
2977     if (start instanceof Array) {
2978       end = []
2979       for (var i=0; i<start.length; i++) {
2980         end[i] = start[i] * endFactor
2981       }
2982     } else {
2983       end = start * endFactor
2984     }
2985     return this.animate(variableName, start, end, duration, tween, config)
2986   },
2987 
2988   animateToFactor : function(variableName, endFactor, duration, tween, config) {
2989     var start = this[variableName]
2990     return this.animateFactor(variableName, start, endFactor, duration, tween, config)
2991   },
2992 
2993   addKeyframe : function(time, target, tween) {
2994     var kf = {
2995       relativeTime: time,
2996       target: target,
2997       tween: tween
2998     }
2999     this.pendingKeyframes.push(kf)
3000     this.addAnimListeners();
3001   },
3002 
3003   addKeyframeAt : function(time, target, tween) {
3004     var kf = {
3005       time: time,
3006       target: target,
3007       tween: tween
3008     }
3009     this.pendingKeyframes.push(kf)
3010     this.addAnimListeners();
3011   },
3012 
3013   appendKeyframe : function(timeDelta, target, tween) {
3014     this.lastAction += timeDelta;
3015     this.addAnimListeners();
3016     return this.addKeyframe(this.lastAction, target, tween)
3017   },
3018 
3019   every : function(duration, action, noFirst) {
3020     var kf = {
3021       action : action,
3022       relativeStartTime : noFirst ? duration : 0,
3023       repeatEvery : duration
3024     }
3025     this.addTimelineEvent(kf)
3026     this.addAnimListeners();
3027     return kf
3028   },
3029 
3030   at : function(time, action) {
3031     var kf = {
3032       action : action,
3033       startTime : time
3034     }
3035     this.addTimelineEvent(kf)
3036     this.addAnimListeners();
3037     return kf
3038   },
3039 
3040   /**
3041    * Trigger an action after a duration in seconds.
3042    * 
3043    * @param duration Duration in ms
3044    * @param action Callback function
3045    */
3046   after : function(duration, action) {
3047     var kf = {
3048       action : action,
3049       relativeStartTime : duration
3050     }
3051     this.addTimelineEvent(kf)
3052     this.addAnimListeners();
3053     return kf
3054   },
3055 
3056   afterFrame : function(duration, callback) {
3057     var elapsed = 0
3058     var animator
3059     animator = function(t, dt){
3060       if (elapsed >= duration) {
3061         callback.call(this)
3062         this.removeFrameListener(animator)
3063       }
3064       elapsed++
3065     }
3066     this.addFrameListener(animator)
3067     return animator
3068   },
3069 
3070   everyFrame : function(duration, callback, noFirst) {
3071     var elapsed = noFirst ? 0 : duration
3072     var animator = function(t, dt){
3073       if (elapsed >= duration) {
3074         if (callback.call(this) == false)
3075           this.removeFrameListener(animator)
3076         elapsed = 0
3077       }
3078       elapsed++
3079     }
3080     this.addFrameListener(animator)
3081     return animator
3082   }
3083 }

3089 /**
3090  * CanvasNode is the base CAKE scenegraph node. All the other scenegraph nodes
3091  * derive from it. A plain CanvasNode does no drawing, but it can be used for
3092  * grouping other nodes and setting up the group's drawing state.
3093  * 
3094  * var scene = new CanvasNode({x: 10, y: 10})
3095  * 
3096  * The usual way to use CanvasNodes is to append them to a Canvas object:
3097  * 
3098  * var scene = new CanvasNode() scene.append(new Rectangle(40, 40, {fill:
3099  * true})) var elem = E.canvas(400, 400) var canvas = new Canvas(elem)
3100  * canvas.append(scene)
3101  * 
3102  * You can also use CanvasNodes to draw directly to a canvas element:
3103  * 
3104  * var scene = new CanvasNode() scene.append(new Circle(40, {x:200, y:200,
3105  * stroke: true})) var elem = E.canvas(400, 400)
3106  * scene.handleDraw(elem.getContext('2d'))
3107  * 
3108  * @constructor
3109  * @extends Transformable
3110  * @extends Animatable
3111  * @implements Animatable
3112  * 
3113  * @param {CanvasNode} config 
3114  * 
3115  * @property {boolean} changed Set to true to signal the scene graph to update.
3116  * @property {boolean} cacheAsBitmap Allows cake to cache the node contents as a bitmap.
3117  *      bmpCache will need to be manually set to null to destroy a cache.
3118  * @property {boolean} visible Whether to draw the node and its childNodes or not
3119  * @property {boolean} drawable Whether to draw the node (doesn't affect subtree)
3120  * @property {boolean} bmpCache Holds a reference to contents cache if any
3121  */
3122 function CanvasNode(config) {
3123      CanvasNode.prototype.initialize.call(this, config)
3124 }

3585   /**
3586      * Returns true if this node's subtree contains obj. (I.e. obj is this or
3587      * obj's parent chain includes this.)
3588      * 
3589      * @param obj
3590      *            Node to look for
3591      * @return True if obj is in this node's subtree, false if it isn't.
3592      */
3593   contains : function(obj) {
3594     while (obj) {
3595       if (obj == this) return true
3596       obj = obj.parentNode
3597     }
3598     return false

3601   /**
3602      * Set this.root to the given value and propagate the update to childNodes.
3603      * 
3604      * @param root
3605      *            The new root node
3606      * @private
3607      */
3608   setRoot : function(root, drawRoot, removeRoot) {
3609     //remove
3610     if(removeRoot && removeRoot.redrawOnlyWhatChanged) {
3611         //var b = this.getAxisAlignedBoundingBox();
3612         var b = this.previousBoundingBox;
3613         
3614         if(b && removeRoot.dirtyRegions) 
3615             removeRoot.dirtyRegions.push(b);
3616             
3617         b = this.getAxisAlignedBoundingBox();
3618         
3619         if(b && removeRoot.dirtyRegions) 
3620             removeRoot.dirtyRegions.push(b);
3621     }
3622     
3623     this.DOMelement = null;
3624     if(this.imageElement)
3625         this.imageElement = null;
3626     
3627     root = root || this;
3628     
3629     this.root = root;
3630     //int much faster than float...
3631     this.pmNum = parseInt(Math.random() * 100000);
3632     this.mNum = parseInt(Math.random() * 100000);
3633     this.drawRoot = drawRoot;
3634     this.relativeMatrix = null
3635     this.lastTransList = null;
3636     this.currentMatrix = [1,0,0,1,0,0];
3637     this.needZIndexUpdate = true;
3638     this.lastZIndex = null;
3639     this.parentMatrixUpdated = true;
3640     this.needsDOMUpdate = this.needMatrixUpdate = this.changed = this.isDirty = true;
3641     this.oldZIndex = null;
3642     this.dispatchEvent(new GenericEvent('rootChanged', {canvasTarget: this, 
3643         relatedTarget: root, removeRoot: removeRoot}));
3644 
3645     if(this instanceof ElementNode && removeRoot 
3646             && this.DOMelement && this.DOMelement.parentNode) {
3647     	this.DOMelement.parentNode.removeChild(this.DOMelement);
3648     }
3649       
3650     //CRIO  
3651     if(!removeRoot) this.transform(null, true)
3652     for (var i=0; i<this.childNodes.length; i++)
3653       this.childNodes[i].setRoot(this.root, this.drawRoot, removeRoot)
3654     //this.transform(null, true)
3655       
3656     //add
3657     if(root && this.drawRoot && this.drawRoot.redrawOnlyWhatChanged) {
3658         var b = this.getAxisAlignedBoundingBox();
3659         
3660         if(b && this.drawRoot && this.drawRoot.dirtyRegions) 
3661             this.drawRoot.dirtyRegions.push(b);
3662     }
3663   },

3688   addEventListener : function(type, listener, capture) {
3689     if (!this.eventListeners[type]) {
3690       var p = this.eventListeners[type] = {capture:[], bubble:[]};
3691       p['capture'] = p.capture;
3692       p['bubble'] = p.bubble;
3693     }
3694     this.eventListeners[type][capture ? 'capture' : 'bubble'].push(listener)
3695   },
