3697   /**
3698      * Synonym for addEventListener.
3699      */
3700   when : function(type, listener, capture) {
3701     this.addEventListener(type, listener, capture || false)
3702   },
3703 
3704   removeEventListener : function(type, listener, capture) {
3705     if (!this.eventListeners[type]) return
3706     //this.eventListeners[type][capture ? 'capture' : 'bubble'].deleteFirst(listener)
3707     Array.deleteFirst.call(this.eventListeners[type][capture ? 'capture' : 'bubble'], listener);
3708     if (this.eventListeners[type].capture.length == 0 &&
3709         this.eventListeners[type].bubble.length == 0)
3710       delete this.eventListeners[type]
3711   },
3712 
3713   dispatchEvent : function(event) {
3714     var type = event.type
3715 
3716     //if(event.type == 'mousedown') console.log([event, this.root.target]);
3717     
3718     if (!event.canvasTarget) {
3719       if (type.search(/^(key|text)/i) == 0) {
3720         event.canvasTarget = this.root.focused || this.root.target
3721       } else {
3722         event.canvasTarget = this.root.target
3723       }
3724       if (!event.canvasTarget)
3725         event.canvasTarget = this
3726     }
3727     
3728     var path = []
3729     var obj = event.canvasTarget
3730     
3731     if(this.root.pickByDepth) {
3732         path = this.root.pickStack || [];
3733         event.canvasPhase = 'capture'
3734 	    for (var i=path.length-1; i>=0; i--)
3735 	      if (!path[i].handleEvent(event)) return false
3736 	    event.canvasPhase = 'bubble'
3737 	    for (var i=0; i<path.length; i++)
3738 	      if (!path[i].handleEvent(event)) return false
3739 	      
3740 	    return true;
3741     }
3742     
3743     path = []
3744     while (obj && obj != this) {
3745       path.push(obj)
3746       obj = obj.parent
3747     }
3748     path.push(this)
3749     
3750     event.canvasPhase = 'capture'
3751     for (var i=path.length-1; i>=0; i--)
3752       if (!path[i].handleEvent(event)) return false
3753     event.canvasPhase = 'bubble'
3754     for (var i=0; i<path.length; i++)
3755       if (!path[i].handleEvent(event)) return false
3756     return true
3757   },
3758 
3759   broadcastEvent : function(event) {
3760     var type = event.type
3761     event.canvasPhase = 'capture'
3762     if (!this.handleEvent(event)) return false
3763     for (var i=0; i<this.childNodes.length; i++)
3764       if (!this.childNodes[i].broadcastEvent(event)) return false
3765     event.canvasPhase = 'bubble'
3766     if (!this.handleEvent(event)) return false
3767     return true
3768   },
3769 
3770   handleEvent : function(event) {
3771     var type = event.type
3772     var phase = event.canvasPhase
3773     if (this.cursor && phase == 'capture')
3774       event.cursor = this.cursor
3775     var els = this.eventListeners[type]
3776     
3777     els = els && els[phase]
3778     if (els) {
3779       for (var i=0; i<els.length; i++) {
3780         var rv = els[i].call(this, event)
3781         if (rv == false || event.stopped) {
3782           if (!event.stopped)
3783             event.stopPropagation()
3784           event.stopped = true
3785           return false
3786         }
3787       }
3788     }
3789     return true
3790   },

3792   preUpdate: function(time, timeDelta) {
3793   	var top = this;
3794   	var parent = top.parent;
3795   	var root = this.root;
3796   	var b2d = top.body !== null && root.enableBox2D;
3797             
3798     if(root.legacyCake) {
3799     	top.needMatrixUpdate = top.changed = true;
3800     }
3801             
3802     if(b2d === true) {
3803         var pos = top.body.GetCenterPosition();
3804                 
3805         top.x = pos.x;
3806         top.y = pos.y;
3807         top.changed = true;
3808         top.rotation = top.body.GetRotation();
3809         var mr = top.body.m_R; 
3810         top.fixedRelativeMatrix = [mr.col1.x, mr.col1.y, mr.col2.x, mr.col2.y, pos.x, pos.y];
3811     } 
3812     
3813     if(top.needMatrixUpdate)
3814         top.transform(null, true);
3815 
3816     if(top.lastZIndex !== top.zIndex && parent !== null) parent.needZIndexUpdate = true;
3817     top.lastZIndex = top.zIndex;
3818     
3819     if(top.frameListeners !== null) {
3820 	    // need to operate on a copy, otherwise bad stuff happens
3821 	    //var fl = top.frameListeners.slice(0)
3822 	    //for(var i=0; i<fl.length; i++) {
3823 	    for(var i in top.frameListeners) {
3824 	      //if (Array.includes.call(top.frameListeners, fl[i]))
3825 	        top.frameListeners[i].apply(top, arguments)
3826 	    }
3827     }
3828         
3829     var willBeDrawn = (!parent || parent.willBeDrawn) 
3830         && (top.display ? (top.display !== 'none' || top.DOMelement !== null) : top.visible);
3831         
3832     if(top.willBeDrawn != willBeDrawn) {
3833       top.isDirty = true;
3834       
3835       //if(root.redrawOnlyWhatChanged)
3836       //    top.handleRedrawRegion(null, true);
3837     }
3838       
3839     top.willBeDrawn = willBeDrawn;
3840   },
3841   
3842   postUpdate: function(time, timeDelta) {
3843   	var top = this;
3844   	var root = this.root;
3845     var parent = top.parent;
3846     
3847     if (top.changed) { 
3848       //root.numChanged++;
3849       //root.numChangedTrue++;
3850       if(top.onChanged) top.onChanged(top.changed);
3851       
3852       if(!AGGRESSIVE_NO_UPDATE)
3853         top.needsDOMUpdate = true;
3854       if(top.changed === true) {
3855         top.needMatrixUpdate = true;
3856         top.transform(null, true);
3857         top.needsDOMUpdate = true;
3858         top.isDirty = true;
3859         if(!root.isFake) top.onDirty();
3860         
3861         if(AGGRESSIVE_NO_UPDATE && 
3862             parent !== null && !parent.changed) parent.changed = top;   
3863         
3864         //top.transform(null, true);
3865       } else if(AGGRESSIVE_NO_UPDATE && parent !== null && !parent.changed)
3866         parent.changed = top.changed;   
3867         
3868       if(parent !== null) top.changed = false
3869     } 
3870     
3871     if(top.needZIndexUpdate === true) {
3872         top.__zSort(top.childNodes);
3873         top.needZIndexUpdate = false;
3874     }
3875     
3876     //top.transform(null, true)
3877   },
3878 
3879   /**
3880      * Handle scenegraph update. Called with current time before drawing each
3881      * frame.
3882      * 
3883      * This method should be touched only if you know what you're doing. If you
3884      * need your own update handler, either add a frame listener or overwrite
3885      * {@link CanvasNode.update}.
3886      * 
3887      * @private
3888      * @param time
3889      *            Current animation time
3890      * @param timeDelta
3891      *            Time since last frame in milliseconds
3892      */
3893   handleUpdate : function(time, timeDelta) {
3894     var root = this.root;
3895 
3896     var ptr = this;
3897     var stack = [this];
3898     var cstack = [this.childNodes];//__getChildrenCopy()];
3899     var idx = [0];
3900     while(stack.length !== 0) {
3901         var top = stack[stack.length - 1];
3902         var i = idx[stack.length - 1]++;
3903         var cref = cstack[stack.length - 1];
3904 
3905         if(i === 0) {
3906         	if(AGGRESSIVE_NO_UPDATE && !top.changed) {
3907 	        	stack.pop();
3908 	            idx.pop();
3909 	            cstack.pop();
3910 	            continue;
3911 	        }
3912 	        
3913         	top.preUpdate(time, timeDelta);
3914         }
3915 
3916         var ch = cref[i];
3917         if(ch) {
3918         	if(!top.cacheIgnoreChildren || !top.bmpCache || top.root.isFake) {
3919                 stack.push(ch);
3920                 idx.push(0);
3921                 cstack.push(ch.childNodes);//__getChildrenCopy());
3922         	}
3923             continue;
3924         }
3925 
3926         //if(cref[i + 1] !== undefined) continue; //still children
3927         
3928         top.postUpdate(time, timeDelta);
3929     	
3930         stack.pop();
3931         idx.pop();
3932         cstack.pop();
3933     }
3934         
3935     //this.transform(null, true)
3936   },
3937

4299   /**
4300      * Handles transforming and drawing the node and its childNodes on each
4301      * frame.
4302      * 
4303      * Pushes context state, applies state transforms and draws the node. Then
4304      * sorts the node's childNodes by zIndex, smallest first, and calls their
4305      * handleDraws in that order. Finally, pops the context state.
4306      * 
4307      * Called after handleUpdate and handlePick.
4308      * 
4309      * This method should be touched only if you know what you're doing.
4310      * Overwrite {@link CanvasNode#draw} when you need to draw things.
4311      * 
4312      * @private
4313      * @param ctx
4314      *            Canvas 2D context
4315      */
4316   realHandleDraw : function(ctx) {
4317     // CSS display & visibility
4318     if (this.display)
4319       this.visible = (this.display != 'none')
4320     if (this.visibility)
4321       this.drawable = (this.visibility != 'hidden')
4322     if (!this.visible) return
4323     //ctx.save()
4324     //var pff = ctx.fontFamily
4325     //var pfs = ctx.fontSize
4326     //var pfo = ctx.fillOn
4327     //var pso = ctx.strokeOn
4328     //if (this.fontFamily)
4329     //  ctx.fontFamily = this.fontFamily
4330     //if (this.fontSize)
4331     //  ctx.fontSize = this.fontSize
4332 
4333     //this.previousBoundingBox = this.getAxisAlignedBoundingBox();
4334 
4335     if (this.clipPath) {
4336       ctx.beginPath()
4337       if (this.clipPath.units == this.OBJECTBOUNDINGBOX) {
4338         var bb = this.getSubtreeBoundingBox(true)
4339         ctx.save()
4340         ctx.translate(bb[0], bb[1])
4341         ctx.scale(bb[2], bb[3])
4342         this.clipPath.createSubtreePath(ctx, true)
4343         ctx.restore()
4344         ctx.clip()
4345       } else {
4346         this.clipPath.createSubtreePath(ctx, true)
4347         ctx.clip()
4348       }
4349     }
4350     
4351     var not_in_region = false;
4352     if(this.root.dirtyBB && this.previousBoundingBox && 0) {
4353     	var sbb = this.previousBoundingBox;
4354     	var obb = this.root.dirtyBB;
4355     	
4356     	var x_clear = ((sbb[0] + sbb[2]) < obb[0]) || 
4357     	   ((obb[0] + obb[2]) < sbb[0]);
4358     	var y_clear = ((sbb[1] + sbb[3]) < obb[1]) || 
4359            ((obb[1] + obb[3]) < sbb[1]);
4360            
4361         not_in_region = x_clear && y_clear;
4362         
4363         //if(not_in_region)
4364         //    console.log('clear!');
4365     }
4366 
4367     var restore_after = false;
4368     if (((this.drawable && this.draw) || this.bmpCache !== null || this.parent == this) && not_in_region === false) {
4369       if(this.opacity !== null || this.font !== null || this.fill !== null || this.stroke ) {
4370         ctx.save();
4371         restore_after = true;
4372       }
4373       
4374       this.transform(ctx, false);
4375       
4376       //this.previousBoundingBox = this.getAxisAlignedBoundingBox();
4377

4379         var bb = this.bmpCache.bmpBoundingBox;//this.getSubtreeBoundingBox(true);
4380 		var point = CanvasSupport.tMatrixMultiplyPoint(this.currentMatrix, 0, 0);
4381 		
4382 		var dscale = 1;
4383 		
4384 		
4385 		if(this.bmpScale) {
4386             /*bb = this.bmpCache.relativeBmpBoundingBox;
4387             point = [0,0];
4388             bb = this.transformBoundingBoxBy(bb, this.parent.currentMatrix);*/
4389             
4390             dscale = 1;//this.bmpScale;
4391             
4392             dscale = this.currentMatrix[0] / this.bmpCache.bmpScale;
4393         }
4394 		
4395         // console.log("drawing bitmap " + (this.id || 'uk'));
4396         //ctx.save();
4397         ctx.setTransform(1,0,0,1,0,0);
4398         //console.log(cbb);
4399         var pbb = [point[0] + bb[0] * dscale, 
4400        		point[1] + bb[1] * dscale, (bb[2]) * dscale, (bb[3]) * dscale];
4401        	if(pbb[2] && pbb[3]) 
4402        	    ctx.drawImage(this.bmpCache, pbb[0], pbb[1], pbb[2], pbb[3]);
4403         //ctx.restore();      
4404       } else {

4406         // if(this.id != 'root')
4407         // console.log("drawing non bitmap " + (this.id || 'uk'));
4408       }
4409     } else
4410     	this.transform(null, true);
4411 
4412     if(!this.cacheAsBitmap || this.root.isFake) {
4413         var c = this.childNodes; //this.__getChildrenCopy()
4414         //this.__zSort(c)

4430   /**
4431      * Transforms the context state according to this node's attributes.
4432      * 
4433      * @param ctx {CanvasRenderingContext2D}
4434      *            Canvas 2D context
4435      * @param onlyTransform
4436      *            If set to true, only do matrix transforms.
4437      */
4438   transform : function(ctx, onlyTransform) {
4439     //Transformable.prototype.transform.call(this, ctx)
4440     this.__transform(ctx);
4441 
4442     if (onlyTransform) return
4443 
4444 	//this.root.curState = this.root.curState || {};
4445 
4446     // stroke / fill modifiers
4447     if (this.fill !== null) {
4448       if (!this.fill || this.fill === 'none') {
4449         ctx.fillOn = false;
4450       } else {
4451         ctx.fillOn = true;
4452         if (this.fill !== true) {
4453           var fillStyle = Colors.parseColorStyle(this.fill, ctx)
4454             ctx.setFillStyle( fillStyle )
4455         }
4456       }
4457     }
4458     
4459     if (this.stroke !== null) {
4460       if (!this.stroke || this.stroke === 'none') {
4461         ctx.strokeOn = false
4462       } else {
4463         ctx.strokeOn = true
4464         if (this.stroke !== true)
4465           ctx.setStrokeStyle( Colors.parseColorStyle(this.stroke, ctx) )
4466       }
4467     }
4468     if (this.strokeWidth !== null)
4469       ctx.setLineWidth( this.strokeWidth )
4470     if (this.lineCap !== null)
4471       ctx.setLineCap( this.lineCap )
4472     if (this.lineJoin !== null)
4473       ctx.setLineJoin( this.lineJoin )
4474     if (this.miterLimit !== null)
4475       ctx.setMiterLimit( this.miterLimit )
4476  
4477     // compositing modifiers
4478     if (this.absoluteOpacity !== null)
4479       ctx.setGlobalAlpha( this.absoluteOpacity )
4480     if (this.opacity !== null)
4481       ctx.setGlobalAlpha( ctx.globalAlpha * this.opacity )
4482     if (this.compositeOperation !== null)
4483       ctx.setGlobalCompositeOperation( this.compositeOperation )
4484 
4485     // shadow modifiers
4486     if (this.shadowColor !== null)
4487       ctx.setShadowColor( Colors.parseColorStyle(this.shadowColor, ctx) )
4488     if (this.shadowBlur !== null)
4489       ctx.setShadowBlur( this.shadowBlur )
4490     if (this.shadowOffsetX !== null)
4491       ctx.setShadowOffsetX( this.shadowOffsetX )
4492     if (this.shadowOffsetY !== null)
4493       ctx.setShadowOffsetY( this.shadowOffsetY )
4494 
4495     // text modifiers
4496     if (this.textAlign !== null)
4497       ctx.setTextAlign( this.textAlign )
4498     if (this.textBaseline !== null)
4499       ctx.setTextBaseline( this.textBaseline )
4500     if (this.font !== null)
4501       ctx.setFont( this.font )
4502     else if(this.fontFamily)
4503       ctx.setFont((this.fontSize || 12) + 'px ' + this.fontFamily);

4521      * Draws the node.

4532   createSubtreePath : function(ctx, skipTransform) {
4533     ctx.save()
4534     if (!skipTransform) this.transform(ctx, true)
4535     for (var i=0; i<this.childNodes.length; i++)
4536       this.childNodes[i].createSubtreePath(ctx)
4537     ctx.restore()
4538   },
4539 
4540   getSubtreeBoundingBox : function(identity) {
4541     if(identity === true) 
4542         identity = [1,0,0,1,0,0];
4543     if(identity) {
4544     	//CRIO
4545     	if(this.needMatrixUpdate)
4546     		this.transform(null, true);
4547         identity = CanvasSupport.tMatrixMultiply(CanvasSupport.tMatrixMultiply(
4548           [1,0,0,1,0,0], identity), this.relativeMatrix);
4549     }
4550     
4551     var bb = this.getAxisAlignedBoundingBox(identity)
4552     for (var i=0; i<this.childNodes.length; i++) {
4553       var cbb = this.childNodes[i].getSubtreeBoundingBox(identity)
4554 
4555       if (!bb) {
4556         bb = cbb
4557       } else if (cbb) {
4558         this.mergeBoundingBoxes(bb, cbb)
4559       }
4560     }
4561 
4562     return bb
4563   },
4564 
4565   mergeBoundingBoxes : function(bb, bb2) {
4566     var obx = bb[0], oby = bb[1]
4567     if (bb[0] > bb2[0]) bb[0] = bb2[0]
4568     if (bb[1] > bb2[1]) bb[1] = bb2[1]
4569     bb[2] += obx-bb[0]
4570     bb[3] += oby-bb[1]
4571     if (bb[2]+bb[0] < bb2[2]+bb2[0]) bb[2] = bb2[2]+bb2[0]-bb[0]
4572     if (bb[3]+bb[1] < bb2[3]+bb2[1]) bb[3] = bb2[3]+bb2[1]-bb[1]
4573   },
4574 
4575   transformBoundingBoxBy: function(bbox, m) {
4576     var xy1 = CanvasSupport.tMatrixMultiplyPoint(m,
4577       bbox[0], bbox[1])
4578     var xy2 = CanvasSupport.tMatrixMultiplyPoint(m,
4579       bbox[0]+bbox[2], bbox[1]+bbox[3])
4580     var xy3 = CanvasSupport.tMatrixMultiplyPoint(m,
4581       bbox[0], bbox[1]+bbox[3])
4582     var xy4 = CanvasSupport.tMatrixMultiplyPoint(m,
4583       bbox[0]+bbox[2], bbox[1])
4584     var x1 = Math.min(xy1[0], xy2[0], xy3[0], xy4[0])
4585     var x2 = Math.max(xy1[0], xy2[0], xy3[0], xy4[0])
4586     var y1 = Math.min(xy1[1], xy2[1], xy3[1], xy4[1])
4587     var y2 = Math.max(xy1[1], xy2[1], xy3[1], xy4[1])
4588     return [x1, y1, x2-x1, y2-y1]
4589   },
4590 
4591   getAxisAlignedBoundingBox : function(identity) {
4592   	//CRIO
4593     if(this.needMatrixUpdate)
4594     	this.transform(null, true);
4595     		
4596     if (!this.getBoundingBox)
4597     	return null;
4598 
4599     //if(identity && this.lastIdentityAABB)
4600     //    return this.lastIdentityAABB
4601     if(!identity && this.lastAABB)
4602         return this.lastAABB;
4603     
4604     var bbox = this.getBoundingBox()
4605     var ret = this.transformBoundingBoxBy(bbox, identity || this.currentMatrix)
4606     
4607     if(identity)
4608         return this.lastIdentityAABB = ret
4609     
4610     return this.lastAABB = ret
4611   },
4612 
4613   makeDraggable : function() {
4614     this.addEventListener('dragstart', function(ev) {
4615       this.dragStartPosition = {x: this.x, y: this.y};
4616       ev.stopPropagation();
4617       ev.preventDefault();
4618       return false;
4619     }, false);
4620     this.addEventListener('drag', function(ev) {
4621       this.x = this.dragStartPosition.x + this.root.dragX / this.parent.currentMatrix[0];
4622       this.y = this.dragStartPosition.y + this.root.dragY / this.parent.currentMatrix[3];
4623       ev.stopPropagation();
4624       ev.preventDefault();
4625       return false;
4626     }, false);
4627   }
4628 };

4644 /**
4645  * Canvas is the canvas manager class. It takes care of updating and drawing its
4646  * childNodes on a canvas element.
4647  * 
4648  * An example with a rotating rectangle:
4649  * 
4650  * var c = E.canvas(500, 500) var canvas = new Canvas(c) var rect = new
4651  * Rectangle(100, 100) rect.x = 250 rect.y = 250 rect.fill = true rect.fillStyle =
4652  * 'green' rect.addFrameListener(function(t) { this.rotation = ((t / 3000) % 1) *
4653  * Math.PI * 2 }) canvas.append(rect) document.body.appendChild(c)
4654  * 
4655  * 
4656  * To use the canvas as a manually updated image:
4657  * 
4658  * var canvas = new Canvas(E.canvas(200,40), { isPlaying : false,
4659  * redrawOnlyWhenChanged : true }) var c = new Circle(20) c.x = 100 c.y = 20
4660  * c.fill = true c.fillStyle = 'red' c.addFrameListener(function(t) { if
4661  * (this.root.absoluteMouseX != null) { this.x = this.root.mouseX // relative to
4662  * canvas surface this.root.changed = true } }) canvas.append(c)
4663  * 
4664  * 
4665  * Or by using raw onFrame-calls:
4666  * 
4667  * var canvas = new Canvas(E.canvas(200,40), { isPlaying : false, fill : true,
4668  * fillStyle : 'white' }) var c = new Circle(20) c.x = 100 c.y = 20 c.fill =
4669  * true c.fillStyle = 'red' canvas.append(c) canvas.onFrame()
4670  * 
4671  * 
4672  * Which is also the recommended way to use a canvas inside another canvas:
4673  * 
4674  * var canvas = new Canvas(E.canvas(200,40), { isPlaying : false }) var c = new
4675  * Circle(20, { x: 100, y: 20, fill: true, fillStyle: 'red' }) canvas.append(c)
4676  * 
4677  * var topCanvas = new Canvas(E.canvas(500, 500)) var canvasImage = new
4678  * ImageNode(canvas.canvas, {x: 250, y: 250}) topCanvas.append(canvasImage)
4679  * canvasImage.addFrameListener(function(t) { this.rotation = (t / 3000 % 1) *
4680  * Math.PI * 2 canvas.onFrame(t) })
4681  * 
4682  * @constructor
4683  * @extends CanvasNode
4684  * 
4685  * @property redrawOnlyWhatChanged Use dirty regions with the canvas to draw
4686  *      only changed portions of the screen.
4687  * @property redrawOnlyWhenChanged Run draw chain only when a change is made.
4688  * @property allowCacheAsBitmap Whether to allow cacheAsBitmap
4689  * @proeprty legacyCake Set this to true to enable old-school cake mode.
4690  */
4691 function Canvas() {
4692 	Canvas.prototype.initialize.apply(this, arguments)
4693 }

5112   createFrameLoop : function() {
5113     var self = this;
5114     var fl = {
5115       running : true,
5116       stop : function() {
5117         this.running = false;
5118       },
5119       run : function() {
5120         if (fl.running) {
5121           var st = +new Date;
5122           self.onFrame();
5123           var dt = +new Date - st;
5124           self.requestAnimFrame.call(window, fl.run, self.canvas.parentNode, dt);
5125         }
5126       }
5127     };
5128     this.requestAnimFrame.call(window, fl.run, this.canvas);
5129     return fl;
5130   },

5132   /**
5133      * Start frame loop.
5134      * 
5135      * The frame loop is an interval, where #onFrame is called every
5136      * #frameDuration milliseconds.
5137      */
5138   play : function() {
5139     this.stop();
5140     this.realTime = new Date().getTime();
5141     this.frameLoop = this.createFrameLoop();
5142     this.isPlaying = true;
5143   },
5144 
5145   /**
5146      * Stop frame loop.
5147      */

5149     this.__blurStop = false;
5150     if (this.frameLoop) {
5151       this.frameLoop.stop();
5152       this.frameLoop = null;
5153     }
5154     this.isPlaying = false;
5155   },

5157   dispatchEvent : function(ev) {
5158     if(ev.type == 'mousedown' || ev.type == 'mouseup' || ev.type == 'mousemove'  
5159           /* && (ev.__setX != this.mouseX || ev.__setY != this.mouseY)*/) {
5160         var ctx = this.getContext()
5161         
5162         this.canvas.parentNode.addMouseEvent(ev);
5163         
5164         //console.log('pick again', ev)
5165 
5166         if(!(this.numPicks > 1 && ev.type == 'mousemove'))
5167             this.handlePick(ctx);
5168     }
5169     
5170     var rv = CanvasNode.prototype.dispatchEvent.call(this, ev)
5171     if (ev.cursor) {
5172       if (this.canvas.style.cursor != ev.cursor)
5173         this.canvas.style.cursor = ev.cursor
5174     } else {
5175       if (this.canvas.style.cursor != this.cursor)
5176         this.canvas.style.cursor = this.cursor
5177     }
5178     return rv
5179   },

5181   handleRedrawRegion : function(ctx, dont_walk) {
5182 
5183     if(this.redrawOnlyWhatChanged || this.showRedrawRegions)
5184         if(!dont_walk) CanvasNode.prototype.handleRedrawRegion.call(this, ctx);
5185         
5186     //console.log('region length ' + this.dirtyRegions.length)
5187 
5188     this.dirtyBB = null;
5189     ctx.beginPath();
5190 
5191     if(this.redrawOnlyWhatChanged && !this.showRedrawRegions) {
5192         for(var i = 0 ; i < this.dirtyRegions.length ; i++) {
5193             var reg = this.dirtyRegions[i];
5194             reg = [reg[0] - 5, reg[1] - 5, reg[2] + 10, reg[3] + 10];
5195      
5196             if(!this.dirtyBB)
5197                 this.dirtyBB = reg;
5198             else
5199                 this.dirtyBB = this.mergeBoundingBoxes(this.dirtyBB, reg);
5200      		
5201             if(this.clear) ctx.clearRect(parseInt(reg[0]) - 5, parseInt(reg[1]) - 5, parseInt(reg[2]) + 10, parseInt(reg[3]) + 10);
5202             ctx.rect(parseInt(reg[0]) - 5, parseInt(reg[1]) - 5, parseInt(reg[2]) + 10, parseInt(reg[3]) + 10)
5203         }
5204         
5205         
5206     
5207         if(!this.dirtyRegions.length)
5208             ctx.rect(0, 0, 100, 100)
5209             
5210         ctx.clip();
5211     } else {
5212         //ctx.rect(0, 0, this.width, this.height)
5213         //ctx.clip();
5214         if(this.clear) ctx.clearRect(0, 0, this.width, this.height);
5215     }
5216 
5217     if(this.dirtyRegions.length)
5218         this.oldRegions = this.dirtyRegions;
5219         
5220     this.dirtyRegions = []
5221   },

5302   /**
5303      * The frame loop function. Called every #frameDuration milliseconds. Takes
5304      * an optional external time parameter (for syncing Canvases with each
5305      * other, e.g. when using a Canvas as an image.)
5306      * 
5307      * If the time parameter is given, the second parameter is used as the frame
5308      * time delta (i.e. the time elapsed since last frame.)
5309      * 
5310      * If time or timeDelta is not given, the canvas computes its own timeDelta.
5311      * 
5312      * @param time
5313      *            The external time. Optional.
5314      * @param timeDelta
5315      *            Time since last frame in milliseconds. Optional.
5316      */
5317   onFrame : function(time, timeDelta) {
5318     this.elementNodeZIndexCounter = 0
5319     this.drawOrderZIndexCounter = 0;
5320     
5321     Canvas.count = (Canvas.count || 0) + 1;
5322     
5323     //if(this.numMatrixUpdates > 15 || this.numRelMatrixUpdates > 15) {
5324     if(!(Canvas.count % (60 * 3))) {
5325     	//console.log("this.numMatrixUpdates " + [this.numMatrixUpdates, this.numRelMatrixUpdates].join(','));
5326     }
5327     
5328     if(this.numDOMUpdates > 15) {
5329     	//console.log("this.numDOMUpdates " + this.numDOMUpdates);
5330     }
5331 
5332     var ctx = this.getContext()
5333     try {
5334       var realTime = (new Date()).getTime()
5335       this.currentRealElapsed = (realTime - this.realTime);
5336       
5337       //if(this.currentRealElapsed < (this.frameLimit || 0) / 1.5)
5338       //      return;
5339 	  
5340 	  if (SHOW_FPS == true) {
5341 		  this.currentRealFps = 1000 / this.currentRealElapsed
5342 		  
5343 		  var nt = realTime / 1000;
5344 			//console.log((nt - this.lastFPSTime));
5345 		  if((nt - this.lastFPSTime) > 1) {
5346 			console.log(parseInt(this.frameCount / 
5347 			   (nt - this.lastFPSTime) * 100) / 100 + " fps");
5348 			console.log(parseInt(1000 * this.frameCount / this.calcFPSAccum 
5349 				* 100) / 100 + " calcFps");
5350 			
5351 			
5352 			console.log("this.numMatrixUpdates " + [this.numMatrixUpdates / this.frameCount , 
5353 				this.numRelMatrixUpdates / this.frameCount ].join(','));
5354 				
5355 			//console.log(['numChanged', this.numChanged / this.frameCount, 
5356 			//	'numChangedTrue', this.numChangedTrue / this.frameCount]);
5357 				
5358 		    this.numMatrixUpdates = 0;
5359 			this.numRelMatrixUpdates = 0;
5360 			this.numDOMUpdates = 0;
5361 			this.lastFPSTime = nt;
5362 			this.frameCount = 0;
5363 			this.calcFPSAccum = 0;
5364 			this.numChanged = 0;
5365 			this.numChangedTrue = 0;
5366 		  }
5367 		  
5368 		  this.frameCount++;
5369 	  }
5370 
5371       var dt = this.frameDuration * this.speed
5372       if (!this.fixedTimestep)
5373         dt = this.currentRealElapsed * this.speed
5374       this.realTime = realTime
5375       if (time != null) {
5376         this.time = time
5377         if (timeDelta)
5378           dt = timeDelta
5379       } else {
5380         this.time += dt
5381       }
5382       this.previousTarget = this.target
5383       this.target = null
5384       this.numPicks = 0;
5385       
5386       var will_draw = (!this.redrawOnlyWhenChanged || this.changed);
5387       this.handleUpdate(this.time, dt);
5388       
5389       if(this.enableBox2D) {
5390 	    this.worldAABB.minVertex.Set(0, 0);
5391 	    this.worldAABB.maxVertex.Set(this.width, this.height);
5392 	    
5393 	    this.world.Step(dt / 1000, 10);
5394 	  }
5395       
5396       
5397       if(0) 1;
5398       
5399      
5400      else if (!this.redrawOnlyWhenChanged || this.changed) {
5401         //try {
5402           //if (this.catchMouse) this.handlePick(ctx);
5403           ctx.beginPath();
5404           this.handleDraw(ctx)
5405         //} catch(e) {
5406         //  console.log(e)
5407           //throw(e)
5408         //}
5409       } 
5410       
5411       this.clearMouseEvents()
5412 
5413       
5414             
5415       //this.changed = false
5416       if(will_draw) {
5417 	      this.currentElapsed = (new Date().getTime() - this.realTime)
5418 	      this.elapsed += this.currentElapsed;
5419 	      this.calcFPSAccum += this.currentElapsed;
5420 	      this.currentFps = 1000 / this.currentElapsed
5421 	      this.frame++
5422 	      if (this.frame % this.fpsFrames == 0) {
5423 	        this.fps = this.fpsFrames*1000 / (this.elapsed)
5424 	        this.realFps = this.fpsFrames*1000 / (new Date().getTime() - this.startTime)
5425 	        this.elapsed = 0
5426 	        this.startTime = new Date().getTime()
5427 	      }
5428           
5429       }
5430 
5431     } finally {//catch(e) {
5432       /*if (ctx) {
5433         // screwed up, context is borked
5434         try {
5435           // FIXME don't be stupid
5436           for (var i=0; i<1000; i++)
5437             ctx.restore()
5438         } catch(er) {}
5439       }
5440       delete this.context*/
5441       //throw(e)
5442     }
5443   },

5517   /**
5518      * Sets globalAlpha to this.opacity and clears the canvas if #clear is set
5519      * to true. If #fill is also set to true, fills the canvas rectangle instead
5520      * of clearing (using #fillStyle as the color.)
5521      * 
5522      * @param ctx
5523      *            Canvas drawing context
5524      */
5525   draw : function(ctx) {
5526     ctx.setGlobalAlpha( this.opacity )
5527     if (this.clear) {
5528       if (ctx.fillOn) {
5529         ctx.beginPath()
5530         ctx.rect(0,0, this.canvas.width, this.canvas.height)
5531         ctx.fill()
5532       } else {
5533         ctx.clearRect(0,0, this.canvas.width, this.canvas.height)
5534       }
5535     }
5536     // set default fill and stroke for the canvas contents
5537     ctx.fillStyle = 'black'
5538     ctx.strokeStyle = 'black'
5539     ctx.fillOn = false
5540     ctx.strokeOn = false
5541   }

5678   handleUpdate : function() {
5679     CanvasNode.handleUpdate.apply(this, arguments)
5680     if (this.willBeDrawn) {
5681     	//CRIO
5682       this.transform(null, true)
5683       if (!this.sound) this.loadSound()
5684       if (this.ready) {
5685         if (this.transformSound) {
5686           var x = this.currentMatrix[4]
5687           var y = this.currentMatrix[5]
5688           var a = this.currentMatrix[2]
5689           var b = this.currentMatrix[3]
5690           var c = this.currentMatrix[0]
5691           var d = this.currentMatrix[1]
5692           var hw = this.root.width * 0.5
5693           var ys = Math.sqrt(a*a + b*b)
5694           var xs = Math.sqrt(c*c + d*d)
5695           this.setVolume(ys)
5696           this.setPan((x - hw) / hw)
5697         }
5698         if (this.needPauseUpdate) {
5699           this.needPauseUpdate = false
5700           this._pauseSound()
5701         }
5702         if (this.needPlayUpdate) {
5703           this.needPlayUpdate = false
5704           if (this.playing) this._playSound()
5705           else this._stopSound()
5706         }
5707         if (this.needStatusUpdate) {
5708           this._setSoundVolume()
5709           this._setSoundPan()
5710         }
5711       }
5712     }
5713   },
5714 
5715   _autoPlaySound : function() {
5716     if (this.autoPlay) this.play()
5717   },
5718 
5719   _setSoundVolume : function() {
5720     this.sound.setVolume(this.volume)
5721   },
5722 
5723   _setSoundPan : function() {

5725   },

5876     }
5877     var xy = CanvasSupport.tMatrixMultiplyPoint(baseTransform.slice(0,4).concat([0,0]),
5878       xo, yo)
5879     var x = this.currentMatrix[4] + xy[0]
5880     var y = this.currentMatrix[5] + xy[1]
5881     var a = this.currentMatrix[2]
5882     var b = this.currentMatrix[3]
5883     var c = this.currentMatrix[0]
5884     var d = this.currentMatrix[1]
5885     var ys = Math.sqrt(a*a + b*b)
5886     var xs = Math.sqrt(c*c + d*d)
5887     if (ctx.fontFamily != null)
5888       this.element.style.fontFamily = ctx.fontFamily
5889 
5890     var wkt = CanvasSupport.isCSSTransformSupported()
5891     if(!this.DOMelement) {
5892         if (wkt && !this.noScaling) {
5893           this.element.style.transform =
5894           this.element.style.MozTransform =
5895           this.element.style.WebkitTransform = 'matrix('+baseTransform.join(",")+')';
5896           //alert('matrix('+baseTransform.join(",")+')')
5897         } else {
5898           this.element.style.transform =
5899           this.element.style.MozTransform =
5900           this.element.style.WebkitTransform = '';
5901         }
5902     }
5903     if (ctx.fontSize != null) {
5904       if (this.noScaling || wkt) {
5905         this.element.style.fontSize = ctx.fontSize + 'px'
5906       } else {
5907         this.element.style.fontSize = ctx.fontSize * ys + 'px'
5908       }
5909     } else {
5910       if (this.noScaling || wkt) {
5911         this.element.style.fontSize = 'inherit'
5912       } else {
5913         this.element.style.fontSize = 100 * ys + '%'
5914       }
5915     }
5916     if (this.noAlpha)
5917       this.element.style.opacity = 1
5918     else
5919       this.element.style.opacity = ctx.globalAlpha
5920     if (!this.element.parentNode && this.root.canvas.parentNode && !this.DOMelement) {
5921       this.element.style.visibility = 'hidden'
5922       this.root.canvas.parentNode.appendChild(this.element)
5923       var hidden = true
5924     }
5925     var fs = this.color || this.fill
5926     if (this.parent) {
5927       if (!fs || !fs.length)
5928         fs = this.parent.color
5929       if (!fs || !fs.length)
5930         fs = this.parent.fill
5931     }
5932     if (!fs || !fs.length)
5933       fs = ctx.fillStyle
5934     if (typeof(fs) == 'string') {
5935       if (fs.search(/^rgba\(/) != -1) {
5936         this.element.style.color = 'rgb(' +
5937           fs.match(/\d+/g).slice(0,3).join(",") +
5938           ')'
5939       } else {
5940         this.element.style.color = fs
5941       }
5942     } else if (fs.length) {
5943       this.element.style.color = 'rgb(' + fs.slice(0,3).map(Math.floor).join(",") + ')'
5944     }
5945     var dx = 0, dy = 0
5946     if (bb) {
5947       this.element.style.width = Math.floor(xs * bb[2]) + 'px'
5948       this.element.style.height = Math.floor(ys * bb[3]) + 'px'
5949       this.eWidth = xs
5950       this.eHeight = ys
5951     } else {
5952       this.element.style.width = ''
5953       this.element.style.height = ''
5954       var align = this.align || this.textAnchor
5955       var origin = [0,0]
5956       if (align == 'center' || align == 'middle') {
5957         dx = -this.element.offsetWidth / 2
5958         origin[0] = '50%'
5959       } else if (align == 'right') {
5960         dx = -this.element.offsetWidth
5961         origin[0] = '100%'
5962       }
5963       var valign = this.valign
5964       if (valign == 'center' || valign == 'middle') {
5965         dy = -this.element.offsetHeight / 2
5966         origin[1] = '50%'
5967       } else if (valign == 'bottom') {
5968         dy = -this.element.offsetHeight
5969         origin[1] = '100%'
5970       }
5971       this.element.style.WebkitTransformOrigin =
5972       this.element.style.MozTransformOrigin = origin.join(" ")
5973       this.eWidth = this.element.offsetWidth / xs
5974       this.eHeight = this.element.offsetHeight / ys
5975     }
5976     if (wkt && !this.noScaling) {
5977       this.element.style.left = Math.floor(dx) + 'px'
5978       this.element.style.top = Math.floor(dy) + 'px'
5979     } else {
5980       this.element.style.left = Math.floor(x+dx) + 'px'
5981       this.element.style.top = Math.floor(y+dy) + 'px'
5982     }
5983     if (hidden)
5984       this.element.style.visibility = 'visible'
5985   }
5986 };
5987 Profiler.wrap_class(ElementNode, "ElementNode");
5988 ElementNode.Extenze(CanvasNode);

5990 
5991 /**
5992  * A Drawable is a CanvasNode with possible fill, stroke and clip.
5993  * 
5994  * It draws the path by calling #drawGeometry
5995  * 
5996  * @constructor
5997  * @extends CanvasNode
5998  */
5999 function Drawable() {
6000      Drawable.prototype.initialize.apply(this, arguments)
6001 }
6002 
6003 Drawable.prototype = { 
6004   pickable : true,
6005   
6006   // 'inside' // clip before drawing the stroke
6007   // | 'above' // draw stroke after the fill
6008   // | 'below' // draw stroke before the fill
6009   strokeMode : 'above',
6010 
6011   ABOVE : 'above', BELOW : 'below', INSIDE : 'inside',
6012 
6013   /** @override */ initialize : function(config) {
6014     CanvasNode.prototype.initialize.call(this, config)
6015   },
6016 
6017   /**
6018      * Draws the picking path for the Drawable.
6019      * 
6020      * The default version begins a new path and calls drawGeometry.
6021      * 
6022      * @param ctx
6023      *            Canvas drawing context
6024      */
6025   drawPickingPath : function(ctx) {
6026     if (!this.drawGeometry) return
6027     ctx.beginPath()
6028     this.drawGeometry(ctx)
6029   },
6030 
6031   /**
6032      * Returns true if the point x,y is inside the path of a drawable node.
6033      * 
6034      * The x,y point is in user-space coordinates, meaning that e.g. the point
6035      * 5,5 will always be inside the rectangle [0, 0, 10, 10], regardless of the
6036      * transform on the rectangle.
6037      * 
6038      * @param x
6039      *            X-coordinate of the point.
6040      * @param y
6041      *            Y-coordinate of the point.
6042      * @return Whether the point is inside the path of this node.
6043      * @type boolean
6044      */
6045   isPointInPath : function(x, y) {
6046     return false
6047   },
6048 
6049   isVisible : function(ctx) {
6050     var abb = this.getAxisAlignedBoundingBox()
6051     if (!abb) return true
6052     var x1 = abb[0], x2 = abb[0]+abb[2], y1 = abb[1], y2 = abb[1]+abb[3]
6053     var w = this.root.width
6054     var h = this.root.height
6055     if (this.root.drawBoundingBoxes) {
6056       /*ctx.save()
6057         var bbox = this.getBoundingBox()
6058         ctx.beginPath()
6059         ctx.rect(bbox[0], bbox[1], bbox[2], bbox[3])
6060         ctx.strokeStyle = 'green'
6061         ctx.lineWidth = 1
6062         ctx.stroke()
6063       ctx.restore()*/
6064       ctx.save()
6065         CanvasSupport.setTransform(ctx, [1,0,0,1,0,0], this.currentMatrix)
6066         ctx.beginPath()
6067         ctx.rect(x1, y1, x2-x1, y2-y1)
6068         ctx.strokeStyle = 'red'
6069         ctx.lineWidth = 1.5
6070         ctx.stroke()
6071       ctx.restore()
6072     }
6073     var visible = !(x2 < 0 || x1 > w || y2 < 0 || y1 > h)
6074     return visible
6075   },
6076 
6077   createSubtreePath : function(ctx, skipTransform) {
6078     ctx.save()
6079     if (!skipTransform) this.transform(ctx, true)
6080     if (this.drawGeometry) this.drawGeometry(ctx)
6081     for (var i=0; i<this.childNodes.length; i++)
6082       this.childNodes[i].createSubtreePath(ctx)
6083     ctx.restore()
6084   },
6085 
6086   /**
6087      * Draws the Drawable. Begins a path and calls this.drawGeometry, followed
6088      * by possibly filling, stroking and clipping the path, depending on whether
6089      * #fill, #stroke and #clip are set.
6090      * 
6091      * @param ctx
6092      *            Canvas drawing context
6093      */
6094   draw : function(ctx) {
6095     if (!this.drawGeometry) return
6096     // bbox checking is slower than just drawing in most cases.
6097     // and caching the bboxes is hard to do correctly.
6098     // plus, bboxes aren't hierarchical.
6099     // so we are being glib :|
6100     
6101     ctx.beginPath()
6102     this.drawGeometry(ctx)
6103     if(!this.fill && !this.stroke) return;
6104     
6105     var ft = false, st = false;
6106     /*var ft = (ctx.fillStyle.transformList ||
6107               ctx.fillStyle.matrix ||
6108               ctx.fillStyle.scale != null ||
6109               ctx.fillStyle.rotation ||
6110               ctx.fillStyle.x ||
6111               ctx.fillStyle.y )
6112     var st = (ctx.strokeStyle.transformList ||
6113               ctx.strokeStyle.matrix ||
6114               ctx.strokeStyle.scale != null ||
6115               ctx.strokeStyle.rotation ||
6116               ctx.strokeStyle.x ||
6117               ctx.strokeStyle.y )*/
6118     
6119     if (ctx.strokeOn) {
6120       switch (this.strokeMode) {
6121         case this.ABOVE:
6122           if (ctx.fillOn) this.doFill(ctx,ft)
6123           this.doStroke(ctx, st)
6124           break
6125         case this.BELOW:
6126           this.doStroke(ctx, st)
6127           if (ctx.fillOn) this.doFill(ctx,ft)
6128           break
6129         case this.INSIDE:
6130           if (ctx.fillOn) this.doFill(ctx,ft)
6131           ctx.save()
6132           var lw = ctx.lineWidth
6133           ctx.setLineWidth(1)
6134           this.doStroke(ctx, st)
6135           ctx.setLineWidth(lw)
6136           ctx.clip()
6137           this.doStroke(ctx, st)
6138           ctx.restore()
6139           break
6140       }
6141     } else if (ctx.fillOn) {
6142       this.doFill(ctx,ft)
6143     }
6144     //this.drawMarkers(ctx)
6145     if (this.clip) ctx.clip()
6146   },
6147 
6148   doFill : function(ctx, ft) {
6149     if (ft || (this.getBoundingBox && ctx.fillStyle.units == this.OBJECTBOUNDINGBOX)) {
6150       ctx.save()
6151       if (this.getBoundingBox && ctx.fillStyle.units == this.OBJECTBOUNDINGBOX) {
6152         var bb = this.getBoundingBox()
6153         var sx = bb[2]
6154         var sy = bb[3]
6155         ctx.translate(bb[0],bb[1])
6156         ctx.scale(sx,sy)
6157       }
6158       ctx.fillStyle.transform(ctx)
6159     }
6160     if (this.fillOpacity != null) {
6161       var go = ctx.globalAlpha
6162       ctx.setGlobalAlpha(go * this.fillOpacity)
6163       ctx.fill()
6164       ctx.globalAlpha = go
6165     } else {
6166       ctx.fill()
6167     }
6168     if (ft) ctx.restore()
6169   },
6170 
6171   doStroke : function(ctx, st) {
6172     if (st || (this.getBoundingBox && ctx.strokeStyle.units == this.OBJECTBOUNDINGBOX)) {
6173       ctx.save()
6174       if (this.getBoundingBox && ctx.strokeStyle.units == this.OBJECTBOUNDINGBOX) {
6175         var bb = this.getBoundingBox()
6176         var sx = bb[2]
6177         var sy = bb[3]
6178         ctx.translate(bb[0],bb[1])
6179         ctx.scale(sx,sy)
6180       }
6181       ctx.strokeStyle.needMatrixUpdate = true
6182       ctx.strokeStyle.transform(ctx)
6183       if (sx != null)
6184         CanvasSupport.tScale(ctx.strokeStyle.currentMatrix, sx, sy)
6185       var cm = ctx.strokeStyle.currentMatrix
6186       // fix stroke width scale (non-uniform scales screw us up though)
6187       var sw = Math.sqrt(Math.max(
6188         cm[0]*cm[0] + cm[1]*cm[1],
6189         cm[2]*cm[2] + cm[3]*cm[3]
6190       ))
6191       ctx.setLineWidth(((ctx.lineWidth == null) ? 1 : ctx.lineWidth) / sw)
6192     }
6193     if (this.strokeOpacity != null) {
6194       var go = ctx.globalAlpha
6195       ctx.setGlobalAlpha(go * this.strokeOpacity)
6196       ctx.stroke()
6197       ctx.globalAlpha = go
6198     } else {
6199       ctx.stroke()
6200     }
6201     if (st) ctx.restore()
6202   },
6203 
6204   drawMarkers : function(ctx) {
6205     var sm = this.markerStart || this.marker
6206     var em = this.markerEnd || this.marker
6207     var mm = this.markerMid || this.marker
6208     if (sm && this.getStartPoint) {
6209       var pa = this.getStartPoint()
6210       if (sm.orient != null && sm.orient != 'auto')
6211         pa.angle = sm.orient
6212       var scale = (sm.markerUnits == 'strokeWidth') ? ctx.lineWidth : 1
6213       ctx.save()
6214         ctx.translate(pa.point[0], pa.point[1])
6215         ctx.scale(scale, scale)
6216         ctx.rotate(pa.angle)
6217         var mat = CanvasSupport.tRotate(
6218           CanvasSupport.tScale(
6219           CanvasSupport.tTranslate(
6220             this.currentMatrix.slice(0),
6221             pa.point[0], pa.point[1]
6222           ), scale, scale), pa.angle)
6223         sm.__copyMatrix(mat)
6224         sm.handleDraw(ctx)
6225       ctx.restore()
6226     }
6227     if (em && this.getEndPoint) {
6228       var pa = this.getEndPoint()
6229       if (em.orient != null && em.orient != 'auto')
6230         pa.angle = em.orient
6231       var scale = (em.markerUnits == 'strokeWidth') ? ctx.lineWidth : 1
6232       ctx.save()
6233         ctx.translate(pa.point[0], pa.point[1])
6234         ctx.scale(scale, scale)
6235         ctx.rotate(pa.angle)
6236         var mat = CanvasSupport.tRotate(
6237           CanvasSupport.tScale(
6238           CanvasSupport.tTranslate(
6239             this.currentMatrix.slice(0),
6240             pa.point[0], pa.point[1]
6241           ), scale, scale), pa.angle)
6242         em.__copyMatrix(mat)
6243         em.handleDraw(ctx)
6244       ctx.restore()
6245     }
6246     if (mm && this.getMidPoints) {
6247       var pas = this.getMidPoints()
6248       var scale = (mm.markerUnits == 'strokeWidth') ? ctx.lineWidth : 1
6249       for (var i=0; i<pas.length; i++) {
6250         var pa = pas[i]
6251         ctx.save()
6252           ctx.translate(pa.point[0], pa.point[1])
6253           ctx.scale(scale, scale)
6254           if (mm.orient != null && mm.orient != 'auto')
6255             pa.angle = em.orient
6256           ctx.rotate(pa.angle)
6257           var mat = CanvasSupport.tRotate(
6258             CanvasSupport.tScale(
6259             CanvasSupport.tTranslate(
6260               this.currentMatrix.slice(0),
6261               pa.point[0], pa.point[1]
6262             ), scale, scale), pa.angle)
6263           mm.__copyMatrix(mat)
6264           mm.handleDraw(ctx)
6265         ctx.restore()
6266       }
6267     }
6268   },
6269 
6270   getStartPoint : false,
6271   getEndPoint : false,
6272   getMidPoints : false,
6273   getBoundingBox : false
6274 
6275 };
6276 Profiler.wrap_class(Drawable, "Drawable");
6277 Drawable.Extenze(CanvasNode);

6346 /**
6347  * Circle is used for creating circular paths.
6348  * 
6349  * Uses context.arc(...).
6350  * 
6351  * Attributes: cx, cy, radius, startAngle, endAngle, clockwise, closePath,
6352  * includeCenter
6353  * 
6354  * @constructor
6355  * @extends Drawable
6356  * @param radius
6357  *            Radius of the circle.
6358  * @param config
6359  *            Object of properties to be set on initialization.
6360  */
6361 //Circle = Klass(Drawable, {
6362 function Circle() {
6363 }
6364 Circle.prototype = {
6365   cx : 0,
6366   cy : 0,
6367   radius : 10,
6368   startAngle : 0,
6369   endAngle : Math.PI * 2,
6370   clockwise : false,
6371   closePath : true,
6372   includeCenter : false,
6373 
6374   /** @override */ initialize : function(radius, config) {
6375     if (radius != null) this.radius = radius
6376     Drawable.initialize.call(this, config)
6377   },
6378   
6379   /**
6380      * Creates a circular path using ctx.arc(...).
6381      * 
6382      * @param ctx
6383      *            Canvas drawing context.
6384      */
6385   drawGeometry : function(ctx) {
6386     if (this.radius == 0) return
6387     if (this.includeCenter)
6388       ctx.moveTo(this.cx, this.cy)
6389     ctx.arc(this.cx, this.cy, this.radius, this.startAngle, this.endAngle, this.clockwise)
6390     if (this.closePath) {
6391       // firefox 2 is buggy without the endpoint
6392       var x2 = Math.cos(this.endAngle)
6393       var y2 = Math.sin(this.endAngle)
6394       ctx.moveTo(this.cx + x2*this.radius, this.cy + y2 * this.radius)
6395       ctx.closePath()
6396     }
6397   },
6398   
6399   /**
6400      * Returns true if the point x,y is inside the radius of the circle.
6401      * 
6402      * The x,y point is in user-space coordinates, meaning that e.g. the point
6403      * 5,0 will always be inside a circle with radius of 10 and center at
6404      * origin, regardless of the transform on the circle.
6405      * 
6406      * @param x
6407      *            X-coordinate of the point.
6408      * @param y
6409      *            Y-coordinate of the point.
6410      * @return Whether the point is inside the radius of this circle.
6411      * @type boolean
6412      */
6413   isPointInPath : function(x,y) {
6414     x -= this.cx
6415     y -= this.cy
6416     return (x*x + y*y) <= (this.radius*this.radius)
6417   },
6418 
6419   getBoundingBox : function() {
6420     return [this.cx-this.radius, this.cy-this.radius,
6421             2*this.radius, 2*this.radius]
6422   }
6423 };
6424 Circle.Extenze(Drawable);

6427 /**
6428  * Ellipse is a scaled circle. Except it isn't. Because that wouldn't work in
6429  * Opera.
6430  * 
6431  * @constructor
6432  * @extends Drawable
6433  * @param config Object of properties to be set on initialization.
6434  */
6435 //Ellipse = Klass(Circle, {
6436 function Ellipse(config) {
6437 	Ellipse.prototype.initialize.apply(this, arguments)
6438 }
6439 Ellipse.prototype = {
6440   radiusX : 0,
6441   radiusY : 0,
6442 
6443   /** @override */ initialize : function(radiusX, radiusY, config) {
6444     this.radiusX = radiusX
6445     this.radiusY = radiusY
6446     Circle.initialize.call(this, 1, config)
6447   },
6448 
6449   drawGeometry : function(ctx) {
6450     if (this.radiusX == 0 || this.radiusY == 0) return
6451     var k = 0.5522847498
6452     var x = this.cx
6453     var y = this.cy
6454     var krx = k*this.radiusX
6455     var kry = k*this.radiusY
6456     ctx.moveTo(x+this.radiusX, y)
6457     ctx.bezierCurveTo(x+this.radiusX, y-kry, x+krx, y-this.radiusY, x, y-this.radiusY)
6458     ctx.bezierCurveTo(x-krx, y-this.radiusY, x-this.radiusX, y-kry, x-this.radiusX, y)
6459     ctx.bezierCurveTo(x-this.radiusX, y+kry, x-krx, y+this.radiusY, x, y+this.radiusY)
6460     ctx.bezierCurveTo(x+krx, y+this.radiusY, x+this.radiusX, y+kry, x+this.radiusX, y)
6461   },
6462 
6463   isPointInPath : function(x, y) {
6464     // does this work?
6465     x -= this.cx
6466     y -= this.cy
6467     x /= this.radiusX
6468     y /= this.radiusY
6469     return (x*x + y*y) <= 1
6470   },
6471 
6472   getBoundingBox : function() {
6473     return [this.cx-this.radiusX, this.cy-this.radiusY,
6474             this.radiusX*2, this.radiusY*2]
6475   }
6476 };
6477 Ellipse.Extenze(Drawable);

6480 /**
6481  * A Spiral is a function graph drawn in polar coordinates from startAngle to
6482  * endAngle. And the source of all life energy, etc.
6483  */
6484 Spiral = Klass(Drawable, {
6485   cx : 0,
6486   cy : 0,
6487   startRadius : 0,
6488   startAngle : 0,
6489   endAngle : 0,
6490 
6491   radiusFunction : function(a) {
6492     return a
6493   },
6494 
6495   /** @override */ initialize : function(endAngle, config) {
6496     this.endAngle = endAngle
6497     Drawable.initialize.call(this, config)
6498   },
6499 
6500   drawGeometry : function(ctx) {
6501     var x = this.cx
6502     var y = this.cy
6503     var a = this.startAngle
6504     var r = this.startRadius + this.radiusFunction(a)
6505     ctx.moveTo(x+Math.cos(a)*r, y-Math.sin(a)*r)
6506     if (this.startAngle < this.endAngle) {
6507       a += 0.1
6508       r = this.startRadius + this.radiusFunction(a)
6509       while (a < this.endAngle) {
6510         ctx.lineTo(x+Math.cos(a)*r, y-Math.sin(a)*r)
6511         a += 0.1
6512         r = this.startRadius + this.radiusFunction(a)
6513       }
6514     } else {
6515       a -= 0.1
6516       r = this.startRadius + this.radiusFunction(a)
6517       while (a > this.endAngle) {
6518         ctx.lineTo(x+Math.cos(a)*r, y-Math.sin(a)*r)
6519         a -= 0.1
6520         r = this.startRadius + this.radiusFunction(a)
6521       }
6522     }
6523     a = this.endAngle
6524     r = this.startRadius + this.radiusFunction(a)
6525     ctx.lineTo(x+Math.cos(a)*r, y-Math.sin(a)*r)
6526   },
6527 
6528   isPointInPath : function(x, y) {
6529     return false
6530   }
6531 })
6532 
6533 Canvas.prototype.checkProgram = function(prog) {
6534 	if(this.gl.currentProgram = prog) return;
6535 	
6536

6539 /**
6540  * Rectangle is used for creating rectangular paths.
6541  * 
6542  * Uses context.rect(...).
6543  * 
6544  * Attributes: cx, cy, width, height, centered, rx, ry
6545  * 
6546  * If centered is set to true, centers the rectangle on the origin. Otherwise
6547  * the top-left corner of the rectangle is on the origin.
6548  * 
6549  * @constructor
6550  * @extends Drawable
6551  * @param width
6552  *            Width of the rectangle.
6553  * @param height
6554  *            Height of the rectangle.
6555  * @param config
6556  *            Object of properties to be set on initialization.
6557  */
6558 //Rectangle = Klass(Drawable, {
6559 function Rectangle() {
6560      Rectangle.prototype.initialize.apply(this, arguments)
6561 }
6562 Rectangle.prototype = {
6563   cx : 0,
6564   cy : 0,
6565   x2 : 0,
6566   y2 : 0,
6567   width : 0,
6568   height : 0,
6569   rx : 0,
6570   ry : 0,
6571   centered : false,
6572 
6573   /** @override */ initialize : function(width, height, config) {
6574     if (width != null) {
6575       this.width = width
6576       this.height = width
6577     }
6578     if (height != null) this.height = height
6579     Drawable.initialize.call(this, config)
6580     
6581     if(this.DOMelement)
6582         this.DOMelement.style.backgroundColor = '#000000';
6583   },
6584   
6585   
6586 
6587   /**
6588      * Creates a rectangular path using ctx.rect(...).
6589      * 
6590      * @param ctx
6591      *            Canvas drawing context.
6592      */
6593   drawGeometry : function(ctx) {
6594     var x = this.cx
6595     var y = this.cy
6596     var w = (this.width || (this.x2 - x))
6597     var h = (this.height || (this.y2 - y))
6598     if (w == 0 || h == 0) return
6599     if (this.centered) {
6600       x -= 0.5*w
6601       y -= 0.5*h
6602     }
6603     if (this.rx || this.ry) {
6604       // hahaa, welcome to the undocumented rounded corners path
6605       // using bezier curves approximating ellipse quadrants
6606       var rx = Math.min(w * 0.5, this.rx || this.ry)
6607       var ry = Math.min(h * 0.5, this.ry || rx)
6608       var k = 0.5522847498
6609       var krx = k*rx
6610       var kry = k*ry
6611       ctx.moveTo(x+rx, y)
6612       ctx.lineTo(x-rx+w, y)
6613       ctx.bezierCurveTo(x-rx+w + krx, y, x+w, y+ry-kry, x+w, y+ry)
6614       ctx.lineTo(x+w, y+h-ry)
6615       ctx.bezierCurveTo(x+w, y+h-ry+kry, x-rx+w+krx, y+h, x-rx+w, y+h)
6616       ctx.lineTo(x+rx, y+h)
6617       ctx.bezierCurveTo(x+rx-krx, y+h, x, y+h-ry+kry, x, y+h-ry)
6618       ctx.lineTo(x, y+ry)
6619       ctx.bezierCurveTo(x, y+ry-kry, x+rx-krx, y, x+rx, y)
6620       ctx.closePath()
6621     } else {
6622       if (w < 0) x += w
6623       if (h < 0) y += h
6624       ctx.rect(x, y, Math.abs(w), Math.abs(h))
6625     }
6626   },
6627 
6628   /**
6629      * Returns true if the point x,y is inside this rectangle.
6630      * 
6631      * The x,y point is in user-space coordinates, meaning that e.g. the point
6632      * 5,5 will always be inside the rectangle [0, 0, 10, 10], regardless of the
6633      * transform on the rectangle.
6634      * 
6635      * @param x
6636      *            X-coordinate of the point.
6637      * @param y
6638      *            Y-coordinate of the point.
6639      * @return Whether the point is inside this rectangle.
6640      * @type boolean
6641      */
6642   isPointInPath : function(x,y) {
6643     x -= this.cx
6644     y -= this.cy
6645     if (this.centered) {
6646       x += this.width/2
6647       y += this.height/2
6648     }
6649     return (x >= 0 && x <= this.width && y >= 0 && y <= this.height)
6650   },
6651 
6652   getBoundingBox : function() {
6653     var x = this.cx
6654     var y = this.cy
6655     if (this.centered) {
6656       x -= this.width/2
6657       y -= this.height/2
6658     }
6659     return [x,y,this.width,this.height]
6660   }
6661 };

6663 Rectangle.Extenze(Drawable);

6665 /**
6666  * Polygon is used for creating paths consisting of straight line segments.
6667  * 
6668  * Attributes: segments - The vertices of the polygon, e.g. [0,0, 1,1, 1,2, 0,1]
6669  * closePath - Whether to close the path, default is true.
6670  * 
6671  * @param segments
6672  *            The vertices of the polygon.
6673  * @param closePath
6674  *            Whether to close the path.
6675  * @param config
6676  *            Optional config hash.
6677  */
6678 Polygon = Klass(Drawable, {
6679   segments : [],
6680   closePath : true,
6681 
6682   /** @override */ initialize : function(segments, config) {
6683     this.segments = segments
6684     Drawable.initialize.call(this, config)
6685   },
6686 
6687   drawGeometry : function(ctx) {
6688     if (!this.segments || this.segments.length < 2) return
6689     var s = this.segments
6690     ctx.moveTo(s[0], s[1])
6691     for (var i=2; i<s.length; i+=2) {
6692       ctx.lineTo(s[i], s[i+1])
6693     }
6694     if (this.closePath)
6695       ctx.closePath()
6696   },
6697 
6698   isPointInPath : function(px,py) {
6699     if (!this.segments || this.segments.length < 2) return false
6700     var bbox = this.getBoundingBox()
6701     return (px >= bbox[0] && px <= bbox[0]+bbox[2] &&
6702             py >= bbox[1] && py <= bbox[1]+bbox[3])
6703   },
6704 
6705   getStartPoint : function() {
6706     if (!this.segments || this.segments.length < 2)
6707       return {point:[0,0], angle:0}
6708     var a = 0
6709     if (this.segments.length > 2) {
6710       a = Curves.lineAngle(this.segments.slice(0,2), this.segments.slice(2,4))
6711     }
6712     return {point: this.segments.slice(0,2),
6713             angle: a}
6714   },
6715 
6716   getEndPoint : function() {
6717     if (!this.segments || this.segments.length < 2)
6718       return {point:[0,0], angle:0}
6719     var a = 0
6720     if (this.segments.length > 2) {
6721       a = Curves.lineAngle(this.segments.slice(-4,-2), this.segments.slice(-2))
6722     }
6723     return {point: this.segments.slice(-2),
6724             angle: a}
6725   },
6726 
6727   getMidPoints : function() {
6728     if (!this.segments || this.segments.length < 2)
6729       return []
6730     var segs = this.segments
6731     var verts = []
6732     for (var i=2; i<segs.length-2; i+=2) {
6733       var a = segs.slice(i-2,i)
6734       var b = segs.slice(i, i+2)
6735       var c = segs.slice(i+2, i+4)
6736       var t = 0.5 * (Curves.lineAngle(a,b) + Curves.lineAngle(b,c))
6737       verts.push(
6738         {point: b, angle: t}
6739       )
6740     }
6741     return verts
6742   },
6743 
6744   getBoundingBox : function() {
6745     var minX = Infinity, minY = Infinity, maxX = -Infinity, maxY = -Infinity
6746     var s = this.segments
6747     for (var i=0; i<s.length; i+=2) {
6748       var x = s[i], y = s[i+1]
6749       if (x < minX) minX = x
6750       if (x > maxX) maxX = x
6751       if (y < minY) minY = y
6752       if (y > maxY) maxY = y
6753     }
6754     return [minX, minY, maxX-minX, maxY-minY]
6755   }
6756 })

6760 /**
6761  * CatmullRomSpline draws a Catmull-Rom spline, with optional looping and path
6762  * closing. Handy for motion paths.
6763  * 
6764  * @param segments
6765  *            Control points for the spline, as [[x,y], [x,y], ...]
6766  * @param config
6767  *            Optional config hash.
6768  */
6769 CatmullRomSpline = Klass(Drawable, {
6770   segments : [],
6771   loop : false,
6772   closePath : false,
6773 
6774   /** @override */ initialize : function(segments, config) {
6775     this.segments = segments
6776     Drawable.initialize.call(this, config)
6777   },
6778 
6779   drawGeometry : function(ctx) {
6780     var x1 = this.currentMatrix[0]
6781     var x2 = this.currentMatrix[1]
6782     var y1 = this.currentMatrix[2]
6783     var y2 = this.currentMatrix[3]
6784     var xs = x1*x1 + x2*x2
6785     var ys = y1*y1 + y2*y2
6786     var s = Math.floor(Math.sqrt(Math.max(xs, ys)))
6787     var cmp = this.compiled
6788     if (!cmp || cmp.scale != s) {
6789       cmp = this.compile(s)
6790     }
6791     for (var i=0; i<cmp.length; i++) {
6792       var cmd = cmp[i]
6793       ctx[cmd[0]].apply(ctx, cmd[1])
6794     }
6795     if (this.closePath)
6796       ctx.closePath()
6797   },
6798 
6799   compile : function(scale) {
6800     if (!scale) scale = 1
6801     var compiled = []
6802     if (this.segments && this.segments.length >= (this.loop ? 1 : 4)) {
6803       var segs = this.segments
6804       if (this.loop) {
6805         segs = segs.slice(0)
6806         segs.unshift(segs[segs.length-1])
6807         segs.push(segs[1])
6808         segs.push(segs[2])
6809       }
6810       // FIXME don't be stupid
6811       var point_spacing = 1 / (15 * (scale+0.5))
6812       var a,b,c,d,p,pp
6813       compiled.push(['moveTo', segs[1].slice(0)])
6814       p = segs[1]
6815       for (var j=1; j<segs.length-2; j++) {
6816         a = segs[j-1]
6817         b = segs[j]
6818         c = segs[j+1]
6819         d = segs[j+2]
6820         for (var i=0; i<1; i+=point_spacing) {
6821           pp = p
6822           p = Curves.catmullRomPoint(a,b,c,d,i)
6823           compiled.push(['lineTo', p])
6824         }
6825       }
6826       p = Curves.catmullRomPoint(a,b,c,d,1)
6827       compiled.push(['lineTo', p])
6828     }
6829     compiled.scale = scale
6830     this.compiled = compiled
6831     return compiled
6832   },
6833 
6834   getBoundingBox : function() {
6835     var minX = Infinity, minY = Infinity, maxX = -Infinity, maxY = -Infinity
6836     var segments = (this.compiled ? this.compiled : this.compile())
6837     for (var i=0; i<segments.length; i++) {
6838       var seg = segments[i][1]
6839       for (var j=0; j<seg.length; j+=2) {
6840         var x = seg[j], y = seg[j+1]
6841         if (x < minX) minX = x
6842         if (x > maxX) maxX = x
6843         if (y < minY) minY = y
6844         if (y > maxY) maxY = y
6845       }
6846     }
6847     return [minX, minY, maxX-minX, maxY-minY]
6848   },
6849 
6850   pointAt : function(t) {
6851     if (!this.segments) return [0,0]
6852     if (this.segments.length >= (this.loop ? 1 : 4)) {
6853       var segs = this.segments
6854       if (this.loop) {
6855         segs = segs.slice(0)
6856         segs.unshift(segs[segs.length-1])
6857         segs.push(segs[1])
6858         segs.push(segs[2])
6859       }
6860       // turn t into segment_index.segment_t
6861       var rt = t * (segs.length - 3)
6862       var j = Math.floor(rt)
6863       var st = rt-j
6864       var a = segs[j],
6865           b = segs[j+1],
6866           c = segs[j+2],
6867           d = segs[j+3]
6868       return Curves.catmullRomPoint(a,b,c,d,st)
6869     } else {
6870       return this.segments[0]
6871     }
6872   },
6873 
6874   pointAngleAt : function(t) {
6875     if (!this.segments) return {point: [0,0], angle: 0}
6876     if (this.segments.length >= (this.loop ? 1 : 4)) {
6877       var segs = this.segments
6878       if (this.loop) {
6879         segs = segs.slice(0)
6880         segs.unshift(segs[segs.length-1])
6881         segs.push(segs[1])
6882         segs.push(segs[2])
6883       }
6884       // turn t into segment_index.segment_t
6885       var rt = t * (segs.length - 3)
6886       var j = Math.floor(rt)
6887       var st = rt-j
6888       var a = segs[j],
6889           b = segs[j+1],
6890           c = segs[j+2],
6891           d = segs[j+3]
6892       return Curves.catmullRomPointAngle(a,b,c,d,st)
6893     } else {
6894       return {point:this.segments[0] || [0,0], angle: 0}
6895     }
6896   }
6897 })
