6900 /**
6901  * Path is used for creating custom paths.
6902  * 
6903  * Attributes: segments, closePath.
6904  * 
6905  * var path = new Path([ ['moveTo', [-50, -60]], ['lineTo', [30, 50], ['lineTo',
6906  * [-50, 50]], ['bezierCurveTo', [-50, 100, -50, 100, 0, 100]],
6907  * ['quadraticCurveTo', [0, 120, -20, 130]], ['quadraticCurveTo', [0, 140, 0,
6908  * 160]], ['bezierCurveTo', [-10, 160, -20, 170, -30, 180]],
6909  * ['quadraticCurveTo', [10, 230, -50, 260]] ])
6910  * 
6911  * The path segments are used as [methodName, arguments] on the canvas drawing
6912  * context, so the possible path segments are:
6913  * 
6914  * ['moveTo', [x, y]] ['lineTo', [x, y]] ['quadraticCurveTo', [control_point_x,
6915  * control_point_y, x, y]] ['bezierCurveTo', [cp1x, cp1y, cp2x, cp2y, x, y]]
6916  * ['arc', [x, y, radius, startAngle, endAngle, drawClockwise]] ['arcTo', [x1,
6917  * y1, x2, y2, radius]] ['rect', [x, y, width, height]]
6918  * 
6919  * You can also pass an SVG path string as segments.
6920  * 
6921  * var path = new Path("M 100 100 L 300 100 L 200 300 z", { stroke: true,
6922  * strokeStyle: 'blue', fill: true, fillStyle: 'red', lineWidth: 3 })
6923  * 
6924  * @constructor
6925  * @extends Drawable
6926  * @param segments
6927  *            The path segments.
6928  * @param config
6929  *            Object of properties to be set on initialization.
6930  */
6931 //Path = Klass(Drawable, {
6932 function Path() {
6933     Path.prototype.initialize.apply(this, arguments);
6934 }
6935 Path.prototype = {
6936   segments : [],
6937   closePath : false,
6938 
6939   /** @override */ initialize : function(segments, config) {
6940     this.segments = segments
6941     Drawable.initialize.call(this, config)
6942   },
6943 
6944   /**
6945      * Creates a path on the given drawing context.
6946      * 
6947      * For each path segment, calls the context method named in the first
6948      * element of the segment with the rest of the segment elements as
6949      * arguments.
6950      * 
6951      * SVG paths are parsed and executed.
6952      * 
6953      * Closes the path if closePath is true.
6954      * 
6955      * @param ctx
6956      *            Canvas drawing context.
6957      */
6958   drawGeometry : function(ctx) {
6959     var segments = this.getSegments()
6960     for (var i=0; i<segments.length; i++) {
6961       var seg = segments[i]
6962       ctx[seg[0]].apply(ctx, seg[1])
6963     }
6964     if (this.closePath)
6965       ctx.closePath()
6966   },
6967 
6968   /**
6969      * Returns true if the point x,y is inside the path's bounding rectangle.
6970      * 
6971      * The x,y point is in user-space coordinates, meaning that e.g. the point
6972      * 5,5 will always be inside the rectangle [0, 0, 10, 10], regardless of the
6973      * transform on the rectangle.
6974      * 
6975      * @param px
6976      *            X-coordinate of the point.
6977      * @param py
6978      *            Y-coordinate of the point.
6979      * @return Whether the point is inside the path's bounding rectangle.
6980      * @type boolean
6981      */
6982   isPointInPath : function(px,py) {
6983     var bbox = this.getBoundingBox()
6984     return (px >= bbox[0] && px <= bbox[0]+bbox[2] &&
6985             py >= bbox[1] && py <= bbox[1]+bbox[3])
6986   },
6987 
6988   getBoundingBox : function() {
6989     if (!(this.compiled && this.compiledBoundingBox)) {
6990       var minX = Infinity, minY = Infinity, maxX = -Infinity, maxY = -Infinity
6991       var segments = this.getSegments()
6992       for (var i=0; i<segments.length; i++) {
6993         var seg = segments[i][1]
6994         for (var j=0; j<seg.length; j+=2) {
6995           var x = seg[j], y = seg[j+1]
6996           if (x < minX) minX = x
6997           if (x > maxX) maxX = x
6998           if (y < minY) minY = y
6999           if (y > maxY) maxY = y
7000         }
7001       }
7002       this.compiledBoundingBox = [minX, minY, maxX-minX, maxY-minY]
7003     }
7004     return this.compiledBoundingBox
7005   },
7006 
7007   getStartPoint : function() {
7008     var segs = this.getSegments()
7009     if (!segs || !segs[0]) return {point: [0,0], angle: 0}
7010     var fs = segs[0]
7011     var c = fs[1]
7012     var point = [c[c.length-2], c[c.length-1]]
7013     var ss = segs[1]
7014     var angle = 0
7015     if (ss) {
7016       c2 = ss[1]
7017       angle = Curves.lineAngle(point, [c2[c2.length-2], c2[c2.length-1]])
7018     }
7019     return {
7020       point: point,
7021       angle: angle
7022     }
7023   },
7024 
7025   getEndPoint : function() {
7026     var segs = this.getSegments()
7027     if (!segs || !segs[0]) return {point: [0,0], angle: 0}
7028     var fs = segs[segs.length-1]
7029     var c = fs[1]
7030     var point = [c[c.length-2], c[c.length-1]]
7031     var ss = segs[segs.length-2]
7032     var angle = 0
7033     if (ss) {
7034       c2 = ss[1]
7035       angle = Curves.lineAngle([c2[c2.length-2], c2[c2.length-1]], point)
7036     }
7037     return {
7038       point: point,
7039       angle: angle
7040     }
7041   },
7042 
7043   getMidPoints : function() {
7044     var segs = this.getSegments()
7045     if (this.vertices)
7046       return this.vertices.slice(1,-1)
7047     var verts = []
7048     for (var i=1; i<segs.length-1; i++) {
7049       var b = segs[i-1][1].slice(-2)
7050       var c = segs[i][1].slice(0,2)
7051       if (segs[i-1].length > 2) {
7052         var a = segs[i-1][1].slice(-4,-2)
7053         var t = 0.5 * (Curves.lineAngle(a,b) + Curves.lineAngle(b,c))
7054       } else {
7055         var t = Curves.lineAngle(b,c)
7056       }
7057       verts.push(
7058         {point: b, angle: t}
7059       )
7060       var id = segs[i][2]
7061       if (id != null) {
7062         i++
7063         while (segs[i] && segs[i][2] == id) i++
7064         i--
7065       }
7066     }
7067     return verts
7068   },
7069 
7070   getSegments : function() {
7071     if (typeof(this.segments) == 'string') {
7072       if (!this.compiled || this.segments != this.compiledSegments) {
7073         this.compiled = this.compileSVGPath(this.segments)
7074         this.compiledSegments = this.segments
7075       }
7076     } else if (!this.compiled) {
7077       this.compiled = Object.clone(this.segments)
7078     }
7079     return this.compiled
7080   },
7081 
7082   /**
7083      * Compiles an SVG path string into an array of canvas context method calls.
7084      * 
7085      * Returns an array of [methodName, [arg1, arg2, ...]] method call arrays.
7086      */
7087   compileSVGPath : function(svgPath) {
7088     var segs = svgPath.split(/(?=[a-z])/i)
7089     var x = 0
7090     var y = 0
7091     var px,py
7092     var pc
7093     var commands = []
7094     for (var i=0; i<segs.length; i++) {
7095       var seg = segs[i]
7096       var cmd = seg.match(/[a-z]/i)
7097       if (!cmd) return [];
7098       cmd = cmd[0];
7099       var coords = seg.match(/[+-]?\d+(\.\d+(e\d+(\.\d+)?)?)?/gi)
7100       if (coords) coords = coords.map(parseFloat)
7101       switch(cmd) {
7102         case 'M':
7103           x = coords[0]
7104           y = coords[1]
7105           px = py = null
7106           commands.push(['moveTo', [x, y]])
7107           break
7108         case 'm':
7109           x += coords[0]
7110           y += coords[1]
7111           px = py = null
7112           commands.push(['moveTo', [x, y]])
7113           break
7114 
7115         case 'L':
7116           x = coords[0]
7117           y = coords[1]
7118           px = py = null
7119           commands.push(['lineTo', [x, y]])
7120           break
7121         case 'l':
7122           x += coords[0]
7123           y += coords[1]
7124           px = py = null
7125           commands.push(['lineTo', [x, y]])
7126           break
7127         case 'H':
7128           x = coords[0]
7129           px = py = null
7130           commands.push(['lineTo', [x, y]])
7131           break
7132         case 'h':
7133           x += coords[0]
7134           px = py = null
7135           commands.push(['lineTo', [x,y]])
7136           break
7137         case 'V':
7138           y = coords[0]
7139           px = py = null
7140           commands.push(['lineTo', [x,y]])
7141           break
7142         case 'v':
7143           y += coords[0]
7144           px = py = null
7145           commands.push(['lineTo', [x,y]])
7146           break
7147 
7148         case 'C':
7149           x = coords[4]
7150           y = coords[5]
7151           px = coords[2]
7152           py = coords[3]
7153           commands.push(['bezierCurveTo', coords])
7154           break
7155         case 'c':
7156           commands.push(['bezierCurveTo',[
7157             coords[0] + x, coords[1] + y,
7158             coords[2] + x, coords[3] + y,
7159             coords[4] + x, coords[5] + y
7160           ]])
7161           px = x + coords[2]
7162           py = y + coords[3]
7163           x += coords[4]
7164           y += coords[5]
7165           break
7166 
7167         case 'S':
7168           if (px == null || !pc.match(/[sc]/i)) {
7169             px = x
7170             py = y
7171           }
7172           commands.push(['bezierCurveTo',[
7173             x-(px-x), y-(py-y),
7174             coords[0], coords[1],
7175             coords[2], coords[3]
7176           ]])
7177           px = coords[0]
7178           py = coords[1]
7179           x = coords[2]
7180           y = coords[3]
7181           break
7182         case 's':
7183           if (px == null || !pc.match(/[sc]/i)) {
7184             px = x
7185             py = y
7186           }
7187           commands.push(['bezierCurveTo',[
7188             x-(px-x), y-(py-y),
7189             x + coords[0], y + coords[1],
7190             x + coords[2], y + coords[3]
7191           ]])
7192           px = x + coords[0]
7193           py = y + coords[1]
7194           x += coords[2]
7195           y += coords[3]
7196           break
7197 
7198         case 'Q':
7199           px = coords[0]
7200           py = coords[1]
7201           x = coords[2]
7202           y = coords[3]
7203           commands.push(['quadraticCurveTo', coords])
7204           break
7205         case 'q':
7206           commands.push(['quadraticCurveTo',[
7207             coords[0] + x, coords[1] + y,
7208             coords[2] + x, coords[3] + y
7209           ]])
7210           px = x + coords[0]
7211           py = y + coords[1]
7212           x += coords[2]
7213           y += coords[3]
7214           break
7215 
7216         case 'T':
7217           if (px == null || !pc.match(/[qt]/i)) {
7218             px = x
7219             py = y
7220           } else {
7221             px = x-(px-x)
7222             py = y-(py-y)
7223           }
7224           commands.push(['quadraticCurveTo',[
7225             px, py,
7226             coords[0], coords[1]
7227           ]])
7228           px = x-(px-x)
7229           py = y-(py-y)
7230           x = coords[0]
7231           y = coords[1]
7232           break
7233         case 't':
7234           if (px == null || !pc.match(/[qt]/i)) {
7235             px = x
7236             py = y
7237           } else {
7238             px = x-(px-x)
7239             py = y-(py-y)
7240           }
7241           commands.push(['quadraticCurveTo',[
7242             px, py,
7243             x + coords[0], y + coords[1]
7244           ]])
7245           x += coords[0]
7246           y += coords[1]
7247           break
7248 
7249         case 'A':
7250           var arc_segs = this.solveArc(x,y, coords)
7251           for (var l=0; l<arc_segs.length; l++) arc_segs[l][2] = i
7252           commands.push.apply(commands, arc_segs)
7253           x = coords[5]
7254           y = coords[6]
7255           break
7256         case 'a':
7257           coords[5] += x
7258           coords[6] += y
7259           var arc_segs = this.solveArc(x,y, coords)
7260           for (var l=0; l<arc_segs.length; l++) arc_segs[l][2] = i
7261           commands.push.apply(commands, arc_segs)
7262           x = coords[5]
7263           y = coords[6]
7264           break
7265 
7266         case 'Z':
7267           commands.push(['closePath', []])
7268           break
7269         case 'z':
7270           commands.push(['closePath', []])
7271           break
7272       }
7273       pc = cmd
7274     }
7275     return commands
7276   },
7277 
7278   solveArc : function(x, y, coords) {
7279     var rx = coords[0]
7280     var ry = coords[1]
7281     var rot = coords[2]
7282     var large = coords[3]
7283     var sweep = coords[4]
7284     var ex = coords[5]
7285     var ey = coords[6]
7286     var segs = this.arcToSegments(ex, ey, rx, ry, large, sweep, rot, x, y)
7287     var retval = []
7288     for (var i=0; i<segs.length; i++) {
7289       retval.push(['bezierCurveTo', this.segmentToBezier.apply(this, segs[i])])
7290     }
7291     return retval
7292   },
7293 
7294 
7295   // Copied from Inkscape svgtopdf, thanks!
7296   arcToSegments : function(x, y, rx, ry, large, sweep, rotateX, ox, oy) {
7297     var th = rotateX * (Math.PI/180)
7298     var sin_th = Math.sin(th)
7299     var cos_th = Math.cos(th)
7300     rx = Math.abs(rx)
7301     ry = Math.abs(ry)
7302     var px = cos_th * (ox - x) * 0.5 + sin_th * (oy - y) * 0.5
7303     var py = cos_th * (oy - y) * 0.5 - sin_th * (ox - x) * 0.5
7304     var pl = (px*px) / (rx*rx) + (py*py) / (ry*ry)
7305     if (pl > 1) {
7306       pl = Math.sqrt(pl)
7307       rx *= pl
7308       ry *= pl
7309     }
7310 
7311     var a00 = cos_th / rx
7312     var a01 = sin_th / rx
7313     var a10 = (-sin_th) / ry
7314     var a11 = (cos_th) / ry
7315     var x0 = a00 * ox + a01 * oy
7316     var y0 = a10 * ox + a11 * oy
7317     var x1 = a00 * x + a01 * y
7318     var y1 = a10 * x + a11 * y
7319 
7320     var d = (x1-x0) * (x1-x0) + (y1-y0) * (y1-y0)
7321     var sfactor_sq = 1 / d - 0.25
7322     if (sfactor_sq < 0) sfactor_sq = 0
7323     var sfactor = Math.sqrt(sfactor_sq)
7324     if (sweep == large) sfactor = -sfactor
7325     var xc = 0.5 * (x0 + x1) - sfactor * (y1-y0)
7326     var yc = 0.5 * (y0 + y1) + sfactor * (x1-x0)
7327 
7328     var th0 = Math.atan2(y0-yc, x0-xc)
7329     var th1 = Math.atan2(y1-yc, x1-xc)
7330 
7331     var th_arc = th1-th0
7332     if (th_arc < 0 && sweep == 1){
7333       th_arc += 2*Math.PI
7334     } else if (th_arc > 0 && sweep == 0) {
7335       th_arc -= 2 * Math.PI
7336     }
7337 
7338     var segments = Math.ceil(Math.abs(th_arc / (Math.PI * 0.5 + 0.001)))
7339     var result = []
7340     for (var i=0; i<segments; i++) {
7341       var th2 = th0 + i * th_arc / segments
7342       var th3 = th0 + (i+1) * th_arc / segments
7343       result[i] = [xc, yc, th2, th3, rx, ry, sin_th, cos_th]
7344     }
7345 
7346     return result
7347   },
7348 
7349   segmentToBezier : function(cx, cy, th0, th1, rx, ry, sin_th, cos_th) {
7350     var a00 = cos_th * rx
7351     var a01 = -sin_th * ry
7352     var a10 = sin_th * rx
7353     var a11 = cos_th * ry
7354 
7355     var th_half = 0.5 * (th1 - th0)
7356     var t = (8/3) * Math.sin(th_half * 0.5) * Math.sin(th_half * 0.5) / Math.sin(th_half)
7357     var x1 = cx + Math.cos(th0) - t * Math.sin(th0)
7358     var y1 = cy + Math.sin(th0) + t * Math.cos(th0)
7359     var x3 = cx + Math.cos(th1)
7360     var y3 = cy + Math.sin(th1)
7361     var x2 = x3 + t * Math.sin(th1)
7362     var y2 = y3 - t * Math.cos(th1)
7363     return [
7364       a00 * x1 + a01 * y1,      a10 * x1 + a11 * y1,
7365       a00 * x2 + a01 * y2,      a10 * x2 + a11 * y2,
7366       a00 * x3 + a01 * y3,      a10 * x3 + a11 * y3
7367     ]
7368   },
7369 
7370   getLength : function() {
7371     var segs = this.getSegments()
7372     if (segs.arcLength == null) {
7373       segs.arcLength = 0
7374       var x=0, y=0
7375       for (var i=0; i<segs.length; i++) {
7376         var args = segs[i][1]
7377         if (args.length < 2) continue
7378         switch(segs[i][0]) {
7379           case 'bezierCurveTo':
7380             segs[i][3] = Curves.cubicLength(
7381               [x, y], [args[0], args[1]], [args[2], args[3]], [args[4], args[5]])
7382             break
7383           case 'quadraticCurveTo':
7384             segs[i][3] = Curves.quadraticLength(
7385               [x, y], [args[0], args[1]], [args[2], args[3]])
7386             break
7387           case 'lineTo':
7388             segs[i][3] = Curves.lineLength(
7389               [x, y], [args[0], args[1]])
7390             break
7391         }
7392         if (segs[i][3])
7393           segs.arcLength += segs[i][3]
7394         x = args[args.length-2]
7395         y = args[args.length-1]
7396       }
7397     }
7398     return segs.arcLength
7399   },
7400 
7401   pointAngleAt : function(t, config) {
7402     var segments = []
7403     var segs = this.getSegments()
7404     var length = this.getLength()
7405     var x = 0, y = 0
7406     for (var i=0; i<segs.length; i++) {
7407       var seg = segs[i]
7408       if (seg[1].length < 2) continue
7409       if (seg[0] != 'moveTo') {
7410         segments.push([x, y, seg])
7411       }
7412       x = seg[1][seg[1].length-2]
7413       y = seg[1][seg[1].length-1]
7414     }
7415     if (segments.length < 1)
7416       return {point: [x, y], angle: 0 }
7417     if (t >= 1) {
7418       var rt = 1
7419       var seg = segments[segments.length-1]
7420     } else if (config && config.discrete) {
7421       var idx = Math.floor(t * segments.length)
7422       var seg = segments[idx]
7423       var rt = 0
7424     } else if (config && config.linear) {
7425       var idx = t * segments.length
7426       var rt = idx - Math.floor(idx)
7427       var seg = segments[Math.floor(idx)]
7428     } else {
7429       var len = t * length
7430       var rlen = 0, idx, rt
7431       for (var i=0; i<segments.length; i++) {
7432         if (rlen + segments[i][2][3] > len) {
7433           idx = i
7434           rt = (len - rlen) / segments[i][2][3]
7435           break
7436         }
7437         rlen += segments[i][2][3]
7438       }
7439       var seg = segments[idx]
7440     }
7441     var angle = 0
7442     var cmd = seg[2][0]
7443     var args = seg[2][1]
7444     switch (cmd) {
7445       case 'bezierCurveTo':
7446         return Curves.cubicLengthPointAngle([seg[0], seg[1]], [args[0], args[1]], [args[2], args[3]], [args[4], args[5]], rt)
7447         break
7448       case 'quadraticCurveTo':
7449         return Curves.quadraticLengthPointAngle([seg[0], seg[1]], [args[0], args[1]], [args[2], args[3]], rt)
7450         break
7451       case 'lineTo':
7452         x = Curves.linearValue(seg[0], args[0], rt)
7453         y = Curves.linearValue(seg[1], args[1], rt)
7454         angle = Curves.lineAngle([seg[0], seg[1]], [args[0], args[1]], rt)
7455         break
7456     }
7457     return {point: [x, y], angle: angle }
7458   }
7459 };

7462 /**
7463  * ImageNode is used for drawing images. Creates a rectangular path around the
7464  * drawn image.
7465  * 
7466  * Attributes:
7467  * 
7468  * centered - If true, image center is at the origin. Otherwise image top-left
7469  * is at the origin. usePattern - Use a pattern fill for drawing the image
7470  * (instead of drawImage.) Doesn't do sub-image drawing, and Safari doesn't like
7471  * scaled image patterns. sX, sY, sWidth, sHeight - Area of image to draw.
7472  * Optional. dX, dY - Coordinates where to draw the image. Default is 0, 0.
7473  * dWidth, dHeight - Size of the drawn image. Optional.
7474  * 
7475  * Example:
7476  * 
7477  * var img = new Image() img.src = 'foo.jpg' var imageGeo = new ImageNode(img)
7478  * 
7479  * @constructor
7480  * @extends Drawable
7481  * @param {Image} image
7482  *            Image to draw.
7483  * @param config
7484  *            Object of properties to be set on initialization.
7485  * 
7486  * @property {Number} sX Source image X Offset
7487  * @property {Number} sY Source image Y Offset
7488  * @property {Number} sWidth Source rectangle region width
7489  * @property {Number} sHeight Source rectangle region height
7490  * @property {Number} dX Destination X offset
7491  * @property {Number} dY Destination Y offset
7492  * @property {Number} dWidth Destination rectangle region width
7493  * @property {Number} dHeight Destination rectangle region height
7494  * @property {boolean} centered True to put [0,0] in the image center, 
7495  *    or false for the upper left
7496  * @property {Image} image The image object to draw
7497  */
7498 //ImageNode = Klass(Drawable, {

7530   /**
7531      * Draws the image on the given drawing context.
7532      * 
7533      * Creates a rectangular path around the drawn image (for possible stroke
7534      * and/or fill.)
7535      * 
7536      * @private
7537      * @param ctx
7538      *            Canvas drawing context.
7539      */
7540   drawGeometry : function(ctx) {
7541     if(this.imageIsLoaded || Object.isImageLoaded(this.image)) {
7542     	this.imageIsLoaded = true;
7543       if(this.rimage === null) this.rimage = this.image.real || this.image;
7544       var cm = this.currentMatrix;
7545       //var w = this.dWidth == null ? this.image.width : this.dWidth
7546       //var h = this.dHeight == null ? this.image.height : this.dHeight
7547       if(this.dHeight === null && this.image.height) {
7548       	this.dHeight = this.image.height;
7549       	this.dWidth = this.image.width;
7550       }
7551       if(this.hdHeight === null) {
7552       	this.hdWidth = -this.dWidth / 2;
7553       	this.hdHeight = -this.dHeight / 2;
7554       }
7555       var w = this.dWidth;
7556       var h = this.dHeight;
7557       //w /= cm[0];
7558       //h /= cm[3];
7559       var x = this.dX;
7560       var y = this.dY;
7561       if(this.centered === true) {
7562       	x += this.hdWidth;
7563         y += this.hdHeight;
7564       }
7565       
7566       if (this.dWidth !== null) {
7567         if (this.sWidth !== null) {
7568           ctx.drawImage(this.rimage,
7569             this.sX, this.sY, this.sWidth, this.sHeight,
7570             x, y, w, h)
7571         } else {
7572           ctx.drawImage(this.rimage, x, y, w, h)
7573         }
7574       } else {
7575         w = this.image.width
7576         h = this.image.height
7577         if (this.usePattern) {
7578           if (!this.imagePattern)
7579             this.imagePattern = new Pattern(this.image, 'repeat')
7580           var fs = this.imagePattern.compiled
7581           if (!fs)
7582             fs = this.imagePattern.compile(ctx)
7583           ctx.save()
7584           ctx.beginPath()
7585           ctx.rect(x, y, w, h)
7586           ctx.setFillStyle(fs)
7587           ctx.fill()
7588           ctx.restore()
7589           ctx.beginPath()
7590         } else {
7591           ctx.drawImage(this.rimage, x, y)
7592         }
7593       }
7594     } else {
7595       var w = this.dWidth
7596       var h = this.dHeight
7597       if (!( w && h )) return
7598       var x = this.dX + (this.centered ? -w * 0.5 : 0)
7599       var y = this.dY + (this.centered ? -h * 0.5 : 0)
7600     }
7601     //ctx.rect(x, y, w, h)
7602   },

7604   /**
7605      * Creates a bounding rectangle path for the image on the given drawing
7606      * context.
7607      * 
7608      * @private
7609      * @param ctx
7610      *            Canvas drawing context.
7611      */
7612   drawPickingPath : function(ctx) {
7613     var x = this.dX + (this.centered ? -this.image.width * 0.5 : 0)
7614     var y = this.dY + (this.centered ? -this.image.height * 0.5 : 0)
7615     var w = this.dWidth
7616     var h = this.dHeight
7617     if (this.dWidth == null) {
7618       w = this.image.width
7619       h = this.image.height
7620     }
7621     ctx.rect(x, y, w, h)
7622   },
7623 
7624   /**
7625      * Returns true if the point x,y is inside the image rectangle.
7626      * 
7627      * The x,y point is in user-space coordinates, meaning that e.g. the point
7628      * 5,5 will always be inside the rectangle [0, 0, 10, 10], regardless of the
7629      * transform on the rectangle.
7630      * 
7631      * @private
7632      * @param x
7633      *            X-coordinate of the point.
7634      * @param y
7635      *            Y-coordinate of the point.
7636      * @return Whether the point is inside the image rectangle.
7637      * @type boolean
7638      */
7639   isPointInPath : function(x,y) {
7640     x -= this.dX
7641     y -= this.dY
7642     if (this.centered) {
7643       x += this.image.width * 0.5
7644       y += this.image.height * 0.5
7645     }
7646     var w = this.dWidth
7647     var h = this.dHeight
7648     if (this.dWidth == null) {
7649       w = this.image.width
7650       h = this.image.height
7651     }
7652     return ((x >= 0) && (x <= w) && (y >= 0) && (y <= h))
7653   },
7654 
7655   getBoundingBox : function() {
7656     var x = this.dX
7657     var y = this.dY
7658     var w = this.dWidth
7659     var h = this.dHeight
7660     if (this.dWidth == null && this.image) {
7661       w = this.image.width
7662       h = this.image.height
7663     }
7664     if (this.centered) {
7665       x -= w * 0.5
7666       y -= h * 0.5
7667     }
7668     return [x, y, w, h]
7669   }
7670 };

7737     this['text'] = this.text;
7738     
7739     this.addEventListener('rootChanged', function(e) {
7740     	if(this.root.isFake || !e.removeRoot) return;
7741     	
7742     	if(this.GLimg && this.root.useEGL) { //removing
7743 	  		gl.addAction(['_DELETE_TEXTURE', parseInt(this.GLimg)]);
7744 	  		this.GLimg = null;
7745 	  	}
7746 	  	
7747 	  	if(this.root.useWebgl && this.webGLImage) { //removing
7748 	  		e.removeRoot.gl.deleteTexture(this.webGLImage);
7749 	  		this.webGLImage = null;
7750 	  	}
7751     });
7752   },

7795   computeXForAlign : function() {
7796     if (this.align == 'left') // most hit branch

7798     else if (this.align == 'right')
7799       return -this.dimensions.width
7800     else if (this.align == 'center')
7801       return  -this.dimensions.width * 0.5
7802   },

7804   measureTextHTML5 : function(octx) {

7806

7808 	  	ctx = this.root.getContext();
7809 	    ctx.save();
7810 	    
7811 	    this.transform(ctx);
7812 	    ctx.setTransform(1,0,0,1,0,0);
7813   	}
7814   	
7815     // FIXME measureText is retarded
7816     var size = 12;//this.scale;

7820

7822             var s = parts[0].substr(0, parts[0].length - 2);
7823             //console.log(s);
7824             s = Number(s);
7825             
7826             size = s;
7827         }
7828     } else if(this.fontSize)
7829     	size = parseInt(this.fontSize);

7835     if (this.textBaseline != null)

7847   },

7850   	
7851     var x = this.cx + this.computeXForAlign();
7852     var y = this.cy + 1.4;
7853     ctx.fillText(this.text, x, y);//, this.maxWidth);
7854   },

7856   drawPickingPathHTML5 : function(ctx) {
7857   	this.dimensions = this.measureText(ctx);
7858     var ascender = 15 // this.dimensions.ascender
7859     var ry = this.cy - ascender
7860     ctx.rect(this.cx, ry, this.dimensions.width, this.dimensions.height)
7861   },
7862   
7863   getBoundingBox : function() {
7864   	//this.dimensions = this.measureText(null);
7865 
7866     if(!this.dimensions || ! this.dimensions.width) 
7867     	this.dimensions = this.measureText(null);
7868 
7869     if(!this.dimensions) return [0, 0, 0, 0];
7870 
7871     var ascender = this.actualTextHeight * 0.5;
7872     var ep = this.actualTextHeight * this.actualTextHeight / 50;
7873     var ry = this.cy - ascender
7874     var x = this.cx + this.computeXForAlign()
7875     
7876     var hoff = 0;
7877     var out = [x - ep, ry, this.dimensions.width + ep * 2, this.dimensions.height];
7878     
7879     switch(this.textBaseline) {
7880     	case 'top':
7881     		hoff = -0.5 * out[3];
7882     		break;
7883     	case 'bottom':
7884     		hoff = 0.5 * out[3];
7885     		break;
7886     	case 'alphabetic':
7887     		hoff = 0.25 * out[3];
7888     		break;
7889     	case 'middle':
7890     	default:
7891     }
7892     
7893     out[1] -= hoff;
7894 
7895     return out;
7896   },

7902   drawMozText : function(ctx) {
7903     var x = this.cx + this.computeXForAlign()
7904     var y = this.cy + 0
7905     if (this.pathGeometry) {
7906       this.pathGeometry.draw(ctx)
7907       ctx.mozDrawTextAlongPath(this.text, this.path)
7908     } else {
7909       ctx.save()
7910       ctx.translate(x,y)
7911       if (this.asPath) {
7912         ctx.mozPathText(this.text)
7913       } else {
7914         ctx.mozDrawText(this.text)
7915       }
7916       ctx.restore()
7917     }
7918   },

7922     var y = this.cy + 0

7924         this.pathGeometry.draw(ctx)
7925         // ctx.mozDrawTextAlongPath(this.text, this.path)
7926     } else if (!this.accuratePicking) {
7927       var ascender = 15 // this.dimensions.ascender
7928       var ry = y - ascender
7929       ctx.rect(x, ry, this.dimensions.width, this.dimensions.height)

7944   measureTextPerfectWorld : function(ctx) {
7945     return ctx.measureText(this.text)
7946   },
7947 
7948   drawPerfectWorld : function(ctx) {
7949     if (this.pathGeometry) {
7950       this.pathGeometry.draw(ctx)
7951       if (this.asPath)
7952         ctx.pathTextAlongPath(this.text)
7953       else
7954         ctx.drawTextAlongPath(this.text)
7955     } else if (this.asPath) {
7956       ctx.pathText(this.text)
7957     } else {
7958       ctx.drawText(this.text)
7959     }
7960   },
7961 
7962   drawPickingPathPerfectWorld : function(ctx) {
7963     if (this.accuratePicking) {
7964       if (this.pathGeometry) {
7965         ctx.pathTextAlongPath(this.text)
7966       } else {
7967         ctx.pathText(this.text)
7968       }
7969     } else { // creates a path of text bounding box
7970       if (this.pathGeometry) {
7971         ctx.textRectAlongPath(this.text)
7972       } else {
7973         ctx.textRect(this.text)
7974       }
7975     }
7976   }
7977 };
7978 switch(CanvasSupport.getTextBackend()) {
7979     case 'HTML5':

7983        break;

7986        TextNode.prototype.__pickingMethod = TextNode.prototype.drawPickingPathMozText;
7987        TextNode.prototype.__measureTextMethod = TextNode.prototype.measureTextMozText;
7988        break;
7989     default:
7990         throw new Error("No draw function for " + CanvasSupport.getTextBackend());

7996 /**
7997  * Gradient is a linear or radial color gradient that can be used as a
7998  * strokeStyle or fillStyle.
7999  * 
8000  * Example:
8001  * 
8002  * var g = new Gradient({ type : 'radial', endRadius : 40, colorStops : [ [0,
8003  * '#000'], [0.2, '#ffffff'], [0.5, [255, 0, 0]], [0.8, [0, 255, 255, 0.5]],
8004  * [1.0, 'rgba(255, 0, 255, 0.8)'] ] })
8005  * 
8006  * @constructor
8007  * @property {String} type Type of the gradient, 'linear' or 'radial'.
8008  * @param config
8009  *      Object of properties to be set on initialization.
8010  * @property {Number} startX
8011  * @property {Number} startY Coordinates for the starting point of the gradient. Center of the starting
8012  *      circle of a radial gradient. Default is 0, 0.
8013  * @property {Number} endX
8014  * @property {Number} endY Coordinates for
8015  *      the ending point of the gradient. Center of the ending circle of a radial
8016  *      gradient. Default is 0, 0.
8017  * @property {Number} startRadius The radius of the starting circle of
8018  *      a radial gradient. Default is 0.
8019  * @property {Number} endRadius The radius of the ending circle
8020  *      of a radial gradient. Default is 100.
8021  * @property {Number} colorStops The color stops for the
8022  *      gradient. The format for the color stops is: [[position_1, color_1],
8023  *      [position_2, color_2], ...]. The possible color formats are: 'red', '#000',
8024  *      '#000000', 'rgba(0,0,0, 0.2)', [0,0,0] and [0,0,0, 0.2]. Default color stops
8025  *      are [[0, '#000000'], [1, '#FFFFFF']].
8026  */
8027 //Gradient = Klass({
8028 function Gradient() {
8029 	Gradient.prototype.initialize.apply(this, arguments);
8030 }
8031 Gradient.prototype = {
8032   type : 'linear',
8033   isPattern : true,
8034   startX : 0,
8035   startY : 0,
8036   endX : 1,
8037   endY : 0,
8038   startRadius : 0,
8039   endRadius : 1,
8040   colorStops : [],
8041 
8042   /** @override */ initialize : function(config) {
8043     this.colorStops = [[0, '#000000'], [1, '#FFFFFF']]
8044     if (config) Object.extend(this, config)
8045   },
8046 
8047   /**
8048      * Compiles the gradient using the given drawing context. Returns a gradient
8049      * object that can be used as drawing context fill/strokeStyle.
8050      * 
8051      * @param ctx
8052      *            Drawing context to compile pattern on.
8053      * @return Gradient object.
8054      */
8055   compile : function(ctx) {
8056     if (this.type == 'linear') {
8057       var go = ctx.createLinearGradient(
8058                     this.startX, this.startY,
8059                     this.endX, this.endY)
8060     } else {
8061       var go = ctx.createRadialGradient(
8062                     this.startX, this.startY, this.startRadius,
8063                     this.endX, this.endY, this.endRadius)
8064     }
8065     for(var i=0; i<this.colorStops.length; i++) {
8066       var cs = this.colorStops[i]
8067       if (typeof(cs[1]) == 'string') {
8068         go.addColorStop(cs[0], cs[1])
8069       } else {
8070         var ca = cs[1]
8071         var a = (ca.length == 3) ? 1 : ca[3]
8072         var g = 'rgba('+ca.slice(0,3).map(Math.round).join(",")+', '+a+')'
8073         go.addColorStop(cs[0], g)
8074       }
8075     }
8076     Object.extend(go, Transformable)
8077     go.transformList = this.transformList
8078     go.scale = this.scale
8079     go.x = this.x
8080     go.y = this.y
8081     go.matrix = this.matrix
8082     go.rotation = this.rotation
8083     go.units = this.units
8084     if (!go.isMockObject)
8085       this.compiled = go
8086     return go
8087   }
8088 };

8161 /**
8162  * SVG parser for simple documents. Converts SVG DOM to CAKE scenegraph.
8163  * Emphasis on graphical images, not on the "HTML-killer" features of SVG.
8164  * 
8165  * var svgNode = SVGParser.parse( svgRootElement, filename, containerWidth,
8166  * containerHeight, fontSize )
8167  * 
8168  * Features: <svg> width and height, viewBox clipping. Clipping
8169  * (objectBoundingBox clipping too) Paths, rectangles, ellipses, circles, lines,
8170  * polylines and polygons Simple untransformed text using HTML Nested transforms
8171  * Transform lists (transform="rotate(30) translate(2,2) scale(4)") Gradient and
8172  * pattern transforms Strokes with miter, joins and caps Flat fills and gradient
8173  * fills, ditto for strokes Parsing simple stylesheets (tag, class or id) Images
8174  * Non-pixel units (cm, mm, in, pt, pc, em, ex, %) <use>-tags
8175  * preserveAspectRatio Dynamic gradient sizes (objectBoundingBox, etc.) Markers
8176  * (though buggy)
8177  * 
8178  * Some of the several missing features: Masks Patterns viewBox clipping for
8179  * elements other than <marker> and <svg> Text styling tspan, tref, textPath,
8180  * many things text Fancy style rules (tag .class + #foo > bob#alice { ... })
8181  * Filters Animation Dashed strokes
8182  */
8183 SVGParser = {
8184   /**
8185      * Loads an SVG document using XMLHttpRequest and calls the given onSuccess
8186      * callback with the parsed document. If loading fails, calls onFailure
8187      * instead if one is given. When loading and an onLoading callback is given,
8188      * calls onLoading every time xhr.readyState is 3.
8189      * 
8190      * The callbacks will be called with the following parameters:
8191      * 
8192      * onSuccess(svgNode, xmlHttpRequest, filename, config)
8193      * 
8194      * onFailure(xmlHttpRequest, possibleException, filename, config)
8195      * 
8196      * onLoading(xmlHttpRequest, filename, config)
8197      * 
8198      * Config hash parameters: filename: Filename for the SVG document. Used for
8199      * parsing image paths. width: Width of the bounding box to fit the SVG in.
8200      * height: Height of the bounding box to fit the SVG in. fontSize: Default
8201      * font size for the SVG document. onSuccess: Function to call on successful
8202      * load. Required. onFailure: Function to call on failed load. onLoading:
8203      * Function to call while loading.
8204      * 
8205      * @param config
8206      *            Object of properties to be set on initialization.
8207      * @param filename
8208      *            The URL of the SVG document to load. Must conform to SOP.
8209      */
8210   load : function(filename, config) {
8211     if (!config.onSuccess) throw("Need to provide an onSuccess function.")
8212     if (!config.filename)
8213       config.filename = filename
8214     var xhr = window.XMLHttpRequest ? new XMLHttpRequest() :
8215                                       new ActiveXObject("MSXML2.XMLHTTP.3.0")
8216     xhr.open('GET', filename, true)
8217     xhr.overrideMimeType('text/xml')
8218     var failureFired = false
8219     xhr.onreadystatechange = function() {
8220       if (xhr.readyState == 4) {
8221         if (xhr.status == 200 || xhr.status == 0) {
8222           try {
8223             var svg = xhr.responseXML
8224             var svgNode = SVGParser.parse(svg, config)
8225             svgNode.svgRootElement = svg
8226           } catch(e) {
8227             if (config.onFailure)
8228               config.onFailure(xhr, e, filename, config)
8229             return
8230           }
8231           config.onSuccess(svgNode, xhr, filename, config)
8232         } else {
8233           if (config.onFailure && !failureFired)
8234             config.onFailure(xhr, null, filename, config)
8235         }
8236       } else if (xhr.readyState == 3) {
8237         if (config.onLoading)
8238           config.onLoading(xhr, filename, config)
8239       }
8240     }
8241     try {
8242       xhr.send(null)
8243     } catch(e) {
8244       if (config.onFailure) {
8245         config.onFailure(xhr, e, filename, config)
8246         failureFired = true
8247       }
8248       xhr.abort()
8249     }
8250   },
8251 
8252   /**
8253      * Parses an SVG DOM into CAKE scenegraph.
8254      * 
8255      * Config hash parameters: filename: Filename for the SVG document. Used for
8256      * parsing image paths. width: Width of the bounding box to fit the SVG in.
8257      * height: Height of the bounding box to fit the SVG in. fontSize: Default
8258      * font size for the SVG document. currentColor: HTML text color of the
8259      * containing element.
8260      * 
8261      * @param svgRootElement
8262      *            The root element of the SVG DOM.
8263      * @param config
8264      *            Object of properties to be set on initialization.
8265      * @returns The root CanvasNode of the scenegraph created from the SVG
8266      *          document.
8267      * @type CanvasNode
8268      */
8269   parse : function(svgRootElement, config) {
8270     var n = new CanvasNode()
8271     var w = config.width, h = config.height, fs = config.fontSize
8272     n.innerWidth = w || window.innerWidth
8273     n.innerHeight = h || window.innerHeight
8274     n.innerSize = Math.sqrt(w*w + h*h) / Math.sqrt(2)
8275     n.fontSize = fs || 12
8276     n.filename = config.filename || '.'
8277     var defs = {}
8278     var style = { ids : {}, classes : {}, tags : {} }
8279     n.color = config.currentColor || 'black'
8280     this.parseChildren(svgRootElement, n, defs, style)
8281     n.defs = defs
8282     n.style = style
8283     return n
8284   },
8285 
8286   parsePreserveAspectRatio : function(aspect, w, h, vpw, vph) {
8287     var aspect = aspect || ""
8288     var aspa = aspect.split(/\s+/)
8289     var defer = (aspa[0] == 'defer')
8290     if (defer) aspa.shift()
8291     var align = (aspa[0] || 'xMidYMid')
8292     var meet = (aspa[1] || 'meet')
8293     var wf = w / vpw
8294     var hf = h / vph
8295     var xywh = {x:0, y:0, w:wf, h:hf}
8296     if (align == 'none') return xywh
8297     xywh.w = xywh.h = (meet == 'meet' ? Math.min : Math.max)(wf, hf)
8298     var xa = align.slice(1, 4).toLowerCase()
8299     var ya = align.slice(5, 8).toLowerCase()
8300     var xf = (this.SVGAlignMap[xa] || 0)
8301     var yf = (this.SVGAlignMap[ya] || 0)
8302     xywh.x = xf * (w-vpw*xywh.w)
8303     xywh.y = yf * (h-vph*xywh.h)
8304     return xywh
8305   },
8306 
8307   SVGAlignMap : {
8308     min : 0,
8309     mid : 0.5,
8310     max : 1
8311   },
8312 
8313   SVGTagMapping : {
8314     svg : function(c, cn, defs, style) {
8315       var p = new Rectangle()
8316       p.width = 0
8317       p.height = 0
8318       p.doFill = function(){}
8319       p.doStroke = function(){}
8320       p.drawMarkers = function(){}
8321       p.fill = 'black'
8322       p.stroke = 'none'
8323       var vb = c.getAttribute('viewBox')
8324       var w = c.getAttribute('width')
8325       var h = c.getAttribute('height')
8326       if (!w) w = h
8327       else if (!h) h = w
8328       if (w) {
8329         var wpx = this.parseUnit(w, cn, 'x')
8330         var hpx = this.parseUnit(h, cn, 'y')
8331       }
8332       if (vb) {
8333         xywh = vb.match(/[-+]?\d+/g).map(parseFloat)
8334         p.cx = xywh[0]
8335         p.cy = xywh[1]
8336         p.width = xywh[2]
8337         p.height = xywh[3]
8338         var iw = cn.innerWidth = p.width
8339         var ih = cn.innerHeight = p.height
8340         cn.innerSize = Math.sqrt(iw*iw + ih*ih) / Math.sqrt(2)
8341         if (c.getAttribute('overflow') != 'visible')
8342           p.clip = true
8343       }
8344       if (w) {
8345         if (vb) { // nuts, let's parse the alignment :|
8346           var aspect = c.getAttribute('preserveAspectRatio')
8347           var align = this.parsePreserveAspectRatio(aspect,
8348             wpx, hpx,
8349             p.width, p.height)
8350           p.cx -= align.x / align.w
8351           p.cy -= align.y / align.h
8352           p.width = wpx / align.w
8353           p.height = hpx / align.h
8354           p.x += align.x
8355           p.y += align.y
8356           p.scale = [align.w, align.h]
8357         }
8358         // wrong place!
8359         cn.docWidth = wpx
8360         cn.docHeight = hpx
8361       }
8362       return p
8363     },
8364 
8365     marker : function(c, cn) {
8366       var p = new CanvasNode()
8367       p.draw = function(ctx) {
8368         if (this.overflow != 'hidden' && this.viewBox) return
8369         ctx.beginPath()
8370         ctx.rect(
8371           this.viewBox[0],this.viewBox[1],
8372           this.viewBox[2],this.viewBox[3]
8373         )
8374         ctx.clip()
8375       }
8376       var x = -this.parseUnit(c.getAttribute('refX'), cn, 'x') || 0
8377       var y = -this.parseUnit(c.getAttribute('refY'), cn, 'y') || 0
8378       p.transformList = [['translate', [x,y]]]
8379       p.markerUnits = c.getAttribute('markerUnits') || 'strokeWidth'
8380       p.markerWidth = this.parseUnit(c.getAttribute('markerWidth'), cn, 'x') || 3
8381       p.markerHeight = this.parseUnit(
8382                           c.getAttribute('markerHeight'), cn, 'y') ||
8383                           3
8384       p.overflow = c.getAttribute('overflow') || 'hidden'
8385       p.viewBox = c.getAttribute('viewBox')
8386       p.orient = c.getAttribute('orient') || 0
8387       if (p.orient && p.orient != 'auto')
8388         p.orient = parseFloat(p.orient)*SVGMapping.DEG_TO_RAD_FACTOR
8389       if (p.viewBox) {
8390         p.viewBox = p.viewBox.strip().split(/[\s,]+/g).map(parseFloat)
8391         var vbw = p.viewBox[2] - p.viewBox[0]
8392         var vbh = p.viewBox[3] - p.viewBox[1]
8393         if (p.markerWidth) {
8394           var sx = sy = Math.min(
8395             p.markerWidth / vbw,
8396             p.markerHeight / vbh
8397           )
8398           p.transformList.unshift(['scale', [sx,sy]])
8399         }
8400       }
8401       return p
8402     },

8407       return p

8429     parseAnimateTag : function(c, cn) {
8430       var after = SVGParser.SVGTagMapping.parseTime(c.getAttribute('begin'))
8431       var dur = SVGParser.SVGTagMapping.parseTime(c.getAttribute('dur'))
8432       var end = SVGParser.SVGTagMapping.parseTime(c.getAttribute('end'))
8433       if (dur == null) dur = end-after
8434       dur = isNaN(dur) ? 0 : dur
8435       var variable = c.getAttribute('attributeName')
8436       var fill = c.getAttribute('fill')
8437       if (cn.tagName == 'rect') {
8438         if (variable == 'x') variable = 'cx'
8439         if (variable == 'y') variable = 'cy'
8440       }
8441       var accum = c.getAttribute('accumulate') == 'sum'
8442       var additive = c.getAttribute('additive')
8443       if (additive) additive = additive == 'sum'
8444       else additive = accum
8445       var repeat = c.getAttribute('repeatCount')
8446       if (repeat == 'indefinite') repeat = true
8447       else repeat = parseFloat(repeat)
8448       if (!repeat && dur > 0) {
8449         var repeatDur = c.getAttribute('repeatDur')
8450         if (repeatDur == 'indefinite') repeat = true
8451         else repeat = SVGParser.SVGTagMapping.parseTime(repeatDur) / dur
8452       }
8453       return {
8454         after: isNaN(after) ? 0 : after,
8455         duration: dur,
8456         restart: c.getAttribute('restart'),
8457         calcMode : c.getAttribute('calcMode'),
8458         additive : additive,
8459         accumulate : accum,
8460         repeat : repeat,
8461         variable: variable,
8462         fill: fill
8463       }
8464     },
8465 
8466     parseTime : function(value) {
8467       if (!value) return null
8468       if (value.match(/[0-9]$/)) {
8469         var hms = value.split(":")
8470         var s = hms[hms.length-1] || 0
8471         var m = hms[hms.length-2] || 0
8472         var h = hms[hms.length-3] || 0
8473         return (parseFloat(h)*3600 + parseFloat(m)*60 + parseFloat(s)) * 1000
8474       } else {
8475         var fac = 60
8476         if (value.match(/s$/i)) fac = 1
8477         else if (value.match(/h$/i)) fac = 3600
8478         return parseFloat(value) * fac * 1000
8479       }
8480     },
8481

8486 
8487     animate : function(c, cn) {
8488       var from = this.parseUnit(c.getAttribute('from'), cn, 'x')
8489       var to = this.parseUnit(c.getAttribute('to'), cn, 'x')
8490       var by = this.parseUnit(c.getAttribute('by'), cn, 'x')
8491       var o = SVGParser.SVGTagMapping.parseAnimateTag(c, cn)
8492       if (c.getAttribute('values')) {
8493         var self = this
8494         var vals = c.getAttribute('values')
8495         vals = vals.split(";").map(function(v) {
8496           var xy = v.split(/[, ]+/)
8497           if (xy.length > 2) {
8498             return xy.map(function(x){ return self.parseUnit(x, cn, 'x') })
8499           } else if (xy.length > 1) {
8500             return [
8501               self.parseUnit(xy[0], cn, 'x'),
8502               self.parseUnit(xy[1], cn, 'y')
8503             ]
8504           } else {
8505             return self.parseUnit(v, cn, 'x')
8506           }
8507         })
8508       } else {
8509         if (to == null) to = from + by
8510       }
8511       cn.after(o.after, function() {
8512         if (o.fill == 'remove') {
8513           var orig = Object.clone(this[o.variable])
8514           this.after(o.duration, function(){ this[o.variable] = orig })
8515         }
8516         if (vals) {
8517           if (o.additive) {
8518             var ov = this[o.variable]
8519             vals = vals.map(function(v){
8520               return Object.sum(v, ov)
8521             })
8522           }
8523           var length = 0
8524           var lens = []
8525           if (vals[0] instanceof Array) {
8526             for (var i=1; i<vals.length; i++) {
8527               var diff = Object.sub(vals[i] - vals[i-1])
8528               var sl = Math.sqrt(diff.reduce(function(s, i) { return s + i*i }, 0))
8529               lens.push(sl)
8530               length += sl
8531             }
8532           } else {
8533             for (var i=1; i<vals.length; i++) {
8534               var sl = Math.abs(vals[i] - vals[i-1])
8535               lens.push(sl)
8536               length += sl
8537             }
8538           }
8539           var animator = function(pos) {
8540             if (pos == 1) {
8541               this[o.variable] = vals[vals.length-1]
8542             } else {
8543               if (o.calcMode == 'paced') {
8544                 var len = pos * length
8545                 var rlen = 0, idx, rt
8546                 for (var i=0; i<lens.length; i++) {
8547                   if (rlen + lens[i] > len) {
8548                     idx = i
8549                     rt = (len - rlen) / lens[i]
8550                     break
8551                   }
8552                   rlen += lens[i]
8553                 }
8554                 var v0 = idx
8555                 var v1 = v0 + 1
8556               } else {
8557                 var idx = pos * (vals.length-1)
8558                 var v0 = Math.floor(idx)
8559                 var rt = idx - v0
8560                 var v1 = v0 + 1
8561               }
8562               this.tweenVariable(o.variable, vals[v0], vals[v1], rt, o.calcMode)
8563             }
8564           }
8565           this.animate(animator, from, to, o.duration, 'linear', {
8566             repeat: o.repeat,
8567             additive: o.additive,
8568             accumulate: o.accumulate
8569           })
8570         } else {
8571           if (from == null) {
8572             from = this[o.variable]
8573             if (by != null) to = from + by
8574           }
8575           if (o.additive) {
8576             from = Object.sum(from, this[o.variable])
8577             to = Object.sum(to, this[o.variable])
8578           }
8579           this.animate(o.variable, from, to, o.duration, o.calcMode, {
8580             repeat: o.repeat,
8581             additive: o.additive,
8582             accumulate: o.accumulate
8583           })
8584         }
8585       })
8586     },
8587 
8588     set : function(c, cn) {
8589       var to = c.getAttribute('to')
8590       var o = SVGParser.SVGTagMapping.parseAnimateTag(c, cn)
8591       cn.after(o.after, function() {
8592         if (o.fill == 'remove') {
8593           var orig = Object.clone(this[o.variable])
8594           this.after(o.duration, function(){ this[o.variable] = orig })
8595         }
8596         this[o.variable] = to
8597       })
8598     },
8599 
8600     animateMotion : function(c,cn) {
8601       var path
8602       if (c.getAttribute('path')) {
8603         path = new Path(c.getAttribute('path'))
8604       } else if (c.getAttribute('values')) {
8605         var vals = c.getAttribute('values')
8606         path = new Path("M" + vals.split(";").join("L"))
8607       } else if (c.getAttribute('from') || c.getAttribute('to') || c.getAttribute('by')) {
8608         var from = c.getAttribute('from')
8609         var to = c.getAttribute('to')
8610         var by = c.getAttribute('by')
8611         if (!from) from = "0,0"
8612         if (!to) to = "l" + by
8613         else to = "L" + to
8614         path = new Path("M" + from + to)
8615       }
8616       var p = new CanvasNode()
8617       p.__motionPath = path
8618       var rotate = c.getAttribute('rotate')
8619       var o = SVGParser.SVGTagMapping.parseAnimateTag(c, cn)
8620       cn.after(o.after, function() {
8621         if (o.fill == 'remove') {
8622           var ox = this.x, oy = this.y
8623           this.after(o.duration, function(){ this.x = ox; this.y = oy})
8624         }
8625         var motion = function(pos) {
8626           var pa = p.__motionPath.pointAngleAt(pos, {
8627             discrete: o.calcMode == 'discrete',
8628             linear : o.calcMode == 'linear'
8629           })
8630           this.x = pa.point[0]
8631           this.y = pa.point[1]
8632           if (rotate == 'auto') {
8633             this.rotation = pa.angle
8634           } else if (rotate == 'auto-reverse') {
8635             this.rotation = pa.angle + Math.PI
8636           }
8637         }
8638         this.animate(motion, 0, 1, o.duration, 'linear', {
8639           repeat: o.repeat,
8640           additive: o.additive,
8641           accumulate: o.accumulate
8642         })
8643       })
8644       return p
8645     },
8646

8655     animateColor : function(c, cn, defs) {

8659       to = SVGParser.SVGMapping.__parseStyle(to, null, defs)
8660       var o = SVGParser.SVGTagMapping.parseAnimateTag(c, cn)
8661       cn.after(o.after, function() {
8662         if (o.fill == 'remove') {
8663           var orig = Object.clone(this[o.variable])
8664           this.after(o.duration, function(){ this[o.variable] = orig })
8665         }
8666         this.animate(o.variable, from, to, o.duration, 'linear', {
8667           repeat: o.repeat,
8668           additive: o.additive,

8670         })

8674     animateTransform : function(c, cn) {
8675       var from = c.getAttribute('from')
8676       var to = c.getAttribute('to')
8677       var by = c.getAttribute('by')
8678       var o = SVGParser.SVGTagMapping.parseAnimateTag(c, cn)
8679       if (from) from = from.split(/[ ,]+/).map(parseFloat)
8680       if (to) to = to.split(/[ ,]+/).map(parseFloat)
8681       if (by) by = by.split(/[ ,]+/).map(parseFloat)
8682       o.variable = c.getAttribute('type')
8683       if (o.variable == 'rotate') {
8684         o.variable = 'rotation'
8685         if (from) from = from.map(function(v) { return v * Math.PI/180 })
8686         if (to) to = to.map(function(v) { return v * Math.PI/180 })
8687         if (by) by = by.map(function(v) { return v * Math.PI/180 })
8688       } else if (o.variable.match(/^skew/)) {
8689         if (from) from = from.map(function(v) { return v * Math.PI/180 })
8690         if (to) to = to.map(function(v) { return v * Math.PI/180 })
8691         if (by) by = by.map(function(v) { return v * Math.PI/180 })
8692       }
8693       if (to == null) to = Object.sum(from, by)
8694       cn.after(o.after, function() {
8695         if (o.variable == 'translate') {
8696           if (from == null) {
8697             from = [this.x, this.y]
8698             if (by != null) to = Object.sum(from, by)
8699           }
8700           if (o.fill == 'remove') {
8701             var ox = this.x
8702             var oy = this.y
8703             this.after(o.duration, function(){ this.x = ox; this.y = oy })
8704           }
8705           this.animate('x', from[0], to[0], o.duration, 'linear', {
8706             repeat: o.repeat,
8707             additive: o.additive,
8708             accumulate: o.accumulate
8709           })
8710           if (from[1] != null) {
8711             this.animate('y', from[1], to[1], o.duration, 'linear', {
8712               repeat: o.repeat,
8713               additive: o.additive,
8714               accumulate: o.accumulate
8715             })
8716           }
8717         } else {
8718           if (from) {
8719             if (from.length == 1) from = from[0]
8720           }
8721           if (to) {
8722             if (to.length == 1) to = to[0]
8723           }
8724           if (by) {
8725             if (by.length == 1) by = by[0]
8726           }
8727           if (from == null) {
8728             from = this[o.variable]
8729             if (by != null) to = Object.sum(from, by)
8730           }
8731           if (o.variable == 'scale' && o.additive) {
8732             // +1 in SMIL's additive scale means *1, welcome to brokenville
8733             o.additive = false
8734           }
8735           if (o.fill == 'remove') {
8736             var orig = Object.clone(this[o.variable])
8737             this.after(o.duration, function(){ this[o.variable] = orig })
8738           }
8739           this.animate(o.variable, from, to, o.duration, 'linear', {
8740             repeat: o.repeat,
8741             additive: o.additive,
8742             accumulate: o.accumulate
8743           })
8744         }
8745       })
8746     },

8756     use : function(c, cn, defs, style) {

8758                 c.getAttribute('href')

8760       if (id) {

8764           var par = p.parent
8765           if (par) {
8766             if (p.stroke) oc.stroke = p.stroke
8767             if (p.fill) oc.fill = p.fill
8768             p.append(oc)
8769           } else {
8770             p = oc
8771           }
8772         })
8773       }
8774       return p

8870     linearGradient : function(c, cn,defs,style) {
8871       var g = new Gradient({type:'linear'})
8872       g.color = cn.color
8873       if (c.getAttribute('color')) {
8874         SVGParser.SVGMapping.color(g, c.getAttribute('color'), defs, style)
8875       }
8876       g.svgNode = c
8877       var x1 = c.getAttribute('x1')
8878       var y1 = c.getAttribute('y1')
8879       var x2 = c.getAttribute('x2')
8880       var y2 = c.getAttribute('y2')
8881       var transform = c.getAttribute('gradientTransform')
8882       g.units = c.getAttribute('gradientUnits') || "objectBoundingBox"
8883       if (x1) g.startX = parseFloat(x1) * (x1.charAt(x1.length-1) == '%' ? 0.01 : 1)
8884       if (y1) g.startY = parseFloat(y1) * (y1.charAt(y1.length-1) == '%' ? 0.01 : 1)
8885       if (x2) g.endX = parseFloat(x2) * (x2.charAt(x2.length-1) == '%' ? 0.01 : 1)
8886       if (y2) g.endY = parseFloat(y2) * (y2.charAt(y2.length-1) == '%' ? 0.01 : 1)
8887       if (transform) this.applySVGTransform(g, transform, defs, style)
8888       this.parseStops(g, c, defs, style)
8889       return g
8890     },
8891 
8892     radialGradient : function(c, cn, defs, style) {
8893       var g = new Gradient({type:'radial'})
8894       g.color = cn.color
8895       if (c.getAttribute('color')) {
8896         SVGParser.SVGMapping.color(g, c.getAttribute('color'), defs, style)
8897       }
8898       g.svgNode = c
8899       var r = c.getAttribute('r')
8900       var fx = c.getAttribute('fx')
8901       var fy = c.getAttribute('fy')
8902       var cx = c.getAttribute('cx')
8903       var cy = c.getAttribute('cy')
8904       var transform = c.getAttribute('gradientTransform')
8905       g.units = c.getAttribute('gradientUnits') || "objectBoundingBox"
8906       if (r) g.endRadius = parseFloat(r) * (r.charAt(r.length-1) == '%' ? 0.01 : 1)
8907       if (fx) g.startX = parseFloat(fx) * (fx.charAt(fx.length-1) == '%' ? 0.01 : 1)
8908       if (fy) g.startY = parseFloat(fy) * (fy.charAt(fy.length-1) == '%' ? 0.01 : 1)
8909       if (cx) g.endX = parseFloat(cx) * (cx.charAt(cx.length-1) == '%' ? 0.01 : 1)
8910       if (cy) g.endY = parseFloat(cy) * (cy.charAt(cy.length-1) == '%' ? 0.01 : 1)
8911       if (transform) this.applySVGTransform(g, transform, defs, style)
8912       this.parseStops(g, c, defs, style)
8913       return g
8914     }
8915   },
8916 
8917   parseChildren : function(node, canvasNode, defs, style) {
8918     var childNodes = []
8919     var cn = canvasNode
8920     for (var i=0; i<node.childNodes.length; i++) {
8921       var c = node.childNodes[i]
8922       var p = false // argh, remember to initialize vars inside loops
8923       if (c.childNodes) {
8924         if (c.tagName) {
8925           if (this.SVGTagMapping[c.tagName]) {
8926             p = this.SVGTagMapping[c.tagName].call(
8927                   this, c, canvasNode, defs, style)
8928           } else {
8929             p = new CanvasNode()
8930           }
8931           if (p) {
8932             p.root = canvasNode.root
8933             p.fontSize = cn.fontSize
8934             p.strokeWidth = cn.strokeWidth
8935             if (c.attributes) {
8936               for (var j=0; j<c.attributes.length; j++) {
8937                 var attr = c.attributes[j]
8938                 if (this.SVGMapping[attr.nodeName])
8939                   this.SVGMapping[attr.nodeName](p, attr.nodeValue, defs, style)
8940               }
8941             }
8942             if (p.id) {
8943               this.setDef(defs, p.id, p)
8944             }
8945             p.tagName = c.tagName
8946             this.applySVGTransform(p, c.getAttribute("transform"), defs, style)
8947             this.applySVGStyle(p, c.getAttribute("style"), defs, style)
8948             if (p.tagName && style.tags[p.tagName])
8949               this.applySVGStyle(p, style.tags[p.tagName], defs, style)
8950             if (p.className && style.classes[p.className])
8951               this.applySVGStyle(p, style.classes[p.className], defs, style)
8952             if (p.id && style.ids[p.id])
8953               this.applySVGStyle(p, style.ids[p.id], defs, style)
8954             if (!p.marker) p.marker = cn.marker
8955             if (!p.markerStart) p.markerStart = cn.markerStart
8956             if (!p.markerEnd) p.markerEnd = cn.markerEnd
8957             if (!p.markerMid) p.markerMid = cn.markerMid
8958           }
8959         }
8960         if (p && p.setRoot) {
8961           p.zIndex = i
8962           canvasNode.append(p)
8963           this.parseChildren(c, p, defs, style)
8964         }
8965       }
8966     }
8967   },
8968 
8969   parseStyle : function(node, style) {
8970     var text = node.textContent
8971     var segs = text.split(/\}/m)
8972     for (var i=0; i<segs.length; i++) {
8973       var seg = segs[i]
8974       var kv = seg.split(/\{/m)
8975       if (kv.length < 2) continue
8976       var key = kv[0].strip()
8977       var value = kv[1].strip()
8978       switch (key.charAt(0)) {
8979         case '.':
8980           style.classes[key.slice(1)] = value
8981           break;
8982         case '#':
8983           style.ids[key.slice(1)] = value
8984           break;
8985         default:
8986           style.tags[key] = value
8987           break;
8988       }
8989     }
8990   },
8991 
8992   parseStops : function(g, node, defs, style) {
8993     var href = node.getAttribute('xlink:href')
8994     g.colorStops = []
8995     if (href) {
8996       href = href.replace(/^#/,'')
8997       this.getDef(defs, href, function(g2) {
8998         if (g.colorStops.length == 0)
8999           g.colorStops = g2.colorStops
9000       })
9001     }
9002     var stops = []
9003     for (var i=0; i<node.childNodes.length; i++) {
9004       var c = node.childNodes[i]
9005       if (c.tagName == 'stop') {
9006         var offset = parseFloat(c.getAttribute('offset'))
9007         if (c.getAttribute('offset').search(/%/) != -1)
9008           offset *= 0.01
9009         var stop = [offset]
9010         stop.color = g.color
9011         for (var j=0; j<c.attributes.length; j++) {
9012           var attr = c.attributes[j]
9013           if (this.SVGMapping[attr.nodeName])
9014             this.SVGMapping[attr.nodeName](stop, attr.nodeValue, defs, style)
9015         }
9016         this.applySVGStyle(stop, c.getAttribute('style'), defs, style)
9017         var id = c.getAttribute('id')
9018         if (id) this.setDef(defs, id, stop)
9019         stops.push(stop)
9020       }
9021     }
9022     if (stops.length > 0)
9023       g.colorStops = stops
9024   },
9025 
9026   applySVGTransform : function(node, transform, defs, style) {
9027     if (!transform) return
9028     node.transformList = []
9029     var segs = transform.match(/[a-z]+\s*\([^)]*\)/ig)
9030     for (var i=0; i<segs.length; i++) {
9031       var kv = segs[i].split("(")
9032       var k = kv[0].strip()
9033       if (this.SVGMapping[k]) {
9034         var v = kv[1].strip().slice(0,-1)
9035         this.SVGMapping[k](node, v, defs, style)
9036       }
9037     }
9038     this.breakDownTransformList(node)
9039   },
9040 
9041   breakDownTransformList : function(node) {
9042     var tl = node.transformList
9043     if (node.transformList.length == 1) {
9044       var tr = tl[0]
9045       if (tr[0] == 'translate') {
9046         node.x = tr[1][0]
9047         node.y = tr[1][1]
9048       } else if (tr[0] == 'scale') {
9049         node.scale = tr[1]
9050       } else if (tr[0] == 'rotate') {
9051         node.rotation = tr[1]
9052       } else if (tr[0] == 'matrix') {
9053         node.matrix = tr[1]
9054       } else if (tr[0] == 'skewX') {
9055         node.skewX = tr[1][0]
9056       } else if (tr[0] == 'skewY') {
9057         node.skewY = tr[1][0]
9058       } else {
9059         return
9060       }
9061       node.transformList = null
9062     }
9063   },
9064 
9065   applySVGStyle : function(node, style, defs, st) {
9066     if (!style) return
9067     var segs = style.split(";")
9068     for (var i=0; i<segs.length; i++) {
9069       var kv = segs[i].split(":")
9070       var k = kv[0].strip()
9071       if (this.SVGMapping[k]) {
9072         var v = kv[1].strip()
9073         this.SVGMapping[k](node, v, defs, st)
9074       }
9075     }
9076   },
9077 
9078   getDef : function(defs, id, f) {
9079     if (defs[id] && defs[id] instanceof Array) {
9080       defs[id].push(f)
9081     } else if (defs[id]) {
9082       f(defs[id])
9083     } else {
9084       defs[id] = [f]
9085     }
9086   },
9087 
9088   setDef : function(defs, id, obj) {
9089     if (defs[id] && defs[id] instanceof Array) {
9090       for (var i=0; i<defs[id].length; i++) {
9091         defs[id][i](obj)
9092       }
9093     }
9094     defs[id] = obj
9095   },
9096 
9097   parseUnit : function(v, parent, dir) {
9098     if (v == null) {
9099       return null
9100     } else {
9101       return this.parseUnitMultiplier(v, parent, dir) * parseFloat(v.strip())
9102     }
9103   },
9104 
9105   parseUnitMultiplier : function(str, parent, dir) {
9106     var cm = this.getCmInPixels()
9107     if (str.search(/cm$/i) != -1)
9108       return cm
9109     else if (str.search(/mm$/i) != -1)
9110       return 0.1 * cm
9111     else if (str.search(/pt$/i) != -1)
9112       return 0.0352777778 * cm
9113     else if (str.search(/pc$/i) != -1)
9114       return 0.4233333333 * cm
9115     else if (str.search(/in$/i) != -1)
9116       return 2.54 * cm
9117     else if (str.search(/em$/i) != -1)
9118       return parent.fontSize
9119     else if (str.search(/ex$/i) != -1)
9120       return parent.fontSize / 2
9121     else if (str.search(/%$/i) != -1)
9122       if (dir == 'x')
9123         return parent.root.innerWidth * 0.01
9124       else if (dir == 'y')
9125         return parent.root.innerHeight * 0.01
9126       else
9127         return parent.root.innerSize * 0.01
9128     else
9129       return 1
9130   },
9131 
9132   getCmInPixels : function() {
9133     if (!this.cmInPixels) {
9134       var e = E('div',{ style: {
9135         margin: '0px',
9136         padding: '0px',
9137         width: '1cm',
9138         height: '1cm',
9139         position: 'absolute',
9140         visibility: 'hidden'
9141       }})
9142       document.body.appendChild(e)
9143       var cm = e.offsetWidth
9144       document.body.removeChild(e)
9145       this.cmInPixels = cm || 38
9146     }
9147     return this.cmInPixels
9148   },
9149 
9150   getEmInPixels : function() {
9151     if (!this.emInPixels) {
9152       var e = E('div',{ style: {
9153         margin: '0px',
9154         padding: '0px',
9155         width: '1em',
9156         height: '1em',
9157         position: 'absolute',
9158         visibility: 'hidden'
9159       }})
9160       document.body.appendChild(e)
9161       var em = e.offsetWidth
9162       document.body.removeChild(e)
9163       this.emInPixels = em || 12
9164     }
9165     return this.emInPixels
9166   },
9167 
9168   getExInPixels : function() {
9169     if (!this.exInPixels) {
9170       var e = E('div',{ style: {
9171         margin: '0px',
9172         padding: '0px',
9173         width: '1ex',
9174         height: '1ex',
9175         position: 'absolute',
9176         visibility: 'hidden'
9177       }})
9178       document.body.appendChild(e)
9179       var ex = e.offsetWidth
9180       document.body.removeChild(e)
9181       this.exInPixels = ex || 6
9182     }
9183     return this.exInPixels
9184   },

9186   SVGMapping : {
9187     DEG_TO_RAD_FACTOR : Math.PI / 180,
9188     RAD_TO_DEG_FACTOR : 180 / Math.PI,
9189 
9190     parseUnit : function(v, cn, dir) {
9191       return SVGParser.parseUnit(v, cn, dir)
9192     },
9193 
9194     "class" : function(node, v) {
9195       node.className = v
9196     },
9197 
9198     marker : function(node, v, defs) {
9199       SVGParser.getDef(defs, v.replace(/^url\(#|\)$/g, ''), function(g) {
9200         node.marker = g
9201       })
9202     },
9203 
9204     "marker-start" : function(node, v, defs) {
9205       SVGParser.getDef(defs, v.replace(/^url\(#|\)$/g, ''), function(g) {
9206         node.markerStart = g
9207       })
9208     },
9209 
9210     "marker-end" : function(node, v, defs) {
9211       SVGParser.getDef(defs, v.replace(/^url\(#|\)$/g, ''), function(g) {
9212         node.markerEnd = g
9213       })
9214     },
9215 
9216     "marker-mid" : function(node, v, defs) {
9217       SVGParser.getDef(defs, v.replace(/^url\(#|\)$/g, ''), function(g) {
9218         node.markerMid = g
9219       })
9220     },
9221 
9222     "clip-path" : function(node, v, defs) {
9223       SVGParser.getDef(defs, v.replace(/^url\(#|\)$/g, ''), function(g) {
9224         node.clipPath = g
9225       })
9226     },
9227 
9228     id : function(node, v) {
9229       node.id = v
9230     },
9231 
9232     translate : function(node, v) {
9233       var xy = v.split(/[\s,]+/).map(parseFloat)
9234       node.transformList.push(['translate', [xy[0], xy[1] || 0]])
9235     },
9236 
9237     rotate : function(node, v) {
9238       if (v == 'auto' || v == 'auto-reverse') return
9239       var rot = v.split(/[\s,]+/).map(parseFloat)
9240       var angle = rot[0] * this.DEG_TO_RAD_FACTOR
9241       if (rot.length > 1)
9242         node.transformList.push(['rotate', [angle, rot[1], rot[2] || 0]])
9243       else
9244         node.transformList.push(['rotate', [angle]])
9245     },
9246 
9247     scale : function(node, v) {
9248       var xy = v.split(/[\s,]+/).map(parseFloat)
9249       var trans = ['scale']
9250       if (xy.length > 1)
9251         trans[1] = [xy[0], xy[1]]
9252       else
9253         trans[1] = [xy[0], xy[0]]
9254       node.transformList.push(trans)
9255     },
9256 
9257     matrix : function(node, v) {
9258       var mat = v.split(/[\s,]+/).map(parseFloat)
9259       node.transformList.push(['matrix', mat])
9260     },
9261 
9262     skewX : function(node, v) {
9263       var angle = parseFloat(v)*this.DEG_TO_RAD_FACTOR
9264       node.transformList.push(['skewX', [angle]])
9265     },
9266 
9267     skewY : function(node, v) {
9268       var angle = parseFloat(v)*this.DEG_TO_RAD_FACTOR
9269       node.transformList.push(['skewY', [angle]])
9270     },
9271 
9272     opacity : function(node, v) {
9273       node.opacity = parseFloat(v)
9274     },
9275 
9276     display : function (node, v) {
9277       node.display = v
9278     },
9279 
9280     visibility : function (node, v) {
9281       node.visibility = v
9282     },
9283 
9284     'stroke-miterlimit' : function(node, v) {
9285       node.miterLimit = parseFloat(v)
9286     },
9287 
9288     'stroke-linecap' : function(node, v) {
9289       node.lineCap = v
9290     },
9291 
9292     'stroke-linejoin' : function(node, v) {
9293       node.lineJoin = v
9294     },
9295 
9296     'stroke-width' : function(node, v) {
9297       node.strokeWidth = this.parseUnit(v, node)
9298     },
9299 
9300     fill : function(node, v, defs, style) {
9301       node.fill = this.__parseStyle(v, node.fill, defs, node.color)
9302     },
9303 
9304     stroke : function(node, v, defs, style) {
9305       node.stroke = this.__parseStyle(v, node.stroke, defs, node.color)
9306     },
9307 
9308     color : function(node, v, defs, style) {
9309       if (v == 'inherit') return
9310       node.color = this.__parseStyle(v, false, defs, node.color)
9311     },
9312 
9313     'stop-color' : function(node, v, defs, style) {
9314       if (v == 'none') {
9315         node[1] = [0,0,0,0]
9316       } else {
9317         node[1] = this.__parseStyle(v, node[1], defs, node.color)
9318       }
9319     },
9320 
9321     'fill-opacity' : function(node, v) {
9322       node.fillOpacity = Math.min(1,Math.max(0,parseFloat(v)))
9323     },
9324 
9325     'stroke-opacity' : function(node, v) {
9326       node.strokeOpacity = Math.min(1,Math.max(0,parseFloat(v)))
9327     },
9328 
9329     'stop-opacity' : function(node, v) {
9330       node[1] = node[1] || [0,0,0]
9331       node[1][3] = Math.min(1,Math.max(0,parseFloat(v)))
9332     },
9333 
9334     'text-anchor' : function(node, v) {
9335       node.textAnchor = v
9336       if (node.setAlign) {
9337         if (v == 'middle')
9338           node.setAlign('center')
9339         else
9340           node.setAlign(v)
9341       }
9342     },
9343 
9344     'font-family' : function(node, v) {
9345       node.fontFamily = v
9346     },
9347 
9348     'font-size' : function(node, v) {
9349       node.fontSize = this.parseUnit(v, node)
9350     },
9351 
9352     __parseStyle : function(v, currentStyle, defs, currentColor) {
9353 
9354       if (v.charAt(0) == '#') {
9355         if (v.length == 4)
9356           v = v.replace(/([^#])/g, '$1$1')
9357         var a = v.slice(1).match(/../g).map(
9358           function(i) { return parseInt(i, 16) })
9359         return a
9360 
9361       } else if (v.search(/^rgb\(/) != -1) {
9362         var a = v.slice(4,-1).split(",")
9363         for (var i=0; i<a.length; i++) {
9364           var c = a[i].strip()
9365           if (c.charAt(c.length-1) == '%')
9366             a[i] = Math.round(parseFloat(c.slice(0,-1)) * 2.55)
9367           else
9368             a[i] = parseInt(c)
9369         }
9370         return a
9371 
9372       } else if (v.search(/^rgba\(/) != -1) {
9373         var a = v.slice(5,-1).split(",")
9374         for (var i=0; i<3; i++) {
9375           var c = a[i].strip()
9376           if (c.charAt(c.length-1) == '%')
9377             a[i] = Math.round(parseFloat(c.slice(0,-1)) * 2.55)
9378           else
9379             a[i] = parseInt(c)
9380         }
9381         var c = a[3].strip()
9382         if (c.charAt(c.length-1) == '%')
9383           a[3] = Math.round(parseFloat(c.slice(0,-1)) * 0.01)
9384         else
9385           a[3] = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, parseFloat(c)))
9386         return a
9387 
9388       } else if (v.search(/^url\(/) != -1) {
9389         var id = v.match(/\([^)]+\)/)[0].slice(1,-1).replace(/^#/, '')
9390         if (defs[id]) {
9391           return defs[id]
9392         } else { // missing defs, let's make it known that we're screwed
9393           return 'rgba(255,0,255,1)'
9394         }
9395 
9396       } else if (v == 'currentColor') {
9397         return currentColor
9398 
9399       } else if (v == 'none') {
9400         return 'none'
9401 
9402       } else if (v == 'freeze') { // SMIL is evil, but so are we
9403         return null
9404 
9405       } else if (v == 'remove') {
9406         return null
9407 
9408       } else { // unknown value, maybe it's an ICC color
9409         return v
9410       }
9411     }
9412   }
9413 }
